title: fast'n fancy macaroons
directions: Combine all ingredients, mixing well.
Drop from spoon 1-inch apart on well greased baking sheet.
Decorate with halved maraschino cherries or sugar sprinkles, if desired.
Bake at 350° for 10-12 minutes or until lightly browned.
Remove at once from baking sheets using moistened spatula.
Makes about 5 dozen.

title: cabbage slaw - iowa style
directions: Chop cabbage fine.
Boil remaining ingredients together until blended.
Cool.
Pour over cabbage.
May be prepared the day before serving, stirring occasionally to marinate.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Cut broccoli and cauliflower into flowerets.
Mix the vinegar, mayonnaise and sugar together and pour over vegetables.
Mix well. Sprinkle bacon bits on top.

title: eloise ham's dressing
directions: Put celery and onions in oil and cook until color changes.

title: chicken and dressing
directions: Cook stewing hen in crock pot covered with water. Add salt and pepper. Cook 6 to 8 hours. In a large baking pan crumble corn bread. Add onions, celery, boiled eggs, pimentos, cream of chicken soup, cream of mushroom soup, sage, salt and pepper. Add enough chicken broth to make a loose mixture and mix well. Debone chicken and add some to the dressing. Bake at 350 degrees for about an hour or until it bubbles and firm in the center.

title: deluxe pot roast
directions: Make lengthwise slits halfway through roast.
Insert a garlic slice into each slit.
Rub roast with salt and pepper; dredge in flour.
Brown roast on all sides in hot oil in a large Dutch oven or skillet.
Add sliced onion and wine to roast in Dutch oven.

title: corn bread salad
directions: Mix.
Add salt and pepper to taste. Better next day.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown ground beef, onion and garlic. Drain.
In a large pot, simmer remaining ingredients.
Add ground beef and simmer. Serve with favorite pasta.

title: garda's rum balls
directions: Form into small balls.
Coat with confectioners sugar.
Place on cookie sheet; cover with plastic wrap and let sit 24 to 48 hours.
These are easier and use fewer ingredients than Holiday Rum Balls.

title: dreamy banana salad
directions: Whip the cream.
Put layer of bananas in bottom of rather large shallow dish.
Add layer of crushed pineapple with juice, layer of sliced bananas, layer of whipped cream.
Start again with layer of vanilla wafers, pineapple, bananas and cream (approximately 3 layers).
May add wafer design or sprinkle top with crushed wafers. Refrigerate and serve.

title: baked fish
directions: Lay fish in foil.
Sprinkle garlic salt, pepper and parsley. Spread mayonnaise lightly on fish, cut butter and lay over mayonnaise.
Slice Maui onion and tomato and lay on butter.
Cut green onion in 2-inch pieces and put over butter.
Lay bacon over green onions.
Sprinkle paprika and squeeze juice of lemon over entire dish.
Close foil, put over hibachi for 30 minutes or until bacon is cooked.
Serves 4 to 8.

title: copper carrot pennies(marinated)
directions: Boil
sliced
carrots in salted water until tender, but not soft.
Alternate layers of carrots, pepper rings and onion slices. Make
marinade
of
seasoning
and
soup ingredients. Blend
well and pour over the vegetables.
Refrigerate.
These are good in refrigerator several days.

title: borscht(an easy way)
directions: Put beets in blender with onion and lemon juice and chicken broth.
Blend until slurpy.
Taste for seasoning and add, if necessary.
If you would like this cold, serve right away.
If you would like a hot soup, heat until just under boiling, then serve. Mix the horseradish and sour cream together and put a dollop on top of each serving.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Combine flour, salt and pepper; coat meat with flour.
Brown in hot fat, adding onion, green pepper and mushrooms.
Drain.
Add soup; simmer, covered, for 30 minutes.
Blend in sour cream before serving.
Serve over rice.

title: savannah red rice
directions: Fry bacon, drain and crumble.
Cook pepperoni and celery in the bacon grease.
Add 2 tablespoons ingredients and bacon.
Bring to a boil.
Cover and turn on low.
Cook 45 minutes, unless using Success rice.

title: old-fashioned no cook ice cream
directions: Beat eggs in electric
mixer
until
they
are light in color. Add sugar to eggs and beat at high speed until mixture is thick. Add
vanilla,
salt
and
evaporated milk; continue beating until sugar
is
dissolved.
Mix
thoroughly into the whole milk. Freeze.
(If
frozen or canned fruit is added, it must be well drained.)

title: pineapple delight
directions: Mix and bake cake as directed on package. When cake is baked, poke holes in cake with toothpick.
Pour crushed pineapple with juice over warm cake and spread evenly.
Mix vanilla pudding as directed on package and add cream cheese.
Mix until smooth and spread over cake. Layer Cool Whip over pudding and sprinkle heavily with coconut.

title: lemon pie(9-inch)
directions: Bake 9-inch pie shell at 400°.
Mix sugar and cornstarch together; add water 1/2 cup at a time.
Heat over medium heat, stirring constantly.
Bring to boil (it will thicken) for 1 minute.
Pour 1/2 hot mixture into egg yolks; stir well.
Return mixture to saucepan and boil 1 minute longer.
Remove from heat; add margarine, lemon juice and food color.
Stir until blended. Pour into pie shell; let cool.

title: beef barley soup
directions: Brown meat in saucepan and drain.
In good-size pot, stir in meat, water, tomatoes, carrots, mushrooms, barley, garlic and oregano.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat.
Cover and simmer for 10 minutes or until barley is tender.
Season to taste.
Stir in Velveeta cheese until melted.
Makes six (1-cup) servings. Delicious soup!

title: country style coleslaw
directions: Make a day ahead if possible.
It will keep several days.

title: sweet and sour chicken
directions: Brown chicken and peppers; set aside.
In saucepan mix together brown sugar and cornstarch, add pineapple juice and vinegar.
Heat, stirring constantly.
When thick add the remaining ingredients.
Simmer 30 minutes; add chicken and peppers, simmer 30 minutes more and serve over rice.

title: potato salad
directions: Cook potatoes with some salt until tender.
Drain; cool.
Mix together with onion and eggs.
Combine remaining ingredients and stir into the potatoes.
Place in a bowl; sprinkle with paprika. Flavors blend if allowed to set awhile.

title: cranberry dessert
directions: Cook cranberries down and add the amount of sugar you like. Mix together the remaining ingredients.
Use a cake pan.
Put 1/2 the mixture in bottom of pan, pour cranberries in, then put the other half of mixture on top.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: oatmeal drop cookies
directions: Stir together first 4 ingredients.
Add brown sugar and oats and mix well.
Add remaining ingredients and stir vigorously until well moistened.
Drop by level tablespoonfuls 2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheets.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Brown and drain sausage.
Add bread, cheese, mustard and salt. Combine beaten eggs and milk; add to meat mixture.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan and refrigerate overnight.
Cover with foil and bake at 325° for 45 minutes.
Uncover and bake for 15 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook and debone chicken.
Keep in large pieces.
Lay in bottom of casserole dish.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Mix soup and milk and pour over chicken.
Combine stuffing with broth (or water) and butter.
Spread over top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour. May be made a day in advance, but do not freeze.

title: sweet-sour shelly beans
directions: Brown bacon lightly with diced onion.
Add liquid drained from beans.
Cook down to about 1/2 cup liquid.
Add remaining ingredients and beans.
Cook until soft.
Serves 4.

title: low fat nachos
directions: Heat beans in a saucepan.
Spread corn chips on a serving dish.
Spoon beans carefully on chips.
Layer yogurt or sour cream, lettuce, tomatoes and avocado over beans ending with salsa.

title: party meatballs
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Form into walnut size balls.
Place into baking dish.
Cook sauce until all is creamy, then pour over meatballs.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: calico beans
directions: Cook bacon and crumble.
Cook beef, onions, catsup, salt and brown sugar.
Drain beans and add all ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Enjoy!

title: easy doughnuts
directions: You will need a
medium size brown paper bag.

title: kristen's favorite shrimp dip
directions: Combine all of the ingredients.
Refrigerate.
(Best when prepared a day ahead.)
Makes about 2 cups.
Serve cold on crackers.

title: no crust coconut pie
directions: Mix flour and sugar.
Add eggs and remaining ingredients. Pour into 2 greased pie pans.
Bake at 350° until brown, for 35 minutes.

title: marbled orange fudge
directions: Grease 13 x 9 x 2 pan with 1 1/2 teaspoon of butter.
In a heavy saucepan, combine sugar, cream and remaining butter.
Cook and stir over low heat until sugar is dissolved.
Bring to a boil. Cook and stir for 4 minutes. Remove from heat and stir chips and marshmallow cream until smooth.
Remove 1 cup and set aside.
Add orange extract and food coloring to remaining mixture.
Pour into pan.
Drop reserved mixture by spoonfuls over top.
Cut through with knife to swirl.
Cover and refrigerate until set.
Cut into squares.
Makes 2 1/2 pounds.

title: ground beef goulash
directions: Place ground beef in a 2-quart ovenware casserole dish.
Cover. Cook in microwave oven about 7 to 8 minutes or until meat is no longer pink.
During cooking, stir twice to break up meat.
Drain off excess fat.
Sprinkle noodles over meat.
Combine water, tomato sauce, soup mix and salt.
Mix well.
Pour over noodles.
Do not stir.
Cover.
Cook in microwave oven 10 minutes, turning dish halfway around after 5 minutes.
After 10 minutes, stir.
Cook another 5 to 6 minutes.

title: wild rice casserole
directions: Cook rice by package directions; set aside.
Melt butter.
Add flour.
Add milk slowly, stirring constantly.
Add cheese; stir until smooth.
Add the salt.
Butter a 2-quart casserole. Alternate layers of rice, mushrooms and sauce; end with sauce on top.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Form into 1-inch balls and bake in a 350° oven for approximately 25 to 30 minutes, until light brown.

title: pineapple pie
directions: Beat egg yolks, sugar, flour, butter and cream.
Mix well and add crushed pineapple.
Cook until thick and pour into pie shell. Beat egg whites and cream of tartar.
Add sugar, 1 tablespoon at a time.
Beat until stiff.
Put on top of pie and brown.

title: salmon patties
directions: Pat the salmon mixture into patties.
Fry in Crisco oil on slow heat until done.

title: 3 layer surprise
directions: Mix flour, margarine and 1 cup nuts.
Press into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 15 minutes at 325°.
Cool.
Beat cream cheese sugar and 1 cup Cool Whip.
Spread over flour mixture.
Mix together both puddings, milk and vanilla.
Pour over cream cheese mixture.
Set 5 minutes.
Spread 2 cups Cool Whip onto pudding.
Sprinkle with 3 tablespoons nuts.
Chill.

title: honey cream dressing for fruit salad
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Chill thoroughly before serving. Makes 2 cups.

title: kahlua dip
directions: Mix cream cheese with small amount of half and half.
Add chopped pecans.
Add Kahlua to taste.
Mixture should be spreadable.
Use sliced apples for dipping or spreading.

title: cherry cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients by hand and drop by teaspoonfuls on greased cookie sheet.
Bake 11 to 12 minutes at 350°.
Let stand 1 minute before removing from pan.

title: deep fried turkey
directions: Use pot big enough to hold turkey.
Cut leg joints to blend. Use 1/2 pound Tony's seasoning per turkey.
Cover whole turkey with seasoning and refrigerate overnight.
Use enough oil to cover turkey.
Heat oil to 290° to 300°.
Add turkey.
Cook for 3 minutes per pound of turkey plus 15 minutes.

title: date nut bars
directions: Beat eggs until thick and foamy.
Add sugar, vanilla and butter.
Beat well.
Sift together flour, baking powder and salt into egg mixture.
Mix into a smooth batter.
Stir in dates and nuts.
Pour into a well-greased and floured 9-inch square pan. Bake at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cut into bars and dust with powdered sugar.

title: spinach salad
directions: Clean spinach torn in bite-size pieces.
Cut mushrooms.
Add cooked, crumbled bacon.
Grate boiled eggs into spinach.
Add French dressing to taste.
Serves 6. Preparation time is 20 minutes.

title: mexican salsa
directions: Bring to a boil.
Simmer for 30 minutes.
Can in pint or quart jars.

title: easy beef stroganoff
directions: Thinly slice steak across grain.
Salt and pepper to taste. Saute meat and onions in butter/oleo just until onions are tender. Put in crock-pot and add remaining ingredients, except for sour cream.
Stir to mix.
Cook on high 30 minutes, then on low 6 to 8 hours.
Stir in sour cream just before serving and just allow to heat.
Serve over cooked rice or noodles.

title: coconut cake
directions: Bake a two layer white cake. Cool and split into 4 layers. Mix the coconut, sour cream and sugar.
(Set aside 1 cup of this mixture.)
Spread main mixture onto layer of cake.
Mix the one remaining cup with the whipped cream.
Ice cake. Refrigerate for 24 hours.

title: fresh coconut pound cake
directions: Cream together butter and sugar; beat until mixture is light and fluffy.
Add one egg at a time, beating well after each addition.
Combine flour, soda and salt.
Mix well.
Add to creamed mixture.
Stir in coconut and both flavorings.
Pour batter into greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 20 minutes or until wooden pick inserted in the center comes out clean.
Cool in pan for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: best meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients except chili sauce; mix well. Shape mixture in a loaf in shallow baking dish. Score the loaf by pressing top with handle of wooden spoon. Fill the score mark with chili sauce. (Score mark deep imprint made in meat loaf.)

title: pralines
directions: Spread graham crackers out on a cookie sheet. Mix butter, brown sugar and pecans in a pan. Bring to a boil and boil for 2 minutes. Pour sugar mixture over graham crackers and bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: ice cream dessert
directions: Put ice cream into a big bowl.
Let it get real soft.
Mix in the Cool Whip.
Break up the Oreos and mix them in.
Mix in the nuts.
Pour into a big Pyrex dish or something similar.
Let it re-freeze.
Keep it covered.

title: brunswick stew
directions: Boil chicken and debone and put in a large pot after chopping or cutting into bite-size pieces.
Add corn, lima beans, tomato puree, chopped onions and Worcestershire sauce (if using) and cook slowly 5 to 6 hours.
Take the potatoes, precooked and mash thoroughly, and add to stew to thicken.
Serves 16.

title: raspberry almond french toast
directions: Slice bread into slices.
Spread half with 1 tablespoon almond paste.
Spread remaining half generously with raspberry preserves and make sandwiches.

title: ham roll-up
directions: Spread cream cheese on slices of ham.
Lay green onions along the edge of ham.
Roll.
Chill until cream cheese is firm, then slice.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: chicken and stir-fried vegetables
directions: Slice chicken breasts in strips.
In nonstick skillet put olive oil and 3 to 4 cloves garlic crushed, heat skillet then add chicken.
Stir-fry until tender about 10 minutes.
Remove chicken and put cleaned, sliced vegetables in skillet and stir for 15 minutes on medium heat.
Then add seasonings, all to your taste. Put chicken with vegetables and add your soy sauce.
Layer rice, vegetables and chicken.
Serves about 4. Makes a pretty dish.

title: frito pie
directions: Mix ground beef, chili and cheese in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with Fritos.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: buttermilk custard
directions: Mix all together and pour in unbaked pie crust.
Cook 30 to 40 minutes until set.

title: 100 year old pound cake
directions: Put eggs in blender for 3 minutes, then mix with sugar, flavorings and milk.
Melt oleo and add to everything.
Add flour. Pour into a greased tube or Bundt pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour, then 300° for 15 minutes.

title: easy pina colada cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large bowl, combine cake mix, pudding mix, 1/2 cup cream of coconut, 1/2 cup rum, oil and eggs. Beat on medium speed 2 minutes.
Stir in crushed pineapple.
Pour in well-greased and floured 10-inch Bundt or tube pan.
Bake 50 to 55 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes.

title: cheese blintz
directions: Cut crust off bread and roll out thin with rolling pin.
Mix cream cheese, egg yolks and sugar.
Spread on bread.
Roll up bread.
Coat with butter.
Sprinkle with cinnamon sugar.
Freeze. To serve:
Cut in half.
Cook frozen at 300° to 350° for 10 minutes or until warm.
Serve warm.

title: blackened fowl
directions: The secret to this succulent entree is 2 elements:
It is best cooked over an open fire with charcoal or burning material (very hot) and must be eaten immediately, so have your guests ready!
If left to cool, you may have to eat it yourself.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Allow spinach to thaw completely.
Squeeze the water from the spinach.
Saute onions in margarine.
Layer spinach, sliced eggs, mushrooms and cheese.
You can mix the 1 cup of half and half or milk with the soup before you layer each.
Mix sauteed onions and margarine with soup also.
Add crumbled crackers or Ritz on top. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: flavorful cheese ball
directions: Combine all cheeses and put aside.
Combine pecans, pimento, salt, garlic, onion and Tabasco sauce.
Mix together cheeses and pecan mixture in food processor or mixer. Shape into a ball. Combine chili powder and paprika and spread on wax paper.
Roll ball in mixture to coat.
Chill at least 4 to 5 hours.
Serves about 10 to 12.

title: easy italian chicken
directions: Place chicken in a shallow baking pan.
Season chicken with salt, pepper, garlic powder and Italian seasonings.
Cover with spaghetti sauce.
Cover and bake at 375° for at least an hour. Remove from oven; add more sauce and top with Mozzarella cheese. Bake uncovered until additional sauce is warm and cheese is melted.
Serve over noodles.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Put Creamettes in bottom layer in greased casserole.
Add all ingredients on top.
Put in refrigerator overnight.
Remove from refrigerator 1 hour before putting in oven.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 350°.
During last 1/2 hour, add buttered bread crumbs.
(I use Hi Ho cracker crumbs.)

title: peanut butter chocolate bars
directions: Beat peanut butter, margarine, brown sugar, granulated sugar and vanilla in large mixer bowl until creamy.
Beat in eggs; beat in flour.
Stir in 3/4 cup milk chocolate chips.
Spread into greased 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 20 to 25 minutes or until edges are lightly browned.
Remove from oven; immediately sprinkle with remaining milk chocolate chips. Let stand for 5 minutes; spread.
Sprinkle with colored sugar if desired.
Cool in pan.

title: kosher dills
directions: Wash cucumbers.
Mix vinegar, water and salt.
Bring to boil. Place cucumbers in jars and add a piece of dill, piece of garlic and 1/2 teaspoon mustard seed.
Then pour boiling mixture into jars to 1/4-inch of top.
Put caps on jars and process in boiling water for 20 minutes.

title: curried fruit bake
directions: Can use cinnamon or nutmeg.

title: peanut butter krispies bars
directions: Bring sugar and syrup just to a full boil over medium heat. Remove from heat.
Stir in peanut butter.
Add Rice Krispies and stir until blended.
Press into an 11 x 17-inch pan and let cool.

title: broccoli dish
directions: Saute onion in butter.
Stir in flour and add water.
Cook until it boils.
Blend in cheese.
Combine broccoli.
Add eggs and stir until mixed.
Pour into greased casserole dish.
Cover with bread crumbs.
Dot with butter.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: black mama brown's barbecue sauce
directions: Bring catsup, brown sugar, vinegar and Worcestershire sauce to a full boil.
Lower heat and simmer for 2 to 3 minutes.
Add onion and margarine.
Stir in margarine until it melts.
This is best if made at least 1 day in advance of using.
Keeps very well if refrigerated.

title: easy meat loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Crush the cereal.
Mix ground beef with remaining ingredients until well blended.
Shape into a loaf in a shallow baking pan.
Bake 1 hour or until brown.

title: chicken-broccoli casserole
directions: Lightly grease an 8 x 8-inch casserole dish.
Place chopped broccoli and chicken in bottom.
Cover with American cheese.
Mix cream of mushroom soup and milk and pour over all.
Make Stove Top according to package directions and spoon over top of casserole. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Serves 4 or 5.

title: chocolate pudding cake
directions: Combine the first 7 ingredients.
Mix in pan.
Combine the next 3 ingredients; sprinkle on cake.
Pour the water over all. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: autumn chowder
directions: Partially cook bacon in Dutch oven.
Stir in onions and finish cooking until bacon is crisp.
Stir in water, potatoes, carrots and bouillon.
Heat until boiling.
Reduce heat and simmer, covered, until potatoes are tender, 15 to 20 minutes.
Stir in milk, corn and black pepper.
Heat to simmer.
Mix cheese and flour; add to soup mixture, stirring constantly, until cheese is melted.
Makes 8 (1 cup) servings.

title: microwave applesauce
directions: In a 2 quart microproof casserole, mix apples, water and lemon juice. Cook covered, on high (max. power) 10 to 12 minutes, or until apples are tender. Stir in remaining ingredients until smooth. Serve warm or cold with pork or as a light dessert with ice cream or cool whip.

title: bread machine oat date-nut bread(makes 1 pound loaf)
directions: Combine ingredients according to manufacturer's directions.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Mix together.
Heat to a boil and cook 5 minutes.
Cool.
Add berries.
Put in baked pie shell and top with whipped cream.

title: easy potato soup
directions: Cut potatoes and onions into small pieces.
Boil in salted water until tender; drain well.
Partially mash potatoes and onions leaving some small pieces.
Add milk, salt, pepper, Tabasco and sugar.
Heat to just below boiling, stirring.
Add margarine. If mixture is too thick, add a little more milk.
May top with paprika or Parmesan cheese if you like.

title: date balls
directions: Cook dates, butter, sugar and vanilla until dates are mushy (5 minutes).
Combine Rice Krispies, coconut and nuts.
Mix with other ingredients.
Roll into balls and powdered sugar.
Let refrigerate overnight.
These are good to make for Christmas.

title: peanut butter chewies
directions: Bring the cup of Karo and sugar to a boil.
Take off heat and stir in the peanut butter, butter and cornflakes.
Serve either in cupcake holders or cut them in squares.

title: m&m cookies(yields 6 dozen)
directions: Blend shortening and sugar.
Beat in vanilla and eggs.
Sift dry ingredients together; add to the sugar and egg mixture.
Stir in 1/2 cup M&M's.
Reserve remaining M&M's for decorating.
Drop mixture from teaspoon onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Decorate tops of cookies with M&M's.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes about 6 dozen cookies.

title: brownie kahlua dessert
directions: Bake brownies as directed.
Brush on Kahlua while cake is warm.
Let cool, then spread half container of Cool Whip on top of brownies.
Spread mousse on top of that.
Top with remainder of Cool Whip.
Crumble Heath bars on top.
Refrigerate.
Serve and enjoy!

title: frosted molasses creams
directions: Pour coffee over shortening; add molasses and eggs; mix well. Add to dry ingredients in mixing bowl and beat till smooth at low speed 2 minutes.

title: oven-fried zucchini spears
directions: Preheat oven at highest setting (475° or 500°).
Liberally spray a nonstick baking tray or cookie sheet with cooking spray. Slice each zucchini lengthwise into 6 or 8 long spears.
(Cut the spears in half to make shorter spears, if desired).
Put the salad dressing in a shallow plate; combine the bread crumbs and cheese in another shallow plate.
Roll the spears first in the salad dressing, then in the crumb mixture.
Arrange the spears in a single layer on the baking tray and bake uncovered 5 minutes.
Turn the spears with a spatula or tongs and bake an additional 3 or 4 minutes.
Makes 4 servings, 55 calories each.

title: barbecue beans
directions: In a large mixing bowl, combine barbecue sauce, beans, onion, syrup, bell pepper and sugar.
Mix thoroughly and pour into large casserole dish.
Separate bacon strips and layer on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Let cool slightly and serve.

title: green pea salad
directions: Thaw and drain peas.
Combine all ingredients.

title: layered salad
directions: In a large bowl, layer the first 8 ingredients in order given. Sprinkle top with Parmesan cheese.
Cover; refrigerate for 24 hours.

title: moist 'n creamy coconut cake
directions: Prepare cake mix according to directions, baking in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cool 15 minutes, then poke holes through cake with a fork.

title: pepper relish
directions: Grind peppers and onions.
Let drain; mix all ingredients. Bring to a rapid boil.
Put in hot jars and seal.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and refrigerate.

title: crescent rolls
directions: Scald milk; add sugar, shortening and salt.
Let cool in large bowl.
Add egg.
Dissolve yeast in water and add flour to make moderately stiff dough.
Knead well until not sticky, about 5 to 10 minutes.
Cover and put in warm place.
Allow to rise until double.
Divide dough in half on floured surface.
Roll out into circles.
Cut into wedges.
Roll wide end of each wedge to point.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: In large mixer bowl, thoroughly combine 1 1/2 cups flour, yeast and spices.
In saucepan, heat milk, brown sugar, butter and salt just until warm (115° to 120°), stirring constantly to melt butter.
Add to dry mixture in mixer bowl.
Add pumpkin.
Beat at low speed with mixer for 1/2 minute, scraping sides of bowl constantly.
Beat 3 minutes at high speed.
By hand, stir in raisins and enough of the remaining flour to make a moderately stiff dough.
Turn out onto lightly floured surface and knead until smooth and elastic (5 to 8 minutes).
Shape into ball. Place in lightly greased bowl, turning once.
Cover and let rise in warm place until double (about 1 hour).
Punch down.
Cover and let rest 10 minutes.
Shape into loaf.
Place in greased 8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 2 1/2-inch loaf pan.
Cover; let rise until double (about 30 minutes).
Bake at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Remove from pan; cool.
Makes 1.

title: seafood linguine
directions: Prepare linguine according to package directions.
In heavy skillet, heat oil over high heat.
Add garlic and onions; cook, stirring for about 30 seconds.
Add tomatoes and basil; cook, stirring for about 1 minute.
Add seafood and cook, stirring until seafood is hot and, if using raw, turn pink.
Sprinkle with scallions and season with salt and pepper to taste.
Spoon over hot linguine.
Makes 4 servings.
Calories per serving, 395.
Fat per gram per serving 8.

title: blueberry nut crunch
directions: Lightly grease 9 x 13-inch baking pan and spread the undrained crushed pineapple over bottom of pan.
Add blueberries, then sugar. Sprinkle cake mix, then drizzle the melted butter over the cake mix.
Top with pecans.
Finally, for a crunch glaze, sprinkle remaining 1/4 cup sugar on top.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 35 to 40 minutes or until cake mix is done.
After cake has cooked about 25 minutes, cut down into cake with spoon to permit juice to come up through cake.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake 1 hour at 325°.

title: ramen slaw
directions: Toss together cabbage, onion, sesame seeds, and dry Ramen noodles. Mix water, oil, sugar, vinegar and ramen seasoning to make dressing.
Pour dressing over cabbage mixture; toss. Sprinkle with almonds. Serves 6.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream butter, sugar, eggs and bananas until light and fluffy. Mix in remaining ingredients.
Pour into greased and floured pans. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: ham and red eye gravy
directions: Put cloves in ham and bake at 325° until 3/4 done.
Bake about 35 minutes per pound.
Make glaze using pineapple juice, cherries, Coca-Cola and brown sugar.
Mix ingredients together and baste ham, then add fruit 1/2 hour before serving.

title: refrigerator corn relish
directions: Cook corn according to package directions; drain.
In a saucepan combine sugar and cornstarch.
Stir in vinegar and water. Stir in corn, celery, pepper, pimiento, onion, turmeric, mustard, and salt.
Cook and stir till thickened and bubbly.
Cook and stir for 2 minutes more.
Cool.
Cover and store in the refrigerator up to 4 weeks.
Serve with beef, pork, or poultry.
Makes about 2 1/2 cups.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Spread cookie dough in a jelly roll pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Let cool.
Mix softened cream cheese and marshmallow cream together.
Spread over crust and top with fruit.
Can use any fruit you want.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients, then add oil and carrots.
Mix well, adding eggs, one at a time.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes in a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix together and chill before eating.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Saute onion and celery in butter.
Add remaining ingredients in order, mixing well.
Continue cooking in skillet on top of stove over low/medium heat until spaghetti is tender.
Serve with cheese on top; garnish with paprika and parsley, if desired.

title: carrot cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Beat eggs, salad oil and vanilla together.
Add dry ingredients, then carrots, pineapple and nuts.
Bake at 350° for approximately 35 minutes.

title: coconut bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Butter and flour an 8 x 8-inch flour pan.
Cream the butter, then add confectioners sugar and cup of flour and blend.
Pat evenly into pan and bake 15 minutes.
While pastry is baking, beat eggs, then add brown sugar and vanilla; beat until thick.
Mix remaining 2 tablespoons flour, salt and baking powder together and add to egg mixture incorporating well.
Beat in nuts and coconut.
Spread evenly over the pastry and bake 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool in pan, then cut in 1 x 4-inch bars.
Makes 16 bars.

title: hershey bar cake
directions: Mix and pour into Bundt pan that has been sprayed with Pam. Bake at 325° for 50 to 60 minutes until firm.
Cool and remove from pan.

title: hot ham yummies
directions: Mix first five ingredients well.
Spread mixture on both halves of dinner rolls.
Add ham and cheese.
Bake at 450° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: fudge truffle cheesecake(one 9-inch cheesecake)
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Prepare Chocolate Crumb Crust.
Set aside.
In heavy saucepan, over low heat, melt chips, stirring. In large mixer bowl, beat cheese until fluffy.
Gradually beat in condensed milk until smooth.
Add melted chips and remaining ingredients; mix well.
Pour into prepared pan.
Bake 1 hour and 5 minutes or until center is set.
Cool; chill.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: lime molded salad
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients and let stand until marshmallows melt and cool.
Add next 3 ingredients and then fold in whipped topping.
Chill.

title: not yo's mama's banana pudding
directions: Line the bottom of a 13 x 9 x 2 inch dish with 1 bag of cookies and layer bananas on top. In a bowl, combine the milk and pudding mix and blend well using a hand held electric mixer. Using another bowl, combine the cream cheese and condensed milk together and mix until smooth. Fold the whipped topping into the cream cheese mixture. Add the cream cheese mixture to the pudding mixture and stir until well blended. Pour the mixture over the cookies and bananas and cover with the remaining cookies. Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: rice pudding
directions: Combine all ingredients and pour into lightly oiled 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Sprinkle with nutmeg or cinnamon if desired.
Place in pan of water and bake in moderate oven at 350° about 50 minutes or until a knife inserted in the center comes out clean.

title: christmas tree bread
directions: Divide dough into 2 parts (one for each tree).
Divide each part into 17 pieces.
Form into small balls.
Arrange on slightly greased baking sheet in a 5, 4, 3, 2, 1 pattern and add 2 balls rolled together for the trunk.
Let rise until double, 20 to 30 minutes.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Mix 2 tablespoons margarine, pepper, flour, salt, sugar and sour cream together and heat until warm.
Pour over green beans in a baking dish and top with cheese, bread crumbs and remaining 3 tablespoons margarine.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: jello angel food cake
directions: Mix cake as directed on box.
Add sugar-free jello powder to cake mix and swirl around in cake.
Bake as directed on cake mix. Serve topped with whip cream.

title: tuna fish casserole
directions: In bowl combine noodles, peas, tuna and soup with water.
Put in casserole.
Top with potato chips.

title: shortcut lasagna
directions: Brown meat with onion and garlic in large saucepan.
Stir in tomato juice, tomato paste, mushrooms, Worcestershire sauce, salt, pepper, parsley flakes and oregano.
Simmer 30 minutes, stirring occasionally, mixture should be saucy.

title: butterscotch rolls
directions: Place frozen rolls in well-greased Bundt or tube pan. Sprinkle with pudding and cinnamon.
Melt butter and add brown sugar.
Stir until dissolved.
Pour over rolls.
Sprinkle pecans over all.
Cover with foil and place towel on top.
Leave on counter overnight.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Remove from pan and serve.

title: layered chocolate pudding delight
directions: Melt margarine; add flour and pecans and mix together.
Press into
9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 350° for 20 minutes until light brown.
Cool.
Beat cream cheese, powdered sugar and 1/2 Cool Whip together and spread over crust.
Refrigerate one hour.
Mix puddings and milk together; pour over cream cheese filling.
Let set.
Top with the rest of the Cool Whip and sprinkle nuts on top if desired.

title: faye's easy pickles
directions: Put cucumbers in a gallon jar.
Fill jar with vinegar, salt, alum and spices.
Leave for 8 weeks.
After 8 weeks, drain well; pour off vinegar and spices.
Add 5 pounds sugar to pickles. Sugar will dissolve and make syrup.
Refrigeration is not necessary.
Do not need to seal.

title: mama mia meatballs
directions: In a large bowl, mix all the ingredients except olive oil. Form mixture into balls about size of a golf ball.

Heat about 1 inch of olive oil in a large frypan and brown the meatballs. Transfer the meatballs, discarding the oil, to a large pot; add tomato sauce and continue cooking over low heat, covered, for about 40 minutes.
Makes about 20 to 24 meatballs.

title: no-bake fruitcake
directions: Roll Keebler Cinnamon Crisps to fine crumbs.
Blend crumbs with raisins, nuts and dates.
In a large mixing bowl blend Marshmallow Creme, milk and rum flavoring on medium speed of electric mixer until smooth.
Gradually add dry ingredients to marshmallow mixture, mixing until all crumbs are moistened.
Press firmly into a waxed paper-lined 8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 2 1/2-inch loaf pan. Refrigerate at least 2 days before serving.

title: cinnamon spread for toast
directions: Mix and spread on toast.

title: sweet glazed turnips
directions: Boil
turnips
in salted water 20 to 25 minutes or until almost tender.
Drain and refresh vegetables under cold running water.
Heat
butter
in
rinsed
out pan.
Stir in sugar until dissolved.
Pour
in
the
stock;
bring to boil.
Add turnips; reduce heat and simmer gently for 8 to 10 minutes, or until the stock
is
reduced
and
the turnips glazed.
Transfer to a hot serving
dish and sprinkle with black pepper and parsley before serving.
Serves 4.

title: caramel banana dip
directions: Combine cream cheese, yogurt, caramel ice cream topping, marshmallow cream and beat until smooth.
Stir in banana liqueur. Serve with small cubes of pound cake or with graham cracker sticks.

title: yeast waffles
directions: Soak yeast in warm water.
Cream sugar and margarine.
Add 6 egg yolks.
Sift salt with flour and add to sugar mixture, alternating with milk.
Stir in yeast.
Put in warm place and let raise 30 to 60 minutes.
Beat egg whites and add to batter.
Bake on waffle iron.

title: picante surprise muffins
directions: Note:
I use self-rising flour and cornmeal, omitting baking powder and salt.

title: carolina hush puppies
directions: Mix all dry ingredients together.
Add onions and milk.
Drop by spoonfuls into hot shortening, about 3 inches deep.
Cook until golden brown.

title: very easy chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Drop by spoonfuls onto an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 7 minutes.
Cool slightly and remove from sheet.

title: norma's beet salad
directions: Dissolve jello in water; add beet juice, vinegar and salt and pepper.
Fold in mayonnaise or lightly beat it in.
Set in freezer about 10 minutes.
Take out and beat until fluffy.
Fold in beets and onion juice.
Put in refrigerator to set.
Garnish with sour cream or sub.

title: cold water pound cake
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff and set aside. Beat together margarine and egg yolks. Add other ingredients. Fold beaten egg whites into mixture.
Put into a greased tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: peanut butter bars
directions: Soak gelatin in 1/4 cup milk; set aside.
Combine peanut butter and remaining milk in a double boiler and place over hot water. Cook and stir until smooth.
Add gelatin and continue to cook and stir until it melts.

title: smothered black-eyed peas
directions: Cook black-eyed peas on low fire.
Add garlic and sliced onion to desired size.
Cook in large frypan for 20 minutes and cover.

title: 4 day pickled watermelon rind
directions: First Day:
Heat water to boil in a large pot.
Add rind and simmer until tender (10 to 15 minutes).
Drain.
Combine remaining ingredients in saucepan.
Heat to boil.
Pour over rind.
Cool, cover and let stand overnight.

title: oatmeal porridge
directions: Stir in 1 pint rolled oats; boil 10 minutes.
Stir constantly.

title: mandarin orange cake
directions: Bring to a boil and pour over hot cake.
Serve with Cool Whip or ice cream.

title: brownies in a jar
directions: Pack brown sugar in bottom of quart jar.
Pour in white sugar.
Then add cocoa.
Mix 3/4 cup flour and baking powder and put in next.
Add another 3/4 cup of flour.
Push chocolate chips into flour.
When ready to make, add eggs, nuts and margarine. Bake in greased 9 x 13-inch pan for 25 to 30 minutes in 350° oven.

title: coconut congealed salad
directions: Melt margarine.
Add the coconut and brown lightly.
Add vanilla wafer crumbs and mix thoroughly.
Line a 9 x 13-inch casserole dish with 1/2 mixture, reserving the other 1/2 for topping.
Put dish in refrigerator to cool.

title: chicken cacciatore
directions: Wash chicken and pat dry.
In a large skillet, melt shortening over medium heat.
Coat chicken with flour.
Cook chicken in hot shortening over medium heat 15 to 20 minutes or until brown. Remove chicken and set aside.
Add onion rings, green pepper and garlic to skillet. Cook and stir over medium heat until onion and pepper are tender.
Stir in remaining ingredients. Add chicken. Cover and simmer 30 to 40 minutes or until thickest pieces are tender.
Makes 4 servings.

title: lazy salad
directions: Beat all ingredients with a mixer, then chill.

title: clam dip
directions: Soften cream cheese.
Add clams, onion and Worcestershire sauce and add small amount of clam juice.
Mix well, chill and serve.

title: chocolate delight(to die for)
directions: Mix margarine, flour and nuts in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Press and bake at 375° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Mix cream cheese, confectioners sugar and 1 cup Cool Whip; spread on cooled crust. Mix pudding and milk; spread on cheese layer.
Top with layer of Cool Whip.
Sprinkle with chopped nuts.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Combine: chunk chicken, chili peppers, onion and cheese.

title: louisiana sweet potato pie
directions: Cut sweet potatoes into large cubes.
Boil until tender.
Mash potatoes in a large bowl; add all ingredients, scalded Pet milk last.
Let this cool.
Fill pie shell not completely full but over half full.
Cook at 375° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: curry chicken salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and let stand for about 1 hour (in refrigerator) before serving on lettuce.

title: icebox fruit cake
directions: Crush crackers fine.
Add milk and other ingredients and mix well.
Then pack in pan and let stand a week in refrigerator.
Do not freeze.
Makes about 8 pounds.

title: corn pudding supreme
directions: Mix well the cream cheese, eggs and sugar. Add and mix in corn muffin mix, creamed corn, canned corn, milk, butter or margarine and salt.
Place in greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° about 45 to 50 minutes until set.

title: bud's favorite salad dressing(may prepare ahead.  yields 3 cups.)
directions: Prepare by shaking ingredients in a jar.
Pour over salad just before serving.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Drain the can of chopped clams; save liquor.
Combine Parmesan, bread crumbs, chopped clams, crumbled bacon, garlic and enough clam juice to bind the mixture.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Wipe mushrooms and remove stems.
Fill with clam mixture. Brush with butter; sprinkle with paprika.
Broil 5 to 10 minutes, or until lightly browned.

title: danish dumplings
directions: In saucepan, combine water and margarine; bring to a boil. Add flour, baking powder and salt, all at once, stirring vigorously.
Cook, stirring constantly, until mixture forms a ball that doesn't separate.
Remove from heat.
Cool slightly.
Add the eggs, one at a time, beating well after each egg until smooth. Stir in parsley.
Drop dumplings from tablespoon to make 12 mounds on top of bubbling soup or stew.
Cover and cook for 20 minutes. (Don't lift cover.)

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Heat sweet potatoes, drain thoroughly and mash.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix thoroughly and place in greased casserole dish. Top with following mixture:
1/2 cup flour, 1 cup brown sugar, 1/3 cup oleo and 1 cup chopped nuts (omitted).
Bake in 350° oven for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: fruit jello mold
directions: Melt Jell-O in water.
Add all ingredients except sour cream. Pour half of the mixture into mold and chill 1 hour.
Spread on sour cream and add remaining ingredients.
Chill.

title: turkey dressing
directions: Mix well and stuff turkey loosely.
Place in oven at 350°. Bake until popcorn blows the ass off turkey, then done.

title: my favorite scrambled eggs
directions: Scramble eggs; add cold water, Parmesan cheese and green onions.
Scramble again until eggs are fluffy.
Pour into hot pan sprayed with nonstick cooking spray and cook to desired texture. Sprinkle lightly with seasoned salt.

title: chewy oatmeal cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Lightly grease a baking sheet with Crisco. In a large bowl, combine Crisco, brown sugar, egg, milk and vanilla.
Beat at medium speed until well blended.
Combine oats, flour, baking soda, salt and cinnamon.
Mix into creamed mixture at low speed until blended.
Stir in raisins and nuts.
Drop dough by rounded tablespoons, 2 inches apart onto a greased baking sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes.
Cool 2 minutes on a cooling rack. Makes 2 1/2 dozen cookies.

title: sparkling mushrooms
directions: Cook mushrooms in olive oil in a skillet over medium-high heat, stirring constantly, 1 to 2 minutes.
Add rosemary, salt and pepper.
Cook 1 minute.
Stir in champagne; reduce heat and simmer 5 minutes.
Garnish, if desired.
Yields 2 servings.

title: empanadas
directions: Place flour on a board and gradually work in butter (reserving 1 tablespoon), egg yolks, salt and baking powder using water enough to produce a firm, but not sticky, dough.
Shape dough into a ball. Cover with a cloth and allow to stand for 10 minutes.
Roll out thin; spread with some of the reserved butter.
Fold like a handkerchief and allow to stand another 10 minutes.
Repeat this procedure once more.
Roll out thin, cut into 30-inch rounds and place a little ham, chicken or jam on one half of each round. Moisten edges, fold over top half and press edges firmly together. Fry in deep oil.

title: spinach squares
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix dry ingredients together in a bowl. Mix milk, eggs, thawed spinach, worcestershire sauce and tabasco together in a different bowl.
Toss dry ingredients with the grated cheeses.
Mix all bowls together.
Melt butter in 9X13 pan. Put mixture into pan and smooth over.
Bake for 35-40 minutes. Let cool 15 minutes and cut into squares.

title: pink lemonade pie
directions: Mix pink lemonade, Eagle Brand and Cool Whip in bowl together. When completely mixed, add 2 or 3 drops of food coloring and mix until filling is pink.
Pour into pie crust and chill for 1 1/2 hours.

title: bacon-sausage roll-ups
directions: Cut the bacon into thirds.
If you don't have small sausages, cut regular-size into 2 pieces.
Wrap bacon around each sausage; secure with wooden toothpicks.
Fill a 13 x 9-inch pan with roll-ups.
Sprinkle brown sugar over links.
Cover.
Refrigerate for 8 hours or overnight.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: special rice
directions: Melt butter.
Add onions and rice.
Mix with rice and mushrooms.
Bake covered at 325° for 1 hour, uncovered 15 minutes to brown.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Cream Crisco/margarine with sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time. Add flour and baking powder.
Add salt and milk.
Add crushed berries; mix well.
By hand, add whole berries.
Grease muffin tins well.
Sprinkle sugar on top before baking.
Makes 12 large muffins or 24 average.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: "girdle buster" pie
directions: Mix crushed cookies with butter. Press into 9-inch pie plate and freeze. Spoon in ice cream and store in freezer. Heat sauce ingredients over low heat. Stir until blended; cool. Serve pie topped with sauce, whipped cream and toasted almonds. Yield: 8 small, rich servings.

title: mexican corn
directions: Chop tomatoes, onion and garlic.
Saute over medium heat until cooked.
Add corn and mix.
Add salt and black pepper to taste. Simmer for 15 minutes on low heat.

title: homemade butter
directions: Soften margarine at room temperature.
Pour in buttermilk and Wesson oil.
Whip with mixer, then put butter in container.
Can freeze.
Delicious on baked potatoes or toast.

title: potato casserole
directions: Cook potatoes; saute onion and bell pepper in butter.
Set aside.
In a double boiler put cheese and let melt.
Add onion, pepper, milk and pimento.
Let cook until mixed well.
Pour over potatoes; mix lightly.
Bake in a 350° oven for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Combine sugar and vegetable oil in large bowl; stir to mix well.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition. Combine dry ingredients; stir into the oil mixture.
Add vanilla and chopped apples; mix well.
Spoon batter into greased 10-inch tube pan and bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours or until cake tests done.

title: cinnamon ornaments
directions: Mix cinnamon and warmed applesauce until mixture forms a ball, adding more cinnamon, if necessary.
Knead dough on wooden cutting board dusted with cinnamon.
Roll out dough to 1/2-inch thickness. Cut with cookie cutters.
Using a drinking straw or coffee stirrer, cut hole in top of each ornament for hanging.
Place on wire screen or cooling racks to air dry (approximately 6 days). To speed drying, place in 200° oven for 3 hours.
Put ribbon in hole.

title: uncle charlie's pesto pasta
directions: In a large saucepan, boil pasta as directed until al dente.

title: chicken breasts supreme
directions: Rinse dried beef to remove salt.
Place in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Skin chicken breasts.
Place chicken over beef; place bacon on chicken.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 30 minutes.
Combine soup and sour cream in saucepan.
Stir over low heat until blended. Pour soup mixture over chicken and bake for 45 minutes.

title: vegetable beef soup with egg dumplings
directions: Cook and stir ground beef in Dutch oven until brown; drain. Add remaining ingredients except the Egg Dumplings.
Heat to boiling.
Reduce heat.
Prepare Egg Dumplings; drop by level teaspoonfuls into soup.
Simmer, uncovered, until dumplings are firm, about 5 minutes.

title: champagne punch
directions: Boil sugar and water 1 minute.
Cool and add juices.
Put in freezer.
Thaw
1 1/2 hours. Add ginger ale and champagne just before serving.
Mixture will be slightly slush, cool and delicious.

title: chicken francaise
directions: Coat cutlets with flour.
Dip in seasoned egg batter.
Saute (until golden on both sides) in hot oil.
(Coating will fall off if oil is not hot enough, turn with spatula.)
Drain on paper towels. Scrape pan.
Add butter, chicken broth, lemon juice, parsley and Prosciutto.
Bring to simmer.
Add meat, saute for 5 minutes or until cooked.
Put on platter and pour sauce over.

title: monkey bread
directions: Cut each biscuit into four pieces.
Place sugar and cinnamon in plastic bag.
Add biscuit pieces a few at a time and shake to coat. Place pieces in a greased tube pan until all are used.
Sprinkle each layer with pecans or whatever desired.
Bring brown sugar and margarine to a boil.
Pour over top of biscuits.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Allow to cool 15 minutes before removing from pan. Turn top side up to serve.
Pieces can just be picked apart.

title: lasagna
directions: Cook noodles and brown ground beef.
Combine beef, soup, spices, tomatoes and paste.
Simmer.
Layer ground beef, noodles and cheese in that order and bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Cream butter and shortening, gradually add sugar, beating well at medium speed.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Combine flour, baking powder and cocoa.
Stir well.
Add to creamed mixture, alternately with milk, beginning and ending with flour mixture.
Mix just until blended after each addition.
Stir in vanilla.
Pour batter into greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 325 for 1 1/2 hours or until wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool in pan 10 minutes.
Let cake cool completely, then frost with the fudge frosting recipe.

title: st.  ann's bazaar-senate bean soup
directions: *Can use smoked ham hock.

title: easy pineapple preserves(microwave)
directions: Mix all ingredients in deep 1-quart bowl.
Microwave on High (100°) until thickened, 2 to 4 minutes, stirring after half the cooking time.
Pour into prepared jars; seal and refrigerate.

title: fresh vegetable salad
directions: Mix sour cream with package of Good Seasons dressing mix and 1 cup Ranch dressing.
Set aside.
Toss all other ingredients together.
Stir in dressing mix.
Chill for about 1 hour.

title: easy cherry cobbler
directions: Melt butter in 9 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Spoon pie filling over butter.
Mix flour, sugar and milk.
Pour over pie filling and bake in a 350° oven for 30 to 40 minutes or until brown.

title: easy apple pie
directions: Mix all dry ingredients as well as lemon juice.
Pour apples into mixture and coat very well.
Using pie shell directions, pour apples into shell.
Put the top pie shell on and cook at 350° for 45 minutes or until apples are tender and the crust is brown.
Serve with ice cream and caramel topping if you like.

title: pastry crust(single)
directions: Stir together flour and salt.
Cut in shortening until it looks like peas.
Sprinkle 1 tablespoon water and toss with fork; repeat until all moist and form ball.
Can use right away or chill for better results.

title: hamburger bake
directions: Press ground beef in bottom of 8 x 8-inch baking dish.
Spread undiluted soup over top.
Arrange frozen Tater Tots on top in rows.
Bake for 1 1/2 hours at 325°.

title: corn fritters
directions: Preheat lightly greased skillet.
Combine egg yolks, corn, flour and salt; mix well.
Fold egg whites into your mixture.
Drop heaping tablespoonfuls of batter into skillet.
Cook over low heat 2 to 3 minutes on each side until lightly browned.

title: coconut caramel pie
directions: Cream the cheese well with mixer. Add Eagle Brand milk. Beat until smooth, then fold in Cool Whip. Toast coconut in thick skillet with butter over low heat. Add pecans. Set aside until cool. Pour 1/4 of mixture in each pie crust. Put 1/4 of toasted coconut on top of mixture. Add caramel topping. Repeat layers. This makes 2 pies.

title: southwest chicken breasts(serves 4)
directions: Combine oil, lime juice, balsamic vinegar, Dijon mustard, garlic, cilantro, salt and pepper in a bowl.
Marinate chicken at least 1 hour.
Grill or broil chicken breasts until done, basting with marinade.

title: mexican wedding cookies
directions: Cream the butter.
Add sugar, creaming until smooth.
Add flour, salt and vanilla.
Blend.
Pinch off small pieces of dough. Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 400° for 12 minutes.
Roll cookies in additional powdered sugar immediately upon removing from oven.

title: lemon cream pie
directions: Squeeze juice from lemons.
Mix lemon juice, cornstarch, sugar, egg yolks, butter and salt, then add boiling water.
Cook in double boiler until thick like honey.
When mixture is cool, pour into baked pie shell and cover with meringue.

title: chocolate frosting
directions: Mix all ingredients until smooth.
Frost cooled cake or cupcakes.

title: clam chowder
directions: In a large soup kettle, brown salt pork and remove from kettle.
In rendered fat, saute onions and celery until tender. Add potatoes, clam juice, water, thyme, and salt and pepper to taste.
Simmer uncovered until potatoes are tender.
Stir in milk, cream, and clams.
Heat through, but do no boil.

title: butterscotch crunchies
directions: Melt and stir over a low flame first 3 ingredients.
When all is melted, remove from stove and add corn flakes.
Stir well. Drop by teaspoonfuls on waxed paper on cookie sheet.
Chill in refrigerator until firm.

title: banana milkshake
directions: Remove peel from banana.
Wrap banana in heavy-duty plastic wrap and freeze until firm.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and eggs together until light and fluffy. Stir in buttermilk. Add oats, mixing well. Bake at 400° for 8 minutes.

title: cherry delight
directions: Beat egg whites real stiff and add baking powder.
Beat and add sugar.
Beat until blended.
Add soda crackers.
(I always add a few more crackers for crust).
Add vinegar, vanilla and nuts (optional); blend with egg whites.
Spread into a well-greased pan and bake in a 350° oven for about 20 minutes or until brown.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Melt together margarine and peanut butter.
Do not cook too hot.
Add vanilla.
Add confectioners sugar.
Stir together until creamy.
Pour into 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Smooth and let chill.

title: key lime pie
directions: Combine milk and egg yolks at low speed.
Slowly add juice, mixing until well blended.
Pour into 9-inch graham cracker pie shell and refrigerate overnight or if preferred, pie can be baked at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Top with whipped cream or meringue and enjoy.

title: bean salad
directions: Cook vinegar and seasonings together for 3 minutes and pour over cooked beans.

title: pork chops with applesauce and sauerkraut
directions: Brown chops in butter.
Season with salt and pepper.
Set aside.
Saut onion in butter left in pan for browning chops.
Add more butter if necessary.
Mix sauted onion thoroughly with rest of ingredients.
Layer 1/2 of the mixture on bottom of a 9 x 13 x 2 pan; next, add the chops and top with remaining mixture.
Cover with foil and bake in a 350° oven for about 2 hours or until desired doneness.
Serve with noodles, rice or boiled potatoes.

title: preserved chicken
directions: Take 1 large field, half a dozen children, 2 or 3 small dogs, a pinch of creek and some small rocks.
Mix the children and dogs well together; put them on the field, stirring constantly.
Pour the creek over the rocks.
Sprinkle the field with flowers.
Spread all under the deep blue sky and bake in the sun.
When brown, set away to cool in the bathtub.

title: toffee bars
directions: Boil brown sugar and butter for 3 minutes.
Line cookie sheet with graham crackers.
Pour mixture over graham crackers and bake for 6 minutes at 350°.
Then sprinkle on 1/2 a bag of chocolate chips.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Beat together everything, but the Cool Whip and milk chocolate chips.
Fold in the Cool Whip.
Pour into graham cracker crust. Top with milk chocolate chips and freeze.
Remove from freezer 1/2 hour before serving.

title: tuna snack - quick
directions: Into the food processor goes the tuna, mayonnaise, a few slices of avocado and scallions.
Add juice from lemon, some dill weed and a cut dill pickle.
Season to taste with salt and pepper. Put on slices of French bread, crackers, etc.

title: poppy seed chicken casserole
directions: Crush 1/2 crackers and layer in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Put 1/2 chicken on crackers.
Mix together sour cream, soup and poppy seed.
Put 1/2 of this mixture on top of the chicken.
Now add the remaining 1/2 of the chicken.
Add the remaining 1/2 of the soup mixture.
Crush the other half of the crackers and place on top of the casserole.
Pour melted margarine over top and bake at 350° until golden.

title: ice cream
directions: Mix together and put in ice cream maker; turn until frozen slush.

title: oreo balls
directions: Crush oreo cookies until very fine. Stir in softened cream cheese. Keep on stirring
the mixture, it takes a long time for this. Roll out into small balls. Refrigerate until firm. Dip in melted almond bark. Store in the refrigerator.

title: veal shanks-milan style(ossobuco ala milanse)
directions: Place veal shanks on aluminum foil and sprinkle with flour. Heat oil in large, heavy casserole.
Add veal to casserole.
Brown on all sides over medium heat.
Remove meat from casserole.
Add onion, carrot and celery.
Saute until slightly brown.
Return veal to casserole.
Stir in wine.
When wine is reduced by half, add tomatoes.

title: buckeyes(candy)
directions: Mix first 3
ingredients together.
Knead by hand.
Roll into 1-inch balls.
Refrigerate 1 hour.
Insert toothpick in each ball.
Melt chocolate morsels and paraffin.
Dip balls in this mix.
Dry/harden on wax paper.

title: carrot cake
directions: Blend oil and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beat after each.
Sift all dry ingredients and add 1/3 at a time, beating after each.
Fold in carrots and nuts.
Bake at 350° until done, approximately 40 minutes.

title: light cheddar cheese straws
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
Stack the won-ton wrappers.
Cut the stack lengthwise into fourths, making 48 strips.
Line a cookie sheet with parchment paper or foil.
Then spray the paper or foil with non-stick spray.
Add the won-ton strips in a single layer so the edges are not touching.
Brush the won-ton strips with the Worcestershire sauce.
Sprinkle each strip with 1/2 teaspoon of the cheese.
Then sprinkle with the poppy seeds.
Bake for 8 to 10 minutes or until golden brown and crisp.
Yield:
48 straws (4 per serving).

title: chicken sloppy joes
directions: Melt butter in pan.
Cook onions until brown.
Add remaining ingredients and heat.
Let cool and place in refrigerator for at least 4 hours to acquire flavor.
Serve over rolls.

title: pecan pie
directions: Blend all ingredients thoroughly and pour in an unbaked pie crust.
Bake 10 minutes at 450°, then lower heat to 350° and bake for 25 minutes more.

title: chocolate pudding cheese pie
directions: Beat cream cheese until very soft.
Gradually add 1/2 cup milk and blend until smooth.
Add remaining milk and pudding.
Beat at lowest speed of mixer for 1 minute.
Pour at once into pie shells. Chill at least 3 hours.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: bananas foster
directions: Slice bananas.
Sprinkle lemon juice over bananas; set aside. Melt butter.
Add sugar; stir well.
Add the bananas, cinnamon and wine; heat until warm.
Serve over ice cream.

title: chocolate chip pound cake
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients.
Stir in chips and grated chocolate. Bake in Bundt pan for 55 minutes at 350°.
Cool in pan for 5 minutes.

title: nocciolette (hazelnut delights)
directions: Cream butter, confectioners sugar and honey.
Add sherry, whiskey or etc., and blend well.
Add nuts and flour.
Knead dough until smooth.
Pinch off pieces of dough the size of a walnut and roll into balls.

title: blackened chicken
directions: Sprinkle some magic seasoning on both sides of chicken. Preheat oven for 10 minutes at 450°.
Put a cast-iron skillet in oven.
Spray cooking spray on pan before putting into oven.
Take pan out of oven and place on burner on medium-high heat.
Pan must be hot before putting chicken in.
Cook chicken on medium-high until done, approximately 13 to 15 minutes.
If you cut your chicken up into strips, cooking time will be about half of time. This seasoning produces a lot of smoke.

title: coconut cake
directions: Spray a 10 x 14 x 2 inch pan with cooking spray.
Mix all ingredients well.
Bake at 325° for 35-40 minutes.

title: violet leigh's chopped barbecue
directions: Wash pork shoulder by rubbing it vigorously with vinegar.
Pat it dry with a paper towel.
Saturate meat with all spices.
Pour a capful of lemon juice and rub it into the meat also.
Spices can marinate 2 to 3 hours or overnight.
If using a crock-pot (highly recommended) put the setting on high for 1/2 hour with bottom layered with barbecue sauce.
Put shoulder in pot; cover.

title: oysters benedict
directions: Split muffins and toast lightly.
Spread thinly with butter. Poach oysters in own juice (a little white wine is optional) until edges curl.
Top each muffin half with slice of bacon.
Place 1 or 2, depending on size, oysters on top.
Keep warm.
Mix rest of ingredients over low heat for "mock Hollandaise."
Spoon over each oyster topped muffin.
Dust with paprika.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Sift flour, sugar, salt and cocoa together.
Add 1/2 of the milk.
Place on stove and cook until thick.
Separate eggs.
Beat egg yolks and add other half of milk.
Add this slowly to mixture, stirring well.
Cook until thick.
Add butter and vanilla.
Pour into baked pie crust.
Cover with meringue topping, using the egg whites.
Brown.

title: coconut kisses
directions: Beat together egg whites and brown sugar.
Fold in corn flakes, nuts, coconut and vanilla.
Drop from spoon onto a greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Place tray on a damp cloth and remove cookies.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken breasts until tender.
Cut into bite-sized pieces. Mix together sour cream and soup in a baking dish.
Add chicken pieces and stir well.
Cover with crushed Ritz crackers.
Bake in a 400° oven for 30 minutes.

title: crock-pot beef tips and rice
directions: Salt and pepper beef to taste.
In crock-pot, brown stew beef in oil.
Add Kitchen Bouquet and Worcestershire sauce.
Layer top of meat with slices of onions and mushrooms.
Pour water over contents to moisten and cover.
Cook on low temperature 8 to 10 hours.

title: italian cream cake with icing
directions: Cream oleo and Crisco.
Add sugar, egg yolks, flour and soda to creamed mixture.
Add milk.
Stir in vanilla, coconut and chopped pecans.
Fold in egg whites.
Use 3 (9-inch) round pans (greased).
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: old-fashioned oatmeal cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375 degrees.

title: el gando(mexican meat casserole)
directions: Cook meat until it separates, add onion, salt, chili
mix and tomatoes.
Simmer until almost dry.
Cook rice as directed on package.
Put a layer of meat and tomato mixture in a 4-quart baking dish.
Spread one can of beans over meat mixture. Cover with cooked rice, then add the rest of the meat and tomato mixture.
Spread with the other can of beans.
Heat the can of Cheddar cheese soup and milk in a double boiler, then pour over the entire dish.
Heat until bubbly at 350°.
Before serving, sprinkle with crushed Fritos.
If you like things spicy hot, add chopped jalapenos on top of the meat mixture. Feeds eight hungry people.

title: favorite punch
directions: Mix all together (except ginger ale).
Put in containers and freeze.
Take out of freezer about 2 hours before serving time. Put punch in punch bowl and pour in ginger ale.

title: savory chicken casserole
directions: In large mixing bowl, combine all ingredients, except potato chips. Pour into 9 x 13 pan and cover with foil. Bake 1 hour and 15 minutes at 350°. Uncover dish and top with crushed potato chips. Bake, uncovered, for 15 more minutes. This makes a thick casserole.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Combine all ingredients together.
Pour into greased pans. Bake in 350° oven for about 1 hour.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: arkansas hot dills
directions: In quart jars, put fresh dill or 2 teaspoons dill seed.
Pack 1/2 full of cucumbers.
Add 1 clove garlic and 3 hot peppers. Complete packing jars with cucumbers.

title: noel salad(this salad is a pretty holiday salad.)
directions: Crush cranberry sauce and put in pan.
Add hot water and heat thoroughly.
In a bowl, mix gelatin with cold water.
Set 5 minutes, then add to cranberry sauce.
Cool.
When mixture starts to jell, fold in ground rind and pulp of orange, celery, nuts, dates and salt.
Pour into a mold and chill until firm.
Unmold on lettuce leaves.
In a bowl, mix food coloring and cream cheese, then spread on salad to trim it.
Serves 6.

title: cauliflower casserole
directions: Wash head
of
cauliflower. Mix rest of ingredients and pour over
cauliflower,	which
has
been
put in large baking dish. Bake until bubbly and done at 350°.

title: easy elegant chicken for non-cooks
directions: Place chicken breasts in a 9 x 12 x 2-inch baking dish.
Mix remaining ingredients together and pour over chicken.
Bake 1 1/2 hours in a 350° oven.
Good served with wild/long grain rice. Serves 6.
tags: cream of mushroom soup or cream of celery soup

title: no bake drop cookies
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa, milk and oleo in large pan.
Bring to a boil and boil 1 1/2 to 2 minutes.
Set aside peanut butter and vanilla. Mix thoroughly.
Add oatmeal. Stir well.
Drop on wax paper. Makes 50 large cookies.

title: fresh papaya nut pie
directions: Prebake pie shell.
Blend orange juice with cornstarch; add sugar and lemon juice.
Heat slowly in a saucepan, stirring constantly until clear and thickened.
Place sliced papayas in pie shell and pour juice mixture over.
Cool to room temperature and then chill.
Serve ringed with whipped cream and sprinkled with chopped nuts.

title: spiced tea
directions: Mix well and use about two teaspoons per cup of boiling water. Try it, you'll like it!

title: stuffed eggplant
directions: Cut eggplant in halves; wash with vinegar and water.
Put to boil in hot salted water until tender.
Remove from water and drain.
Put into skillet onions, tomatoes, garlic and shortening. Cover for a few minutes on a low flame.
Add bread crumbs and cook dry.
Remove the pulp of the eggplant and add to the mixture.
Add ground meat and seasoning.
Return to fire and cook some more. Allow to cool before adding egg.
Fill shells with mixture.
Dust with bread crumbs; fry or bake.

title: quesadilla grandia
directions: Lightly spread butter on one tortilla. Add grated cheese to cover tortilla. Sprinkle on tomatoes, green onions and jalapeno peppers evenly. Cover with another tortilla and press edges together. Place on plate, cover with a paper towel and microwave for 1 minute on high. Remove paper towel, cut across, like a pizza. Separate pieces. Serve warm with a scoop of salsa, guacamole and sour cream on a bed of lettuce.

title: zucchini soup
directions: Cook together.
Cool for 20 minutes.
Put in food processor.

title: dirt pudding
directions: In a large bowl, mix pudding and milk.

In another large bowl, whip the cream cheese, Cool Whip and sugar until well blended. Combine the two mixtures and layer with cookie crumbs in a clay or plastic flowerpot, ending with crumbs to give the appearance of dirt.
Wrap the stem of a cut or artificial flower in foil and place in the center of the pot.
For added fun, partially bury a few gummy worms in the dirt.
Refrigerate sans flower, until serving time.

title: puppy chow
directions: Melt oleo and chocolate chips in microwave.
Add peanut butter; mix well.
Stir in cereal; mix until well coated.
Pour mixture into a big paper bag.
Pour in the powdered sugar and shake well.
Makes a large batch!

title: southwest salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill overnight to let flavors blend. Low-fat and yummy!

title: mama berry syrup sponge cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together and mix well.
Pour into baking pan and bake until done.
(Mixture will be thin.) There is no temperature setting.
This was made by my Grandmother, Georgia Berry, on a wood stove.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Stir dry ingredients together and store in a 3 pound coffee can.
Put 1/3 cup mix in cup.
Add hot water and stir.

title: spiced apple tea
directions: Combine all ingredients and heat to boiling.
Serve warm.

title: light yellow birthday cake
directions: Cream together shortening and sugar until fluffy.
Beat eggs in thoroughly.
Sift together Softasilk, baking powder and salt. Stir in alternately with milk and vanilla.
Pour into greased and floured 9-inch cake pans or oblong 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes (35 to 40 minutes in oblong pan).

title: ice cream sandwich dessert
directions: Cut one ice cream sandwich in half.
Place one whole and 1 half sandwich along short side of an ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan. Arrange 8 sandwiches in opposite direction in the pan.
Spread half of the whipped topping over sandwiches.
Swirl caramel syrup generously across the top.
Drizzle the chocolate syrup across the top.
Sprinkle with chopped nuts.
Repeat layers.
Cover and freeze.
Can be kept in freezer up to 2 months.
Remove from freezer 20 minutes before serving.
Cut in squares.

title: toasted butter pecan cake
directions: Toast pecans in 1/4 cup butter at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes. Sift flour with baking powder and salt.
Cream butter and sugar. Add eggs, one at a time, blending well.
Add dry ingredients, alternating with milk.
Stir in vanilla and 1 1/3 cups pecans. Bake in 3 (8 or 9-inch) pans at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: hot buffalo wings
directions: Cook chicken in small amount of oil until done.
Mix butter and hot sauce.
Dip chicken in hot sauce and reheat until hot. Serve.

title: fried cucumber rings
directions: Peel, slice lengthwise and scoop out pulp.
Cut into 2 1/2 x 1/2-inch strips.
Combine milk and egg, mix well.
Set aside. Combine biscuit mix, bread crumbs and salt.
Dip cucumber in milk mixture then bread crumb mixture.
Fry in hot oil until golden brown.
Drain on paper towels.
Yields 4 servings.

title: pat smith's swiss steak
directions: Mix together dry mustard, salt, pepper and flour.
Pound as much of this mixture into meat as you can.

title: zucchini cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Fold in nuts and raisins last. Bake 1 hour and 10 minutes at 350° (test with a toothpick) in a 10-inch tube pan or bake in 3 small loaf pans (about 40 minutes).

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix with buttermilk.
Have mixture stiff and drop into hot grease from teaspoon.

title: hungarian chicken soup(csirke leves)
directions: Place chicken in water; bring to boil; skim.
Add all vegetables and seasonings.
Cook slowly for an hour or until chicken is done.
Strain before serving.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix together, put in a greased casserole and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Cream butter or margarine with cream cheese and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Gradually add flour, vanilla or lemon extract and salt; mix well.
Grease and flour a tube or Bundt pan, pour cake mix out into pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.
Let set in pan for 10 minutes before removing.

title: taffy apple dip
directions: Soften cream cheese; add brown sugar and vanilla.
Top with chopped peanuts.
Serve with sliced apples.

title: baked chicken and rice
directions: Put Minute rice on the bottom of covered casserole bowl.
Lay chicken breast on top of rice.
Sprinkle onion soup on top of that.
Spoon cream soup on top of that.
Pour 2 cans of water over all of it.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: sour cream rolls
directions: Mix all ingredients and put in ungreased muffin pan. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until brown.

title: spareribs with onion sauce
directions: Cut ribs into 3 to 4 rib pieces.
Place into foil-lined jelly roll pan well apart and roast at 400° for 20 minutes.
Drain off fat.
Arrange ribs in a 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: chester stew(serves 6)
directions: Combine in order given in a large casserole (with lid) or a Dutch oven.
Stir.
Cover and bake at 250° about 5 hours.
Serve with rice, French bread and salad.

title: broccoli cheese soup
directions: In a gallon pot, bring chicken broth, broccoli, carrot, celery, onion and parsley to a boil.
Simmer until thoroughly heated, about 1/2 hour.
While mixture is simmering, mix cornstarch with water, then add along with half and half and Velveeta.
Cook until thickened.

title: meat balls
directions: Mix all items in large mixing bowl.
Shape into balls; brown. Just before sauce is done, drop in meat balls.
Practice makes perfect.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Mix sauce and 1 cup of hot water with mixer until smooth.
In another bowl, dissolve jello and 1 cup of hot water.
Add pecans and cranberry mixture.

title: mint ice cream
directions: Whip cream and add milk slow.
Mix well.
Put mints between wax paper and crush.
Stir crumbs into cream and pour into tray in freezer.
When nearly frozen, remove and stir once more.

title: low-fat applesauce oatmeal muffins
directions: Sprinkle evenly over batter in baking cups.
Bake 20 to 22 minutes or until deep golden brown.
Serve warm.
Makes 1 dozen.

title: copper pennies
directions: Cook carrots in boiling water to cover in a medium saucepan until tender. Drain and cool. Add sliced onions and peppers. Combine soup and remaining ingredients.
Pour over carrot mixture. Cover and refrigerate at least 12 hours.
Exchanges:
1 bread/starch.
Serving Size:
3/4 cup.

title: cardinal punch(makes 44 servings)
directions: Combine juices with ice and chill.
Pour into punch bowl over block of ice; add ginger ale.
Garnish glasses with mint sprig. (May add orange sherbet scoops.)

title: chicken pot pie
directions: In a 3-quart oblong baking dish, combine soup, milk, thyme and pepper.
Stir in veggies and chicken.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes or until mixture begins to bubble.
Cut each biscuit into quarters.
Remove dish from oven; stir.
Arrange biscuit pieces over hot chicken mixture.
Bake 15 minutes or until biscuits are golden brown.
Makes 5 servings.

title: blueberry cake
directions: Sift flour once; measure and add baking powder and salt and sift again.
Cream butter and sugar gradually and cream together. Add egg and beat.
Add flour alternately with milk in small amounts, beating after each addition until smooth.
This makes a stiff batter.
Fold in berries.
Turn into a greased 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan, spreading evenly.
Bake in moderate oven at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: grilled flank steak
directions: Sprinkle steak on both sides with garlic powder.
Prick with fork.
Place in shallow pan.
Combine remaining ingredients and pour over steak.
Cover and marinate 8 hours in refrigerator, turning occasionally.
Remove steak and grill over coals for 7 to 9 minutes on each side.
Slice across grain, 12 to 14 slices.

title: chicken nacho platter
directions: Heat process cheese spread and sour cream in saucepan over low heat; stir until process cheese is melted.
Add chicken and chilies; heat thoroughly.
Layer half of chips and chicken mixture on platter; repeat layers.
Top with lettuce and tomato.
Garnish with additional sour cream if desired.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: chocolate star cookies
directions: Cream peanut butter and shortening. Add egg, sugar, brown sugar, vanilla, milk, salt, soda and flour. Roll in balls and roll in sugar. Bake 8 minutes at 350°. Add stars. Bake 2 to 5 more minutes.

title: monkey bread
directions: Toss the buttermilk biscuits with a mixture of 3/4 cup sugar and 1 teaspoon cinnamon.
Bring the remaining margarine, sugar and cinnamon to a boil.
Arrange biscuits in a Bundt or angel food cake pan.
Pour hot mixture over all.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix pudding in Cool Whip.
Add pineapple, marshmallows and nuts.
Mix thoroughly.

title: chicken a la king
directions: Mix first three ingredients in casserole dish.
Sprinkle corn flakes over top and spray with butter.
Bake for 1 hour at 375 degrees.

title: dressing for endive
directions: Beat eggs; add vinegar and water.
Blend sugar and cornstarch. Add to eggs, vinegar and water.
Add browned bacon.
Cook, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Pour over cleaned endive. Can also be used over lettuce.

title: vegetable bake
directions: Combine thawed and drained vegetables, soup, 1/2 cup cheese, sour cream and 1/2 can of onions.
Pour into 1-quart casserole.

title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: Cook 7-Up, sugar and cornstarch until thick.
Fold over berries.

title: pineapple upside-down cake
directions: Grease sides of 13 x 9-inch (glass) pan; melt margarine in bottom.
Crumble brown sugar over top margarine.
Arrange pineapple slices on top.
Prepare cake mix as directed and pour over top.
Bake at 325° for 50 minutes.
Cool for 5 minutes and turn upside down.

title: split pea soup
directions: Rinse and drain peas.
In a large pot add boiling water, seasoning, celery, onion, ham, carrots and peas.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat to simmer.
Cover and cook slowly for 2 hours, stirring occasionally to keep from sticking to pot.
After you turn off, let set for about half hour and add milk.
Start with 1 cup and add more if consistency is not smooth.

title: homemade noodles
directions: Mix together flour,
shortening,
salt and water.
Roll out on floured surface
real
thin.
Roll
up like jelly roll. Cut into noodles.
Leave out to dry while you cook your broth. Drop noodles into broth and cook with meat.

title: mexican salsa(serves 4)
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Let sit at least 1 hour for juices to combine.
Serve as a sauce for tacos, tostadas, steak or use as a dip with corn chips.

title: cheese wafers
directions: Cream butter and cheese; add salt, pepper, garlic powder, sugar and flour to creamed mixture.
Roll dough into small balls and flatten.
Bake at 275° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Cool thoroughly. Store in airtight container.
Keeps for weeks in freezer or refrigerator.

title: easy blueberry pie
directions: In saucepan, mix 1 cup blueberries, sugar, water and cornstarch.
Boil 1 minute; add lemon juice and cool.
Stir in remaining 3 cups blueberries.
Pour into baked pie crust.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Cream butter and cream cheese; add sugar.
Beat well.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well.
Add flour and vanilla.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan.
Bake in a 300° oven for 1 1/2 hours.

title: crazy apple cake
directions: Break egg over apples.
Stir with a fork.
Add remaining ingredients.
Sprinkle with cinnamon and sugar.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: italian cream cake
directions: Cream the margarine, shortening and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add egg yolks; mix well.
