Sift flour and soda together and add to creamed mixture alternately with buttermilk, beginning and ending with dry ingredients.
Add vanilla, coconut and nuts. Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Pour into three 9-inch greased and floured cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until done.

title: roast wild duck
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Clean ducks; wash and pat dry.
Stir together salt, 1/2 teaspoon pepper and 1/4 teaspoon rosemary leaves.
Sprinkle in cavity and on outside of each duck.

title: biscuit and baking mix
directions: In a very large bowl, sift together the flour, baking powder, sugar and salt.
Use a pastry blender or two knives or your fingertips to cut in the shortening, one cup at a time, until the mix looks like coarse meal.
Put in a covered container or plastic bag; store at room temperature for about 3 months.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Mix and refrigerate several hours: cranberries, pineapple and marshmallows. Then add: sugar, nuts and Cool Whip.	Keep refrigerated.

title: open-faced supreme sandwich
directions: Make open-faced sandwich with bread, cheese, meat, tomato, bacon and lettuce.
Combine remaining ingredients and add pickle juice to thin if needed.
Use as topping for sandwich.
Makes enough dressing for 6 servings.

title: apple bundt cake
directions: Cream oil and sugar; add eggs, one at a time, beating well. Sift dry ingredients and spices together.
Add sugar mixture.
Add remaining ingredients and fold together.
Bake in well-greased pan at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Cool 20 minutes before removing from pan.

title: cabbage
directions: Core cabbage; wash and cut coarsely.
Fry bacon in large skillet until crisp.
Add cabbage and stir-fry until it wilts. Add onion and keep cooking, stirring well.
Add a little water and cover.
Lower heat and continue cooking until cabbage is done.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In small bowl, combine flour, baking soda and salt; set aside.
In large bowl, beat butter, sugar, brown sugar and vanilla extract until creamy.
Beat in eggs. Gradually beat in flour mixture.
Stir in Nestle semi-sweet morsels.

title: herbed bread coating
directions: Mix dry ingredients well and cut in shortening until crumbly. Store in airtight container.

title: oh henry bars
directions: Combine sugar and syrup.
Bring to a boil.
Remove from heat. Add peanut butter.
Pour over cereal.
Mix; press into buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.
Melt chocolate chips and spread over the top.
Let cool.
Cut into bars.

title: chocolate fudge frosting
directions: Mix sugar and cocoa.
Add whipping cream and vanilla.
Cut butter in chunks and mix well.
Cook over medium heat until mixture reaches soft ball stage on candy thermometer.

title: maple pecan cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar well.
Beat in yolks,
one
at a time. Stir in flavoring.
Sift together flour
and soda.
Add to creamed mixture alternately with sour
cream.
Add
pecans and fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Pour
into greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at
or until done.
Let cool in pan 10 minutes before removing.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Mix jello in
boiling water.
Add other ingredients and congeal.

title: indian cornbread
directions: Sift together cornmeal, soda and salt. Mix together buttermilk, eggs, creamed corn, oil, cheese, peppers and onion. Add to dry ingredients. Bake for 1 hour in a 375° preheated oven. Can be baked in a cast-iron skillet or Teflon pan.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Put chicken into pot with water and cook until tender.
Remove bones and cut or shred into small chunks or pieces.
Put drained chicken noodle soup into casserole dish.
Drain liquid from vegetables and put as second layer into casserole dish.
For 3rd layer, put the chicken.
Warm cream of chicken soup with chicken broth until of right consistency and pour over casserole. Sprinkle crumbled potato chips on top or use a pie crust.
Bake in oven at 400° for 45 minutes or until bubbly.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Sift flour and salt together.
Add oat meal.
Add sweetener to buttermilk and stir with margarine into flour mixture.
Knead dough lightly on floured board for a few minutes.
Roll thin and cut into squares or with cookie cutter.
Bake at 400° (10 to 12 minutes) until golden brown.
Yield:
3 dozen cookies.
Carbohydrate 3.5 g, protein .6 g, fat .7 g, calories 29.
One square = 1/4 bread exchange, 1/4 fat exchange.

title: dream bars
directions: Cream the brown sugar with the butter or margarine and flour. Press on bottom of greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.
Cool.

title: sunshine smoothie
directions: Put all ingredients in blender and whirl until smooth and frosty.

title: breakfast raisin-banana roll-ups
directions: In a bowl, beat cream cheese, honey and peel.

For each sandwich, spread 1 side of tortilla with 2 tablespoons cheese mixture. Cover with half of 1 sliced banana and sprinkle with 2 tablespoons raisins. Roll tortilla up tightly. Cut in half to serve. Repeat to make 3 more sandwiches.
Sandwiches can be made up to 12 hours in advance, wrapped tightly in plastic wrap and refrigerated.
Makes 4 servings.

title: apple crisp
directions: Place apples in greased pan.
Blend remaining ingredients until mixture is crumbly.
Spread over apples.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: 14 day sweet pickles
directions: Put in stone jar.
Cover
cucumbers with hot brine of 1 pint salt to 1
gallon of water.
Let stand seven days.	Drain and cover with 1
tablespoon
alum
to 1 gallon of water.
Let stand 24 hours.
Drain.
Cut
every
pickle
and	cover
with boiling water; let	stand
hours,
drain.
Make
syrup	of vinegar, sugar and
stick
cinnamon.
Boil this syrup and pour over pickles.
Heat this
syrup	for
3 mornings, adding 1 cup sugar each day and can the third day.

title: tutti-frutti ice cream
directions: Combine ingredients and pour into an ice cream freezer.
Fill to the line with milk.
Stir well and freeze.

title: scalloped tomatoes and artichoke hearts
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease shallow casserole.
Drain tomatoes and artichokes; rinse artichokes in water and quarter. Saute onion and shallots in butter until tender.
Add tomatoes, artichokes and basil; heat 2 to 3 minutes, stirring gently. Season.
Turn into prepared casserole and bake at 325° for 10 to 15 minutes or until heated through.

title: taco pie
directions: Place biscuits in a 10 inch pie pan, pressing together gently to form a pie crust. Set aside.

title: prize christmas salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in hot water; add cold water.
Chill until partly thickened, fold in orange, pineapple, cranberry sauce and nuts.
Chill until firm.

title: prune cake
directions: Sift together flour, soda, salt, cinnamon, cloves, nutmeg and sugar.
Stir in oil and add eggs, one at a time and beat.
Add buttermilk, vanilla, raisins, nuts and prunes.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: cauliflower and broccoli salad
directions: Mix mayonnaise, cheese and sugar.
Add to other ingredients, except bacon.
Chill overnight.
Add bacon right before serving.

title: lemon blossom pie
directions: Stir together egg yolks, lemon peel and lemon juice; set aside. In heavy saucepan, mix sugar, cornstarch and salt.
Gradually stir in boiling water.
Bring to boil over medium heat, stirring briskly.
Continue to stir and cook until clear, smooth and thick, about 3 minutes.
Carefully stir in egg and lemon mixture.
Boil, stirring about 2 minutes.
Remove from heat, stir in butter and cool 5 minutes.

title: yummy potatoes
directions: Mix together first 7 ingredients.
Cook potatoes in salted water with bay leaf.
Cool.
When cold, peel and grate coarsely. Mix potatoes with mixture of first 7 ingredients and place in a greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Cover and bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Sprinkle top with mixture of grated cheese and potato chips.
Bake a few minutes more to melt cheese.

title: maple syrup for pancakes
directions: Bring to a boil.
Pour into a jar.
Ready to eat over pancakes or waffles.

title: peaches 'n cream
directions: Cream together and spread on top of peaches.

title: spiced tea
directions: Mix together.
Keep in covered jar.
Use 2 teaspoons per cup of hot water.
Good hot or cold.

title: quick yeast rolls
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Let rise 15 minutes.
Put on floured surface and knead until not sticky.
Break off and form rolls. Place in greased pan.
Let rise 30 minutes.
Bake at 425° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: black pepper spice cake
directions: Sift together first 3 ingredients and set aside.
Mix shortening, 3/4 teaspoon soda and spices until fluffy.
Gradually blend in white and brown sugar and vanilla.
Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Add flour mixture and sour milk alternately.
Turn batter into 3 well-greased, lightly floured 9-inch round cake pans. Bake in 375° oven for 25 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes.

title: red beans and rice
directions: Brown sausage and ground beef.
Drain.
Add other ingredients.
Mash up one can of red beans for base and add all beans and chili powder to meat mixture.
Cook very slow for 2 to 3 hours.
May need to add water.
Serve over rice.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cut squash into 1/4-inch slices.
Bring 2 cups water to a boil; add squash, salt and sugar.
Cover and cook 20 minutes. Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt 4 tablespoons of the butter in a small skillet.
Add onion and cook until transparent.
After squash is tender, drain and add all of onion mixture.
Mix together in casserole dish.
One at a time, add the Cheddar, sour cream Romano, salt and pepper (I usually use white pepper) to taste, mixing thoroughly after each addition. Pour squash mixture into a large casserole dish.
In skillet, saut bread crumbs in the remaining butter until well mixed.
Top casserole with the bread crumbs and bake 20 to 30 minutes or until bubbly.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream Crisco and add sugar. Mix until pretty creamy. Add eggs 1 at a time and mix after each. Sift flour before measuring. Mix dry ingredients together and then add a small amount at a time, alternating with milk until all has been added, scraping sides of bowl while mixing. Add vanilla and put into a greased and floured tube pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Remove from pan and cool on rack. Makes a big cake.

title: pineapple-cheese casserole
directions: Drain pineapple; save juice.
Mix sugar, flour and 3 tablespoons pineapple juice.
Mix with the pineapple chunks and cheese.
Mix butter with cracker crumbs and spread over top.
Bake for 20 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: apricot salad
directions: Bring pineapple and sugar to a boil in a saucepan.
Remove from heat and add jello according to package directions.
Add cream cheese and mix until smooth.
Add celery and nuts.
Cool. Whip cold evaporated milk until stiff.
Fold into first mixture. Mix well. Pour into jello mold.
Refrigerate until set.

title: dirt pudding
directions: Crush cookies; sprinkle half of the cookies in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch glass dish.
Beat together the milk and instant pudding until mixture thickens; set aside.
Beat together margarine, sugar and cream cheese until creamy.
Add whipped topping and pudding to cheese mixture.
Stir well.
Pour mixture over crushed cookies. Sprinkle rest of cookies on top.
Cover and refrigerate at least 1 hour.
(Can decorate with gummy worms or silk flowers.)

title: texas sheath cake
directions: Prepare batter by mixing flour with sugar in large bowl. Bring margarine, cocoa and water to rapid boil.
Immediately pour over flour mixture and mix well.
Add sour milk, eggs, cinnamon, soda and vanilla.
Pour into greased 17 x 11-inch sheet pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Prepare frosting.

title: baked pizza sandwich
directions: Cook and drain meat.
Stir half of pizza sauce and the oregano into meat; heat to boiling.
Mix Bisquick, egg and milk; measure 3/4 of batter into pan.
Pour remaining sauce over batter, spreading evenly.
Put 4 slices cheese, the meat mixture, mushroom soup and remaining cheese and batter on top.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake, uncovered, until brown in a 400° oven, 20 to 25 minutes.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix dry ingredients and milk.
Boil until nearly thick.
Add beaten egg yolks.
Boil until thick.
Be sure and keep stirring it.
Let cool.
Pour into a baked pie shell and cover with meringue. Brown.

title: deer and gravy
directions: Roll meat in flour, salt, pepper and tenderizer.
Put shortening in skillet.
Brown meat on both sides.
Remove from skillet.
Pour meat and 1 can mushroom soup into crock-pot.
Cook on high setting about 8 to 9 hours.

title: hot spiced percolator punch
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in a 30-cup automatic percolator.
Place salt and spices in the percolator basket.
Assemble unit; plug it and perk.
Serve piping hot.

title: hershey bar pie
directions: Mix into crumbly mass in pie pan; line pan to form crust. Save a few crumbs for the top of the pie.
Bake at 375° for 8 minutes; refrigerate until cool.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in greased casserole dish, then top with the grated cheese and the buttered bread crumbs.
Bake in a 350° oven until bubbly.

title: cajun roux
directions: Heat oil in heavy pot.
When oil is hot, gradually add flour, stirring constantly until well mixed.
Lower flame and continue stirring until chocolate brown.
Do not overcook.
This traditional Cajun recipe is used to thicken other recipes.

title: mexican meat loaf
directions: Brown hamburger and mix with the soups.
In a casserole dish (3 x 9 x 15-inch), put 1 layer of tortillas, cover with meat sauce.
Another layer of
tortillas and cover with meat sauce. Cover with grated cheese.
Cover casserole with foil.
Bake at 325° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: tortellini soup
directions: Bring first 5 ingredients to a boil in a large saucepan. Stir in Tortellini and return to a boil. Reduce heat and simmer for 3 minutes for refrigerated tortellini; for frozen tortellini simmer about 8-10 minutes. Stir in parsley and sprinkle with Parmesan cheese. Serve immediately. Yields 7 cups.

title: chili-corn casserole
directions: Mix together creamed corn, whole kernel corn, corn meal, garlic powder, vegetable oil and egg.
Stir in cheese and green chilies.
Bake in a casserole dish until a toothpick, poked into middle comes out clean.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in 1 cup hot water.
Dissolve cranberry sauce in Jell-O mixture.
Add crushed pineapple and nuts.
Chill until set.
(Great with turkey or ham.)

title: black bean soup
directions: Bring water to a boil and add beans.
Reduce heat to simmer and skim off any foam.
Cover and cook for 1 hour.
Meanwhile, heat oil in skillet over moderate heat.
Add onions and saute about 4 minutes.
Stir in the garlic, carrots, celery and cumin; saute about 3 minutes.
Add about 1/2 cup water from the beans.
Reduce heat and cook for 20 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add water as needed.
Remove from heat.
Add bay leaves, parsley, ham bone, ham, salt and pepper to beans.
Stir in vegetables.
Cover and cook for 2 hours, adding a little hot water if too thick.
Discard ham bone. Add sherry and cook until hot.

title: old-fashioned gingerbread
directions: Cream fresh butter and sugar together.
Blend all ingredients together with sugar mixture.
Grease and heat a 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan real hot.
Pour batter into pan and bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: buttermilk pound cake
directions: Cream sugar and Crisco.
Add eggs, beating after each egg. Add buttermilk and vanilla alternately with flour mixture (flour, salt and soda).
Grease tube or Bundt pan; sprinkle with flour. Put dough in.
Preheat oven to 325°.
Cook for 1 1/4 hours.
Do not open door while cooking.

title: cheese cake
directions: Prepare cheese cake mix as directed on box.
Add cool whip to mix and beat together until blended.
Pour into shells and sprinkle graham cracker crumbs on top and refrigerate.

title: sugar layer cake
directions: Cream sugar and shortening;
add
egg and vanilla. Sift dry ingredients together and
add
to first mixture with milk. Divide between two greased
and floured layer cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: st. patrick's day cupcakes
directions: Grease muffin cups or line with paper bake cups.
In a large mixing bowl stir together flour, pudding mix, chocolate pieces, sugar, baking powder, and salt.
In a small bowl combine beaten eggs, milk, oil, and vanilla or almond extract.
Stir into flour mixture just till combined.
Fill muffin cups 2/3 full.

title: pumpkin roll
directions: Beat eggs at high speed for five minutes.
Beat in sugar, pumpkin and lemon juice.
Stir dry ingredients (except pecans) together in a separate bowl.
Stir dry mixture into the pumpkin mixture.
Pour into a greased and floured cookie pan.
Spread evenly and top with pecans.
Bake in a 350° oven for 15 minutes. While still hot, turn out on a towel and sprinkle with powdered sugar.
Starting at narrow end, roll towel and cake together; cool.

title: southern mexican cornbread
directions: Season ground chuck with salt and pepper; cook in skillet over medium heat until browned.
Drain well; set aside.
Combine cornnmeal, onion, cheese and peppers in a large bowl; mix well. Stir eggs into milk; add to dry ingredients and stir just to moisten.

Add corn and mix well. Spoon half the batter into a two-quart casserole dish that has been coated with vegetable spray. Place the ground chuck over the batter, then top with remaining batter. Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Yields 8 servings, each serving contains 488 calories; 51% fat.

title: applesauce bread
directions: Combine oats, sugar and cinnamon.
Add applesauce, egg, milk and raisins; stir until mixed.
Pour batter into a greased and floured loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Remove from pan and cool on a wire rack before slicing.

title: oyster cracker treats
directions: Mix all ingredients except crackers, then pour over the crackers in a large bowl.
Stir and let sit overnight.
Will keep well in closed container.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat shortening, both sugars, egg, water and vanilla until creamy.
Add combined remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Drop rounded teaspoonful onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Makes about 5 dozen.

title: chicken and sausage jambalaya
directions: The first 4 items: In large pot, cover chicken with water. Add celery, onion and garlic; boil until tender, about 1 hour. Save broth. Remove meat from bones. In 5 cups of stock, cook rice until all liquid is absorbed, about 25 minutes.

title: spice potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 400°. Spray baking pan with nonstick cooking spray. Wash potatoes and cut in wedges (leave peeling on). Combine oil, juice, garlic and seasoning. Pour over potatoes in baking pan. Add salt and pepper to taste. Bake 40 minutes or until done.

title: kentucky's best chicken
directions: Mix ingredients.
Store in refrigerator for future use.

title: apricot fluff
directions: Prepare Jell-O; whip until foamy.
Add apricots and whip until well beaten.
Add Dream Whip and marshmallows.
Refrigerate until firm.
Serves 12 to 15.

title: custard filling
directions: Reserve whites of eggs.
Mix thoroughly the cornstarch, sugar and salt.
Add slowly to hot milk, stirring constantly until mixture thickens.
Cook in double boiler about 10 minutes.
Blend a little of this mixture with egg yolks.
Return to double boiler; stir and cook until eggs are set (2 minutes).
Add vanilla; pour into cracker crust.
Make a meringue of 3 stiffly beaten egg whites and 3 tablespoons granulated sugar.
Spread on top of custard filling.
Sprinkle with remaining graham cracker crumbs.
Bake in slow oven (300° to 325°) until lightly browned.

title: savory crescent chicken squares
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In medium bowl blend cream cheese and 2 tablespoons margarine (reserve 1 tablespoon) until smooth.
Add the next 6 ingredients; mix well.
Separate crescent dough into 4 rectangles; firmly press perforations to seal.
Spoon 1/2 cup meat mixture onto center of chicken mixture, twist slightly and seal edges.
Brush tops with reserved tablespoon of margarine; dip in crouton crumbs.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet 20 to 25 minutes until golden brown.
Refrigerate any leftovers.

title: danish cucumber soup
directions: Peel cucumbers.

Cut 4 into thin slices and set aside. Cut remaining cucumbers in half. Remove seeds and chop. Set aside. In a large saucepan, saute onion in butter 3 minutes. Blend in flour. Gradually add chicken broth, stirring well. Add all but 8 cucumber slices to broth mixture. Add bay leaves, salt and pepper. Cover and simmer 10 minutes. Remove bay leaves. Strain 2/3 broth in a large saucepan along with half and half, lemon juice and chopped cucumber.
In electric blender, puree cooked cucumbers and remaining broth. Add to other ingredients in large saucepan. Heat slowly.
Ladle into soup bowls.
Top each serving with a cucumber slice and a sprinkle of chopped dill.
Makes 6 to 9 servings.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: In a large bowl, mix corn, relish and eggs.
Add corn meal gradually; add milk to desired consistency.
Add 1 tablespoon oil. Brown 1 pound sausage.
Add to corn meal mixture.
Pour half of mixture into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread with grated cheese, then pour on other half of mixture.
Bake at 375° until golden brown or until done in center.

title: wacky cake
directions: Stir the first five ingredients until evenly mixed.
Make three holes in the mixture.
Into the first hole, pour margarine or oil, the second, vinegar and the third, vanilla.
Pour cold water over the entire mixture.
Mix until smooth.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: french coconut pie
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into pie shell (not deep dish). Bake at 350° for approximately 45 minutes to 1 hour.
This pie tastes real good.

title: spicy pork
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients with 1/2 cup water in 3-quart glass dish.
Mix well.
Arrange pork chops on top.
Cover. Microwave on Roast for 13 minutes.
Turn pork chops.
Microwave for 15 minutes longer.

title: pound cake
directions: Let cream cheese, butter and eggs set at room temperature. Mix together the cream cheese and butter until creamy.
Gradually add the flour, eggs, vanilla and sugar.
Bake for 40 minutes at 350°.

title: rice chantilly
directions: Combine rice, sour cream and 1/2 cheese.
Spoon into buttered 1-quart casserole dish.
Top with remaining cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: magic fudge
directions: Melt chocolate in double boiler.
Add sweetened milk, vanilla, salt and nuts; stir until smooth.
Pour into square pan and chill.

title: snickerdoodle cookies
directions: Mix shortening, sugar and eggs.
Blend in flour, cream of tartar and salt.
Stir well.
Shape dough in 1-inch balls and roll into sugar and cinnamon mix.
Place 2-inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: blueberry salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Drain pineapple and liquid to gelatin mixture.
Stir in pie filling and pineapple.
Pour into a 2-quart flat pan and refrigerate until firm.
Blend softened cream cheese, sugar, sour cream and vanilla.
Spread over congealed salad.
Sprinkle nuts over top.

title: fruit delight
directions: Mix all together and refrigerate about 2 hours before serving.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients except cheese.
Put half of the mixture in pan and sprinkle the cheese over it.
Add the rest of the mixture. Bake at 400° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: fruit salad
directions: You may use cherry pie filling if you prefer.
You may increase your fruit also and still use 1 can of pie filling. Drain oranges and pineapple.

title: mini pizzas
directions: Spread tomato paste on crackers.
Sprinkle with oregano.
Top with pepperoni and cheese.
Place 12 crackers at a time in a circle on a paper plate.
Microwave 45 seconds.
Turn dish 1/2 turn after 20 seconds.
Serve hot.

title: apple crumb pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and let sit for 1 hour.
Pour into pie crust.

title: collards with bacon
directions: Fry bacon in large skillet over medium heat. Transfer bacon to paper towel to drain. Discard all but 2 tablespoons drippings from the skillet. Add green onions and garlic to drippings. Saute over medium heat until tender, about 2 minutes. Add collards or kale and broth. Cover and cook until the greens wilt and is almost tender, stirring occasionally, about 12 minutes. Uncover and cook until the greens are tender and most of the broth is cooked away, stirring occasionally, another 12 minutes longer. Transfer greens to a serving dish and sprinkle with bacon.

title: tall timber cranberry salad
directions: Chop cranberries coarsely.
Stir in sugar and refrigerate for 12 hours.
Drain cranberries.
In a large bowl, combine cranberries, grapes, pineapple and nuts.
In separate bowl, whip Cool Whip and cream cheese until blended.
Fold cream cheese mixture into cranberry mixture.
Chill.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix together graham cracker crumbs, sugar and butter. Press into a 9 x 13-inch cake pan. Cream butter and sugar together. Add eggs and vanilla. Mix until light and fluffy. Pour on crust. Slice bananas and dip into pineapple juice from crushed pineapple. Layer on filling; spread well drained pineapple over bananas. Follow directions on the package to make 2 packages of Dream Whip. Spread on pineapple. Sprinkle with a layer of coconut, a layer of chopped pecans and a layer of cherries.

title: meringue for pie
directions: Beat egg whites and salt until soft peaks form.
Add Marshmallow Creme.
Spread over pie filling, sealing to edge of crust.
Bake at 350° for about 10 to 12 minutes until browned.

title: chicken "gumbo"
directions: Lightly saute first 3 ingredients in fat.
Add next 6 ingredients and bring to a boil.
Lower heat and simmer 45 minutes.
Add chopped meat, heat and serve with parsley.
Yield: 4 to 6 servings.

title: bacon roll-ups
directions: Cut each bacon slice into 3 short pieces.
Mix stuffing mix as directed on package.
Beat egg and add to stuffing.
Put about 1 teaspoon stuffing on each piece of bacon.
Roll up and secure with toothpick.
Place on rack in pan.
Bake about 8 minutes on each side, turning once, in 425° oven.

title: lemon picnic cake
directions: Mix all 5 ingredients and beat until blended.
Bake cake in a 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.
Poke holes in cake with a long tined fork.

title: oatmeal lace cookies
directions: Mix together ingredients.
Drop by 1/2 teaspoon onto aluminum foil (shiny side up).
Bake at 350° for 5 to 7 minutes, or until golden brown.
Cool on foil.
Peel off and enjoy!

title: southern chicken casserole
directions: Cook broccoli; drain and arrange in a greased casserole. Place chicken or turkey over broccoli.
Combine soup, water, mayonnaise, lemon juice and curry powder in a small bowl.
Mix well.
Pour sauce over chicken.
Top with buttered bread crumbs. Bake at 350° for 20 or 25 minutes or until bubbly.

title: grandpa perkins' fudge
directions: Cook the mixture like fudge in a heavy pan, stirring all the time with a wooden spoon.
Test in a cold cup of water to a very firm soft ball, like fudge.
Then remove from heat and start beating by hand or mixer until creamy.
Stir in nuts. You may pour in a damp cloth like a date loaf or pour in a long buttered Pyrex dish.
Let cool and cut.

title: sandy frazier's chicken casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients (except crumbs and butter).
Place mixture in 9 x 13-inch dish.
Brown bread crumbs in butter.
Sprinkle over casserole.
Refrigerate overnight.
Remove from refrigerator 1 hour before baking at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: cream of broccoli
directions: In a large pan, bring broccoli, broth, onion and pepper to a boil. Reduce heat to low; cover and let simmer 8 to 10 minutes or until broccoli is tender. Process until smooth, then return to pan. Add 3 1/4 cups of milk to pan and bring to a boil. Stir cornstarch into remaining milk until smooth. Stir into boiling soup; simmer 1 minute, until thick. Reduce heat to medium; stir in cheese until melted. Makes 7 cups.

title: easy pancakes
directions: Mix all ingredients and cook.

title: banana pudding
directions: In a large bowl mix pudding and milk well.
Next add Eagle Brand milk and Cool Whip.
Garnish with bananas and vanilla wafers.
Chill.

title: cherry cheese pie
directions: Beat cream cheese until light and fluffy.
Add Eagle Brand milk.
Mix well.
Add lemon juice and vanilla.
Pour into crust. Chill for 3 hours.

title: walking chalupa
directions: On a large, round serving dish, layer ingredients in the order given.
Surround with tortilla chips and serve.

title: rich noodle casserole
directions: Cook noodles as per package directions.
Drain.
Combine rest of ingredients, except shredded cheese.
Add noodles.
Pour into a greased 2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle with shredded cheese.
Bake in preheated oven for 40 to 45 minutes or until heated through and cheese is melted and light brown.
Excellent for meatless meal or as side dish for potluck dinners.

title: split pea soup
directions: Place peas in a strainer and hold under running water to clean them.
Transfer to a bowl and cover with cold water.
Let soak overnight.
Drain and place in a 3-quart pot together with all other ingredients, except croutons.
Bring to boil and let simmer on low heat for 3 to 4 hours.
Stir frequently and make sure peas don't stick to the bottom of pot.
Add more liquid, if soup gets too thick.
When finished, it should be consistency of heavy cream.
Serve hot.
Add crisp croutons just before serving. Serves 4 to 6.

title: german shortcake recipe
directions: Cream sugar and shortening well.
Mix in other ingredients alternately until well mixed.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Melt margarine; let cool.
Combine all ingredients; mix completely.
Pour into 2 pie shells.
Bake for 10 minutes at 435°, then turn oven down to 325° and bake for 30 to 45 minutes, or until knife comes out clean.

title: sweet cream biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Mix ingredients all together until dough forms.
Turn onto cloth covered board or wax paper, well dusted with baking mix.
Gently roll to coat.
Shape into a ball. Knead 10 times.
Roll 1/2-inch thick.
Cut with a 2-inch cutter, dipped in mix.
Bake on greased cookie sheet until golden (10 to 12 minutes).
Makes about 1 dozen.

title: coffee cake
directions: My wonderful wife went through her collection of recipes and made a great dessert for us.
Of course, anything that has two icings couldn't be bad.
It's good stuff and ideal for a party.

title: chinese noodle salad
directions: Stir-fry snow peas and carrots in a little sesame oil; remove while still crisp.
Saute almonds in 1/2 cup sesame oil on low heat.
Leave remainder of vegetables raw.
Also strips of stir-fried chicken may be added.

title: lemongrass spareribs(xuong nuong xa)
directions: Combine and mix all ingredients into a bowl.
Arrange the ribs in single layer in a large shallow dish.
Pour the marinade over them and coat them well.
Marinate at room temperature for at least 3 hours or covered in the refrigerator overnight.
Preheat the grill and cook until ribs are done.
Serve hot.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: cheese cake
directions: Cream the cream cheese, 1/2 cup sugar and egg yolks.
Add whipping cream, flour and vanilla extract.
Mix together real well.
Add 1/2 cup sugar to egg whites and beat until stiff.
Add to mixture and mix well.
Pour into spring-form pan which has been greased. Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Leave in oven overnight.

title: punch
directions: Crush 5 bananas real good.
Add the juices and bananas to the water and sugar syrup and freeze.
Take out 3 hours before serving and add 3 (32 ounce) 7-Up.

title: quick lasagna
directions: In a large skillet, brown beef, and cook onion, garlic and oregano.
Add soup, water and vinegar.
Simmer 30 minutes.
Stir occasionally.

title: molded tuna salad
directions: Drain tuna; flake.
Combine with olives, celery and eggs. Soften gelatin in water and dissolve over hot water.
Stir in salad dressing.
Add sour cream, onion, salt, lemon juice and parsley.
Combine with tuna mixture.
Spoon into 1-quart mold and chill until firm.

title: creamy baked hash brown potatoes
directions: Combine 1/2 cup butter,
the
onion,
soup,
milk, sour cream, cheese and flour.
Bring
to
a boil and then pour over thawed potatoes in a buttered
3 quart flat baking dish.
Melt the rest of the butter
and put in crushed corn flakes.
Shred a little more cheese and
put
over
potatoes;
then
put
the buttered, crushed corn flakes on
top of contents.
Bake for 1 hour at 325°. Can be
made
ahead
of
time
and frozen until ready to bake.

title: chocolate crinkles
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and vanilla.
Beat in eggs; add cocoa. Sift dry ingredients together and blend alternately with milk. Chill 3 hours.
Roll into balls, then roll in powdered sugar. Bake 10 to 15 minutes at 350° on greased cookie sheet.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: mississippi mud cake
directions: Mix eggs and sugar.
Stir in margarine.
Sift flour and cocoa together and stir in.
Stir in vanilla.
Bake 30 minutes in greased 9 x 13-inch pan at 350°.
Spread on immediately the marshmallow cream.
Melt margarine.
Add remaining ingredients and spread on cake.

title: roasted pecans
directions: Stir pecans, salt, butter and Tabasco sauce.
Bake 10 minutes in 350° oven.
Sprinkle with Worcestershire sauce.
Bake 15 minutes.
Remove from oven and sprinkle with garlic salt.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large bowl. Cover and chill overnight. Drain before serving. Will keep for 1 week in refrigerator.

title: golden punch
directions: Combine juices, sugar and water; let stand at least 30 minutes.
Add ginger ale when ready to serve.
Place ice ring in punch to keep cold and serve.
Yields 32 to 40 servings.

title: pineapple filling
directions: Mix flour, sugar and eggs; add pineapple.
Put in greased 2-quart casserole.
Add bread cubes to melted butter and then into pineapple mixture.
Bake 40 minutes at 350°.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Bake at 350° for 45 minutes in a greased casserole dish.

title: bean soup
directions: Soak beans overnight in 10 cups of water.
Drain and put into large pot.
Add ham hock and 10 cups of water; cook for 1 hour and 30 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients; cook for an additional 1 1/2 hours or until tender.
Serves 10.

title: butterscotch haystacks
directions: Line trays with wax paper.
Microwave morsels in large, microwave safe bowl at Medium-High for 1 minute; stir.
Microwave at additional 10 to 20 second intervals, stirring until smooth. Stir in peanut butter until well blended.
Add chow mein noodles and marshmallows; toss until all ingredients are coated.
Drop by rounded tablespoons onto prepared trays.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.
Yield 36 servings.

title: zucchini sausage casserole
directions: Wash zucchini and trim ends.
Cook whole zucchini in boiling salted water for 10 to 12 minutes or until almost tender.
Drain thoroughly and chop zucchini coarsely.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken until tender; cool.
Remove all skin, fat and bones.
Place chicken in bake dish.
Mix soup and milk together; pour over chicken.
Mix stuffing and broth together; pour over chicken.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°, or until bubbly and nicely browned.

title: strawberry sherbet
directions: Process in food processor for several seconds only.

title: spinach balls
directions: Mix.
Make into small balls and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: o.k. bars
directions: Heat corn syrup and sugar to boiling in heavy saucepan, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and stir in peanut butter. Pour over cereal and raisins (optional) and stir until well coated.
Press into ungreased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan and cool.
Melt chips together and spread over top.
Cool, then cut into bars.

title: rich lemon bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In medium bowl, combine 1 1/2 cups flour and 1/2 cup powdered sugar.
Cut in margarine until crumbly. Press into bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan, lightly greased.
Bake 15 minutes.
Combine 3 tablespoons flour and remaining ingredients. Mix well.
Pour over baked crust and bake 20 to 25 minutes or until brown.
Cool.
Cut into bars and sprinkle with additional powdered sugar.
Store in refrigerator.

title: squash casserole
directions: Slice squash; boil 5 minutes in small amount of salted water. In a large skillet; saute onion, celery and pepper in oleo until clear.
Add squash; saute 2 minutes longer.
Add egg, sugar and chestnuts.

title: okra creole
directions: In large pot, add tomato paste, stewed tomatoes, okra and 4 cups water.
Season to perfection; let come to boil.
Stir in large skillet the shrimp, sausage, bell pepper and onion. Stir-fry in skillet until done, about 15 or 20 minutes.
Add shrimp, sausage, bell pepper and onion to large pot of sauce; let cook about 45 minutes.
Serve over rice or with crackers.

title: oatmeal bars
directions: Cook raisins in water until tender; drain, reserving 1 1/4 cups liquid.
Cream sugar and shortening; beat in eggs well.
Add salt, soda, cinnamon, cloves and flour.
Stir in raisin liquid. Add oats and raisins.
Spread on large cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Cut into squares.

title: irish raisin bread(for bread machine)
directions: Put dry yeast in inner pot.
Add remaining ingredients, except water, milk and raisins.
Carefully pour in the warm water and milk.
Press the select button for "medium".
Press start button. The electronic beeper sounds 10 times five minutes before secondary kneading is finished.
At this signal, add the raisins. After taking out the baked bread from the bread oven, let cool, then slice as desired.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown the meat and seasoning; drain. Melt the cheese over low heat. Last mix the meat, lettuce and Fritos. Pour the cheese over it.

title: baked zucchini and cheese
directions: In bowl, combine zucchini, onion and bacon and gently stir in the Cheddar cheese, flour, eggs, oil, salt and pepper.
Stir the mixture until it is combined well.
Turn mixture into a well buttered baking pan (10 x 6 x 2-inches).
Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes or until golden brown.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: meatballs in mustard sauce
directions: Mix hamburger with the flour, salt and pepper.
Add the Accent and mix thoroughly.
Melt butter or margarine in a deep skillet. Form ground meat into meatballs about the size of golf balls. Place in skillet and cook until they're golden brown.
Add meat stock and simmer 10 minutes.
Remove approximately 3/4 cup of broth and stir mustard, brown sugar and cocoa in it.
Return to meat mixture and simmer again.
Baste meatballs with sauce.
Serve with plain boiled potatoes or with boiled rice.
This also goes well with buttered noodles.

title: 7-up salad
directions: Prepare gelatin according to directions, substituting the 7-Up for water.
Let cool to room temperature.
Stir in the remaining ingredients.
Pour into mold.
Refrigerate.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: carrots marinade
directions: Peel carrots and cut into sticks.
Combine remaining ingredients and pour over carrots.
Marinate 24 hours.

title: spinach torte
directions: Mix all together.
Pour into lightly greased 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Cool 5 to 10 minutes before serving.

title: million dollar white fudge
directions: Mix sugar, evaporated milk, Karo and salt.
Cook over medium heat to soft ball stage, stirring constantly.
(Do not overcook.) Take from heat, add chips and marshmallows and stir until all are melted.
Stir in vanilla and nuts.
Mix well.
Pour in buttered jelly roll pan, 15 x 10 x 1-inch to cool.
Cut when cool.

title: rice artichoke salad
directions: Cook Rice-A-Roni according to directions, cool.
Add onions, peppers and olives.
Drain artichokes but reserve marinade. Combine marinade, curry, mayonnaise and artichokes, quartered. Combine everything, mix lightly.
Cover and refrigerate.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Bring first 4 ingredients to a boil.
Boil 2 minutes.
Remove from heat and add last 3 ingredients.
Drop by spoonfuls onto waxed paper.
Let cool and harden.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: apricot nectar cake
directions: Mix ingredients and beat for 4 minutes.
Bake in a tube pan for 55 minutes at 350°.

title: timmy's favorite maple syrup
directions: Bring all to a boil, stirring until sugar dissolves (a good rolling boil).
Turn off burner, but leave pot on burner until bubbling stops and store in a glass container when cool.

title: quick cookies
directions: Mix together. Roll in balls and flatten on cookie sheet.
Bake 8 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: marinated vidalia onions
directions: Slice onions and separate into rings.
Combine water, sugar and vinegar.
Stir until sugar dissolves.
Pour over onion rings. Cover and chill at least 3 hours; drain.
Stir in mayonnaise and celery seed.

title: sloppy joes
directions: In a saucepan over low heat, combine sauce ingredients.
Mix well and simmer while preparing meat.
Next, heat a heavy nonstick skillet, at least 10 inches in diameter, over medium-high heat. Add ground beef and saute, stirring occasionally, 4 to 5 minutes or until meat is no longer pink.
Pour contents of pan into a strainer or colander lined with paper towels.
Allow fat to drain out.
Add onion to pan and saute, stirring frequently, about 5 minutes or until translucent.
Return meat to pan and add sauce.
Heat 3 minutes, stirring occasionally, add additional hot pepper sauce, if desired.
Spoon half-cup of the mixture over each bun.
Serve immediately.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together into baking dish.
Bake at 350°.

title: lemon squares
directions: First add flour, salt, oleo and powdered sugar.
Mix at low speed.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan and bake 20 minutes at 350°. Remove from oven and spread with the following:
Mix eggs, sugar and lemon juice.
Bake 25 minutes longer.
Sprinkle lightly with powdered sugar, cool 10 minutes and cut into squares.

title: hot mulled cider
directions: Combine all ingredients and heat 10 to 15 minutes.
Strain to remove spices.
Store in refrigerator until ready to heat and serve.

title: sweet and sour slaw
directions: Put cabbage, pepper, onion and sugar in bowl; let set for 1 hour.
Boil vinegar, oil and celery seed and pour over cabbage mixture.
Mix well.
Add pimentos for color (optional).
Will keep up to 2 weeks.
Refrigerate in airtight container.

title: baked beans
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook bacon and onion (in microwave if desired); drain.
In large casserole dish pour beans, onions, bacon, brown sugar, catsup and mustard.
Mix; add garlic powder and mix again.
Cover; bake in oven 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Take cover off for last 20 minutes.
Serves about 8.

title: sausage enchiladas
directions: Brown sausage and drain.
Mix cream cheese and Ro-Tel tomatoes together.
Add sausage.
Spread thin layer of refried beans on tortillas and then layer with sausage mixture and cheese.
Roll up tortilla and put in 9 x 13-inch dish. Cover with remaining cheese. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: mushroom balls
directions: Combine all ingredients; mix well.
Shape into small meatballs.
In casserole, dilute the mushroom soup and 1 can water.
Add meatballs; cook in oven for about 1 hour at about 325° to 350°.
It's delicious over mashed potatoes or cooked rice.

title: chocolate chess pie
directions: Melt butter and chocolate in saucepan and add milk and sugar. Blend together with chocolate mixture.
Add vanilla.
Add eggs one at a time to mixture, stir until mixed thoroughly (add pecans if desired).
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 325° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: tex-mex dip
directions: Peel, pit and mash avocado.
Whip in juice, salt and pepper. Combine sour cream, mayonnaise and seasoning.
Spread beans in serving dish (9 x 13-inches) and top with avocado mixture, then sour cream mixture.
Chop up onions, tomatoes, olives and lettuce real small.
Layer the onions, tomatoes, olives, lettuce and cheese.

title: banana cow
directions: Combine all ingredients and blend in blender.

title: ritz pie
directions: Grease a 9-inch pie pan with oleo.
Beat egg whites until stiff; add sugar and baking powder.
Fold in crumbled Ritz crackers, nuts and vanilla.
Put in pie pan.
Smooth top.
Bake in a 350° oven for 25 minutes.
Cool.
Spread Cool Whip on top. Grate a small chocolate bar on top.
Serves 6 to 8.
Easy, yet really good!

title: cherry jubilee pie
directions: Drain juice from cherries, save.
Add enough water to juice to make 1 cup of liquid.
Bring to boil.
Dissolve Jell-O in large bowl with boiled liquid.
Add pint of ice cream to dissolved Jell-O mixture.
Stir until melted.
Let set until thick but not solid. Stir in cherries and pour into pie shell.
Refrigerate.
Top with whipped cream.

title: christmas jello mold
directions: Mix lime jello and hot water; let set some and pour into mold.
Mix pineapple, lemon jello and Cool Whip; let it start to set.
When lime jello layer is set, pour lemon jello layer on top and let it set.
Mix mayonnaise and raspberry jello and pour over all when beginning to set.
Chill until serving.

title: three-nut clusters
directions: Arrange 36 one-inch paper candy cups on sheet cake pan. Combine nuts and coconut in small bowl.
Melt chocolate over low heat, stirring until smooth.
Add mixed nuts to chocolate, stirring to coat.
Drop mixture by heaping teaspoonfuls into candy cups.
Refrigerate until set.
Pack in covered container with waxed papers between layers.
Makes about 3 dozen pieces.

title: marquisettes
directions: Melt chocolate morsels in top of double boiler; pour into bowl of electric mixer.
Add butter, egg yolks, sugar and flour; beat until light and fluffy.
Beat egg whites until stiff, not dry. Fold into batter.
Reserve one cup of batter.
Spread remainder in greased and floured 9-inch square baking pan; bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool in pan.
Cream sweet butter; fold into reserved batter and beat in electric mixer until thick and light.
Spread butter cream on cake and sprinkle with grated chocolate.
Chill until firm.
The cake sinks as it cools, leaving a high rim of cake around edges.
When you frost the cake, do not attempt to cover the rim; spread frosting evenly, leaving rim exposed.
Dip sharp knife in hot water; cut 25 squares.
Refrigerate.

title: cucumber pickles
directions: Remove skin
and
seeds
from large cucumbers, cut into chunks.
Combine
water
and
lime,
soak
cucumbers
in
lime solution for
hours, using an enamel or glass or stainless steel container.
Rinse cucumbers well, soak 3 hours longer in clear water.
Drain.
Combine
sugar,
vinegar,
salt and food coloring.
Heat to	make a syrup.
Put spices in cloth bag and tie bag securely.
Place bag in syrup mixture.	Soak cucumbers in syrup mixture overnight.
The next day, boil for 35 minutes to an hour
or until cucumbers are clear and tender.
Place in hot sterilized	jars
and
seal.
Yields
about
pints
(6 quarts).

title: savory sausage ring
directions: Combine all but peaches and mix well.
Place peach halves on bottom of 6 cup mold (Bundt pan) and then pack sausage into pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Invert mold on absorbent paper.
Do not remove pan.
Let stand until grease is all drained out.
Invert onto serving dish.

title: pesto sauce
directions: Place basil in a blender or food processor with chopping blade.
Add the oil, garlic, parsley, salt, pepper and pine nuts. Blend or process until everything is chopped fine.
Remove and place in a bowl.
Add the grated Parmesan cheese.
Mix.
Toss this with hot spaghetti.

title: beef-chili rellenos won ton appetizers(servings:  4)
directions: Brown and drain beef.
Combine beef, onions, cheese, oregano, cumin, garlic salt and chiles.
Place a spoonful of the meat mixture on each won ton wrapper and follow package directions for folding and sealing.
Deep fry 1 1/2 minutes or until golden; drain on paper towels.
Serve warm.
Makes 6 dozen appetizers.

title: chocolate chip cheesecake
directions: In a large bowl, beat cream cheese until fluffy.
Gradually add condensed milk.
Beat until smooth.
Add eggs and vanilla. Mix well.

title: lemon nut refrigeration cookies
directions: Cream the butter; add sugar.
Mix and blend well.
Add lemon extract and egg; mix well.
Sift flour, baking powder, salt and nutmeg.
Mix with the sugar-butter mixture.
Form into two rolls, 1 1/2-inches in diameter.
Chill overnight.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Thoroughly blend all ingredients and pour into two 9-inch unbaked pie shells.
Bake at 450° for 20 minutes, then at 350° for 30 minutes or until knife inserted comes out clean.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients; pour in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish (greased).
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: *One pound of fresh broccoli may be used.

title: sour cream cookies
directions: Mix butter, sugar, sour cream, eggs, nutmeat and lemon.
Mix flour, soda and baking powder.
Mix all, then you can drop by spoon and flatten with fork or roll out and cut with cookie cuts. Just good.

title: quick chicken casserole
directions: Mix together the preceding ingredients and pour into a greased casserole pan.
Top with crushed potato chips.
Bake at 350°
until it bubbles, about 30 minutes.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Blend sugar and oil.
Beat in eggs and pumpkin.
Sift and add plain flour, soda, baking powder, salt, cinnamon, nutmeg and cloves.
Add nuts (optional).
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Makes 3 miniature loaf pans.
Great with Russian Spice Tea.

title: pumpkin crunch
directions: Line 9 x 13-inch pan with foil.
Pour pumpkin mix in pan. Shake cake mix over top.
Add nut meats, then pour butter over top.

title: sausage and cheese breakfast casserole
directions: Spray bottom of large casserole dish (9 x 13 1/2-inch) with Pam.
Butter 5 slices of bread and place butter side up in casserole dish.
Cover with cheese slices.
Crumble sausage on top of cheese.
Butter remaining 5 slices of bread and place butter side down on top of sausage.
Beat eggs and milk together and pour over casserole.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: peruvian ground beef (capos)
directions: Boil cabbage about 30 minutes.	Take cabbage and start peeling the leaves.
Cook ground beef until brown.	Cook rice. Mix tomato sauce and chopped onions together with bay leaves.
Cut sausages in small portions. Mix sauce and meats together.
Stuff into cabbage leaves.
Let cook for 45 minutes; then ready to eat.

title: angel cookie recipe
directions: Mix all ingredients and put in a pizza pan.
Makes 2 large thin pizza crusts and 1 medium pizza crust. Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar, then add eggs.
Beat thoroughly. Sift dry ingredients together and add raisins.
Add flour mixture to batter alternately with applesauce.
Mix well.
Add nuts.
Pour into a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan or Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: scandinavian salad
directions: Mix the vinegar, sugar, oil, water and salt; put in a quart jar and shake up.
Pour over vegetables.
Let stand overnight. Drain 1 hour before serving.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into grease 9 x 13 dish or pan.
Bake at 425° for 40 minutes.

title: yogurt creme sauce
directions: Combine yogurt, Marshmallow Creme and juice, mixing with electric mixer or wire whisk until well blended.
Chill.
Serve with assorted fruit.
Makes 1 3/4 cups.

title: kindness cookies
directions: Mix honey, oil and eggs. Then add orange rind, salt and oatmeal.
Drop spoonfuls on oiled cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Be kind and share your cookies!

title: cheese croustades
directions: Mix cheeses, mayonnaise, lemon juice, pepper.
Drop by spoonful into Siljans croustades.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: hush puppies
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients; add eggs and 1 cup of milk, stirring well.
Add additional milk if necessary for desired consistency.
Carefully drop batter into hot oil; fry a few at a time, 1 to 2 minutes on each side until golden brown.
Drain and serve immediately.

title: broccoli balls
directions: Mix all together.
Scoop with ice cream scoop.
May be frozen. Pop into microwave for 10 to 12 minutes or in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: "no peek" beef stew
directions: Combine.
Bake 5 hours at 300°, covered.
Do not open oven or lid during the baking time.

title: creamy rice and vegetables
directions: Bring vegetables, milk, garlic salt and basil to a boil in a large saucepan.
Stir in rice and cheese; cover.
Remove from heat.
Let stand 10 minutes or until milk is absorbed.

title: lemon sherbet
directions: Chill the lemon and orange juice and sugar in the freezer. Add milk and cream.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Pour mixture into ice cream freezer.
Mix for approximately 30 minutes, until consistency of mush.
Freeze.
Makes approximately 3-quarts.

title: orange cookies
directions: Beat butter, eggs, sugar and sour milk; mix well.
Add baking powder, soda, salt and flour.
Mix well.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: red lobster rolls
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients.
Form biscuits (balls).
Bake at 450° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Mix melted butter and add garlic powder and brush on top of baked biscuits.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix all dry ingredients in a large bowl.
Add water, eggs, oil, pumpkin and walnuts.
Mix well.
Fill 6 aluminum loaf pans half full.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: yummy bars
directions: Prepare brownie mix according to box directions, adding 1/2 cup pecans.
Spread in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix graham crumbs, condensed milk, chocolate chips and 1/2 cup pecans.
Spread over brownie mix.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool.
Ice with confectioners sugar, mixed with enough milk to spread smoothly. Melt chocolate with butter and drizzle over top.

title: party salad
directions: Boil together the pineapple and sugar for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and add jello, cream cheese, walnuts, celery and cold water.
Next, add Cool Whip.
Put in a large baking dish and refrigerate for 24 hours.

title: crock-pot turkey breast
directions: Cut raw vegetables in chunks.
Put in large crock-pot.
Add water and rosemary.
Cover and cook on low for 10 to 12 hours. You can also use sage or your favorite herbs instead of rosemary. Strain liquid and thicken for gravy.

title: chinese salad
directions: Drain vegetables and put in bowl.
Mix 3/4 cup vinegar and 1 cups sugar.
Combine and bring to a boil.
Let cool.
Mix all together and let set for several hours or overnight in refrigerator.

title: spinach sandwiches
directions: Mix all together the day before serving.
This recipe will make 1 1/2 large loaves of bread.
Delicious and lovely to serve at parties.
May be used as a dip.

title: teriyaki steak
directions: Soak meat in onion and pepper solution overnight or at least 2 to 3 hours, then grill.

title: cream caramel cake
directions: A few nut meats may be added if desired.
Bake in 2 layers or loaf tin in 350° oven.

title: marzipan holly cake
directions: To make this holly cake, frost a 2 layer white or yellow cake with a package of fluffy frosting mix.
Arrange the leaves and berries on top and around the base of the cake.

title: red, white and blueberry shortcake
directions: Split cake into 3 layers.
Place bottom layer on serving plate.
Spread with 1 cup blueberry pie filling.
Add second layer of
cake.
Spread with 1 cup strawberry filling.
Top with 3rd layer of cake.
Frost top and sides of cake with whipped topping. Chill, slice and serve with remaining pie filling on top with whipped topping.
Make as many layers as you want.
Yield: 6 to 8 servings.

title: hot bacon salad dressing
directions: Cook bacon. Remove, leaving small amount of drippings.
Cook in other ingredients while stirring until it thickens.
May add some flour.
Drop in crumbled bacon before serving over fresh salad.
Fantastic!

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients except butter and crackers; crumble crackers and mix with butter.
Spread on potato mixture and bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix all together and drop by spoonfuls onto cookie sheet.
Cook 20 to 25 minutes until brown in 350° oven.

title: mom's slush
directions: Mix sugar and water together till sugar dissolves.
Mix in all other ingredients, except soda.
Put in freezer container - freeze overnight.
(Will not freeze solid.)
To serve - dip ice cream scoop of mix in glass, and pour soda over.
(I prefer - Mountain Dew or ginger ale -a little more flavor to them.)

title: chicken divan
directions: Arrange partially cooked broccoli in an ungreased casserole. Put chicken on broccoli.
Mix together soup, mayonnaise, curry and lemon juice.
Pour over chicken.
Sprinkle one-half cup grated Parmesan cheese on top.
Add bread crumbs mixed with butter on top of cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes (longer if casserole was refrigerated).

title: skillet cookies
directions: Cook dates, oleo, sugar, egg and vanilla together for 5 to 10 minutes.
Add Rice Krispies and nuts.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on wax paper.
Roll in coconut.

title: easy oven stew
directions: Heat oven to 300°.
In large Dutch oven or roasting pan, combine all ingredients; mix well.
Cover; bake at 300° for 6 to 7 hours, stirring occasionally.
Remove bay leaves before serving. Makes 12 (1-cup) servings.

title: caramel pie
directions: Brown 1/2 cup sugar in a black skillet until melted and bubbling.
Add 1/2 cup boiling water and stir quickly.
Set aside. Combine 1 cup sugar and 6 tablespoons flour.
Add egg yolks, milk and sugar mixture.
Mix well.
Cook over medium heat until thick. Stir constantly.
Remove from heat and add margarine and vanilla. Mix.
Pour into pie shell. Beat egg whites until stiff.
Gradually add 1/2 cup sugar and 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Beat well.
Pile on pie and bake at 350° until brown.

title: french breakfast puffs
directions: Mix all ingredients together at once.
Bake in greased muffin tins at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Makes about 12 muffins.

title: spaghetti with clam sauce
directions: Toss pasta with 2 tablespoons parsley and 1 tablespoon oil. Heat 1 tablespoon oil in pan over medium heat.
Add onions, garlic, thyme and pepper.
Cook 3 minutes until onion is tender. Stir in wine and bring to boil.
In small bowl, stir flour, reserved clam juice and 2 tablespoons parsley until blended.
Add to mixture in pan.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, about 3 minutes until it thickens and boils.
Stir in clams; do not boil.
Pour portion over pasta on individual plates; grate Parmesan over.

title: refrigerator rolls
directions: Cream shortening and sugar with electric mixer; add boiling water and mix until shortening melts.
Add salt and the eggs, one at a time, beating well.
Add yeast which had been dissolved in warm water.
Add flour, 1/2 cup at a time.
Place in well-greased mixing bowl, cover and refrigerate.
(This will keep several days in refrigerator.)

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and refrigerate.

title: sweet potato casserole(6 to 8 servings)
directions: Combine sweet potatoes, sugar, butter, eggs, vanilla, cinnamon, nutmeg and milk; mix well.
Spoon into a 2-quart casserole.
Cover with Topping.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: tomato lima bean bake
directions: Saute green pepper and onion.
Place all ingredients in a casserole.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: hamburger pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine ground beef, evaporated milk, ketchup, bread crumbs and onion in large bowl.
Spread mixture evenly in unbaked pie shell.
Bake for 45 minutes and remove pie from oven.
Sprinkle cheese evenly on top.
Serves 6 people.

title: poppy seed bread
directions: Mix sugar, oil, eggs and milk.
Add the rest of the ingredients.
Pour into a lightly greased and floured tube pan or 2 loaf pans.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: polish round rye dip
directions: Spoon out center of bread, reserving bread pieces to be used as dipping pieces.

title: sliced cabbage kimchi
directions: Dissolve the salt in lukewarm water and sprinkle over cabbage.
Cover and let stand for 7 hours.
Rinse the cabbage 3 times in cold water and let drain in a colander.

title: peanut butter cup pie
directions: In a small bowl, mix peanut butter and honey.
Melt in microwave on High for about 20 seconds.
Stir in rice crisps and press into a 9-inch pie pan.
Chill.

title: tennessee cherry delight
directions: Melt magarine.
Add flour and chopped pecans.
Press into a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake for 30 minutes, or until brown.
Let cool.

title: cranberry congealed salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O and sugar in 1 cup of boiling water.
Let cool.
Add orange, cranberries and pecans.
Congeal in icebox overnight in decorator container.

title: cherry winks
directions: Cream shortening and cream cheese.
Gradually add sugar, beating until light and fluffy.
Add eggs and almond extract.
Beat well.
Combine flour, soda and salt.
Add to creamed mixture, beating well.
Chill about 1 hour.

title: spinach and artichoke dip
directions: Saut onion in butter.
Mix with all other ingredients.
Mix well.
Place in baking dish and sprinkle 1/4 cup cheese on top. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until hot and bubbly.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: lima bean casserole
directions: Cook and drain beans and add pimentos.
Over low heat, melt cheese in soup and stir into beans.
Salt and pepper to taste. Top with cracker crumbs and brown in oven.

title: noodle casserole
directions: Brown ground beef, chopped pepper and onion; add salt to taste.
Cook noodles; drain well.
Mix all ingredients.
Bake at 300° for 20 minutes.

title: sunshine soup
directions: Simmer celery, potatoes, onion, salt and bouillon in 1-quart water until partially soft.
Add veggie bag and continue simmering until soft.
Add soup and cheese.
Heat until cheese is melted. Do not boil.

title: chocolate fudge number 1
directions: Boil first 4 ingredients in saucepan or double boiler to soft ball stage.
Cool; beat until fluffy.
Add 1 teaspoon vanilla and 1 1/2 cups chopped nuts.
Add butter.
Pour into greased pan.
Cut into squares.

title: shrimp boulettes or patties
directions: In food processor, place onions, bell pepper and green onions. Do these first and then process potatoes and shrimp. Add eggs when all is processed and mix well. Now add your seasoning to the mixture and drop by teaspoon in hot oil and cook until brown.

title: easy chocolate delight pie
directions: Heat all but 3 squares of the chocolate with 1/4 cup of the milk in microwave at High for 1 1/2 to 2 minutes.
Stir until melted.
Beat in cream cheese, sugar and remaining milk.
Gently stir in whipped cream until smooth.
Spoon into crust.
Freeze until firm.
Remove from freezer and let stand 30 minutes.
Melt remaining chocolate squares and drizzle over pie as a garnish.

title: squash patties
directions: Place squash and onion in a colander and sprinkle with salt. Let stand until all moisture is gone.
Pour into large bowl and add flour, cornmeal, pepper, cheese and egg.
Mix well.
Form into patties and fry until golden brown on both sides.

title: red beans and rice
directions: Soak beans overnight in cold water or boil 2 minutes and let stand 1 hour.
Place beans in a pot; add enough water to cover and bring to a boil.
Add onion, garlic and salt pork.
When half done, add salt and pepper and cook until tender.
Add the rice and cook over low heat 10 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: butterscotch brownies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease an 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Blend oil and brown sugar.
Beat in egg. Sift dry ingredients and stir in vanilla and nuts.
(I mix nuts with flour mixture.)
Spread in pan, bake 30 minutes. When slightly cool, cut in squares.

title: meaty baked beans
directions: In large skillet, brown beef with onion and green pepper until meat is brown and vegetables are tender.
Drain fat.
Stir in brown sugar and ketchup.
Add beans and mix well.
Spoon into 2 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 hour or until beans are as thick as desired.
Double recipe for large quantity.

title: bubba's red beans and rice
directions: Mix beans and water in a very large pot; bring to a boil over high heat, stirring occasionally.
Reduce heat to medium; stir in ground chuck, onions, mushrooms, olives and celery.
Cook over medium heat until meat is done.
Add bouillon, soy sauce and Worcestershire sauce.
Turn heat to high and bring to a boil. When mixture reaches a vigorous boil, turn off heat.
Stir in rice, cover pot and let stand until cool enough to serve.
Serves 2 Bubbas or 5 regular people.

title: italy-pizza base
directions: Sift the flour into a big bowl.
Add the dried yeast.
Add the water and oil.
Stir thoroughly until it forms a dough.
Knead until smooth and stretchy.
Cover with a damp cloth and leave to rise for 30 minutes.
Grease 2 round 10-inch pizza pans.
Halve the dough and press each half into a pan.
Spread the bases with your chosen toppings and bake for 25 minutes at 350°.

title: mildred swifts sour cream cookies
directions: Cream together sugar, butter, vanilla and egg real good, because when mixing in flour and dry ingredients and sour cream, you mix as little as possible.
Blend in other ingredients, beginning and ending with flour mixture, alternating with sour cream.
Roll on floured board.
(Handle as little as possible.) Cook on greased cookie sheet 6 to 8 minutes on 425°.
May sprinkle with sugar before baking.
Be careful.
Do not overbake.

title: ribs with onion sauce
directions: Roast ribs, meaty side down, in shallow roasting pan at 450° for 30 minutes.
Drain off excess fat.
Turn ribs, meaty side up. Meanwhile, cook onion and garlic in hot oil until tender. Add remaining ingredients, 1/2 cup water and 1 1/2 teaspoons salt. Simmer 10 minutes.
Pour sauce over ribs.
Reduce oven temperature to 350°.
Bake ribs about 1 1/2 hours or until tender, basting occasionally, with sauce.
If sauce gets too thick, add more water.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: banana cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs, and then other ingredients with bananas last.
Pour into greased, floured pan (1 large rectangular or 2 smaller pans).
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes (or until spongy when you touch it).

title: funky chicken
directions: Mix dressing, water, preserves and soup mix.
Place chicken in ungreased baking pan.
Cover with mixture.
Bake 1 to 1 1/2 hours, depending on size of pieces, at 325°.

title: zucchini pie
directions: Boil zucchini in water lightly.
Let set for a few minutes. Drain and put in pie shell. Sprinkle with lemon juice. Add other ingredients. Add crust. Bake 40 minutes at 400°.

title: banana cream pie
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together and add milk in saucepan. Stirring constantly, bring to a boil.
Add butter and vanilla. Pour into prepared baked crust when cool.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Cream the butter and sugar. Add eggs and beat. Add applesauce and beat.
Add sifted dry ingredients.
Beat.
Fold in raisins and nuts. Bake in tube cake pan at 350° for 60 minutes or until done.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Combine first four ingredients.
Bring to a boil.
Let mixture cool, then add berries and pour into baked pie shell.
Refrigerate until well chilled.
Top with whipped topping if desired.

title: chicken-n-dumplings
directions: Boil chicken with carrots and celery.
Remove chicken from water and debone.
To water with carrots and celery, add 1 stick margarine, cans of cream of mushroom, celery and chicken soups. Stir this mixture.
Slice thawed tortillas in strips (1-inch). Layer tortilla strips and chicken.
Simmer for 1 hour.
Do not stir.

title: yellow one-bowl cake
directions: Soften margarine; add sugar and eggs.
Beat until creamy.
Add rest of ingredients and beat 2 minutes.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: fresh tomato salsa
directions: Combine all ingredients, stirring gently, cover and chill. (You may substitute parsley for the cilantro.)
Yields 3 1/2 cups.

title: buttermilk fried chicken
directions: Place chicken in a large flat dish.
Pour buttermilk over; cover and refrigerate for 1 hour.

title: scalloped cheesy potatoes
directions: Preheat oven 425°.
Grease 13 x 9 x 2 inch baking dish.
In large bowl, stir together the soup and cheese.
With a rubber spatula, fold in the potatoes and onions until thoroughly coated. Scrape into prepared baking dish.
Cover with foil.

title: jean thompson's strawberry salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water; stir until clear.
Add strawberries and mix well (I cut up strawberries as I mix with hot Jell-O).
Refrigerate 10 minutes or until slightly thickened. Fold in Cool Whip.
Refrigerate at least 2 hours.
Strawberry lovers love this at Thanksgiving, Christmas or any other time it's served!

title: gateau clardine
directions: Whip the heavy cream until firm and set aside.
Mix the pudding with the milk until combined.
Fold in whipped cream.

title: aunt freda's apple cake
directions: Generously grease tube or Bundt cake pan before pouring mixed ingredients in.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: dump cake
directions: Put pie filling in a 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Sprinkle box of dry cake mix over filling.
Place thin slices of oleo over cake mix and pour cup of water around edges.
Sprinkle with chopped nuts.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Use any pie filling combination.

title: oriental stir-fry
directions: In small bowl mix soy sauce, sherry, cornstarch, salt, red pepper and ginger. Heat oil in wok or high sided frying pan. Briefly fry cashews; remove. Fry peppers and onions; remove. Add more oil if needed; fry chicken or beef pieces. Remove. Add remaining vegetables; stir-fry 2 to 3 minutes. Add sauce and all previously fried ingredients. Stir and fry another 2 to 3 minutes. Serve with white or fried rice.

title: calico beans
directions: Brown and drain hamburger.
Mix all ingredients in crock-pot. Cook all day long.

title: beef and rice casserole
directions: Place uncooked rice in casserole. Brown ground chuck in skillet. Season with onion powder, garlic powder and salt and pepper to taste. Put on top of rice. Pour remaining ingredients over this. Bake for 1 hour at 350°, uncovered.

title: quickie chicken and rice
directions: Cut up	chicken.
Mix
the
salt,
pepper,
Accent
and paprika together
and sprinkle the pieces of chicken well. Set them
aside.
Mix together the rice, soup mix, soup and water. Let stand
for	5 minutes, then pour into a 9 x 13-inch baking pan. Put
the pieces of chicken on top of the mixture.
Place uncovered in a 350° oven and bake for 45 minutes, or until the rice
is puffed up and the chicken is tender.
Serve at once. Serves 4.

title: sugarless cake
directions: Preheat oven to 300 degrees.
Mix all ingredients and bake in a prepared tube pan for 40 minutes.

title: shrimp gelatin salad
directions: Soak gelatin in 1/2 cup water (cold).
Heat soup to boiling. Blend in gelatin and cream cheese.
(If mixture is lumpy, use mixer to mix.)
Cool.
Add remaining ingredients and place in mold, greased in mayonnaise.
Use a fish mold for this presentation; it makes your salad look elegant.
Push the 2 stuffed green olives in the front of your fish for the eyes.
If you don't have a fish mold, put in any mold and omit the green olives.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: broccoli bread
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan or an iron skillet.
I prefer using the Cheddar cheese and I also prefer some other cornbread mix that is not as sweet as Jiffy!

title: scalloped scallops
directions: Coat crackers and bread with melted butter.
In casserole, place layer of scallops and a layer of crumbs.
Mix until all used up.
(Save some crackers for the top.)
Add milk and bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes (uncovered).

title: baked macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni as package directs; drain.

title: overnight salad
directions: Fry bacon; drain, cool and crumble into small pieces.
In a large bowl, layer lettuce, cauliflower, onion and bacon.
Repeat 3 times.
Pour sugar, salt and cheese on top.
Finish with the mayonnaise.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Toss the salad just before serving.
Enjoy.

title: peach pie chantilly
directions: Combine peaches and sugar.
Mix Dream Whip.
Add to peaches and sugar.
Pour into pie shell.
Top with peaches and chill 2 hours.

title: granny's banana bread
directions: Dissolve soda in water.
Mix all ingredients well and bake in loaf pan for 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.

title: sugarless cake
directions: Cook raisins in 2 cups of water.
Drain and reserve liquid. Blend the next 5 ingredients and stir into raisins, adding the remaining ingredients and raisin liquid.
Mix well and bake in 9 x 9-inch pan at 350° until straw comes out clean.

title: swedish potatis korv
directions: Mix all together.
Put in 2 kidney shaped pans in steamer and steam for 2 hours.

title: breast of chicken on rice
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix mushroom soup with milk, set 1/2 aside.
Mix remaining mixture with rice, mushrooms and 1/2 onion soup mix.
Pour into oblong 11 x 7-inch pan.
Put chicken breast over mix, then top with reserved soups/milk.
Sprinkle with remaining onion soup and bake 1 hour, covered, or 15 minutes, uncovered at 350°.
Serves 4.

title: arroz con pollo
directions: In an 8-quart Dutch oven over medium-high heat, in hot oil, brown chicken, a few pieces at a time; set aside.
In the drippings, over medium heat, cook onion until it is tender.
Add chicken, water, tomatoes, pimentos and olives and all their liquids and remaining ingredients except peas.
Heat to boiling.
Reduce heat to low.
Cover Dutch oven and simmer chicken mixture 30 minutes or until chicken is almost fork-tender, occasionally lifting rice with fork.
Add thawed peas to Dutch oven and cook 10 minutes more.
(If mixture seems dry when peas are added, cook covered; if it seems moist, cook uncovered.)

title: cupcakes
directions: You have to get buns and cheese and mustard.
You start the fire.
Barbecue hamburgers cook for 50 minutes or so.
You can add lettuce.
That's all.

title: diabetic cocoa
directions: Combine cocoa and salt in small saucepan.
Add water and place over low heat or in top of double boiler.
Boil gently for 2 minutes, stirring constantly.
Add milk and sugar substitute.
Stir constantly until mixture comes to a boil.
Remove from heat immediately.
Add vanilla.
Stir and serve.
Yields 4 servings. Serving size:
1 cup.

title: baked stuffed shrimp
directions: Crush crackers to make fine crumbs (food processor works best). Add ingredients, except shrimp, and mix together.
Clean shrimp. Remove all shells except tail and split for stuffing.
Stuff shrimp with stuffing (rolled into small balls and formed to shrimp). Sprinkle with butter and bake, uncovered, at 350° for 25 minutes. Sprinkle with lemon.

title: no fat biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Mix ingredients thoroughly.
Knead dough, roll out and cut out.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes until browned.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Pour into greased, large casserole dish and bake, uncovered, at 375° for 1 hour.

title: caramel coconut ice cream dessert
directions: Heat milk butterscotch chips and marshmallows in double boiler until melted; mix well.
Cool until thick.
Mix margarine, coconut, graham cracker crumbs and pecan pieces together to make crust.
Put half of crumb mixture in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan, keeping the other half for the top.
Cut 1/2 to 1 gallon of softened ice cream into thin slices.
Place 1/2 of the thin sliced ice cream on the crust.
Pour the sauce over the frozen solid ice cream.
Set this in freezer to set up so you can repeat ice cream layer.
Repeat ice cream layer.
Top with rest of crumbs.

title: sally lunn (bread)
directions: Heat milk with butter and lard just to boil.
Cool to lukewarm. Pour over eggs, beaten lightly.
Add sugar and salt.
Dissolve yeast in water, then add to mixture.
Beat in flour.
Let rise in covered bowl from 3 to 6 hours, dependent on weather.
Poke down and put in well-greased tube or Bundt pan.
Let rise, covered for 1 hour.
Cook, covered, 45 minutes at 325°.
This is an old southern bread from Virginia which has been made for years in my family.

title: turkey roulettes
directions: Sift together the flour, baking powder and salt.
Cut in shortening with pastry blender.
Stir in milk to make a soft dough. Round up on lightly floured cloth-covered board.
Knead very lightly, just to smooth up.
Roll out 1/8-inch thick into a rectangle 9 x 18-inch.
Mix together turkey, cut into thin bite size pieces, gravy, green pepper and onion.
Spread mixture over dough.
Roll up tightly, beginning at wide side.
Seal well by pinching edge of dough into roll.
Cut into 1 1/2-inch slices. Arrange cut side up in well-greased pan.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes in hot oven (425°).
Serve with hot gravy or medium white sauce. Garnish tops with finely chopped parsley.
Serves 6.

title: cream of broccoli soup
directions: Cook broccoli until done; reserve about 3/4 cup of the liquid. Add 2 bouillon cubes to this liquid until dissolved.
Saute onion and carrots in 3 tablespoons butter.
Add to broccoli and liquid. Add milk, cheese, salts, pepper and 2 tablespoons butter.
Cook until cheese is melted completely and liquid is very hot (but not boiling).
Stir in cornstarch mixture.
Stir until thickened.

title: wilma's lasagna
directions: Cook noodles; drain.
Brown meat, stirring with fork until crumbly. Stir in garlic and salt.
Add tomato sauce and simmer. Mix together cream cheese, sour cream, cottage cheese and green onions.
Arrange alternate layers of noodles, meat sauce and cream cheese mixture in a 2 1/2-quart casserole.

title: peanut butter and kisses cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In a medium bowl, beat together butter, peanut butter, brown sugar, 1/4 cup granulated sugar, egg, vanilla and salt.
Beat until light and fluffy.
Add flour and baking soda, mixing until blended.
Shape dough into 48 balls using a rounded teaspoonful for each.
Roll balls in the 3 tablespoons sugar and place 2-inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake for 8 to 10 minutes or until light brown.
Immediately top each cookie with a candy kiss, carefully press into cookie.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Drain pineapple. Add enough water to juice to make 1 cup. Bring to a boil. Add Jell-O.
Mix cranberries, pineapple and Seven-Up with juice and Jell-O.
Pour in mold, etc.
Let jell. Top with whipped Cool Whip. Toast nuts in 2 tablespoons margarine; sprinkle on top.

title: pear honey
directions: Cook first 3 ingredients until thick (nearly as thick as apple butter), then add the can of pineapple and cook 15 minutes longer. Put in jars and seal.

title: oreo ice cream dessert
directions: Crumble Oreos with butter.
Hold out 2 cups, place rest on bottom of pan.
Spread soft ice cream on top; freeze about 20 minutes.
Put hot fudge on top of ice cream and top with Cool Whip.
Cover with 2 cups of the crushed Oreos.
Keep in freezer.

title: deluxe pecan pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into 2 unbaked pie shells.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes; reduce heat to 350° and bake 30 to 35 minutes.

title: tortilla beef roll-ups
directions: Mix cream cheese, mustard and horseradish together until smooth; spread over the tortillas. Top each with lettuce, cilantro, beef and tomatoes. Roll up and then wrap with plastic wrap for at least 2 hours. Cut each roll into slices and serve.

title: cream of crab soup
directions: Saute onion in margarine. Stir in Beau Monde and next 4 ingredients. Cook, stirring constantly, until it begins to boil. Combine cornstarch and 2 cups skim milk gradually.
