Add to hot mixture. Bring to a boil over medium heat, stirring constantly. Cook 1 minute. Reduce heat and stir in crabmeat and sherry. Yields 5 cups.

title: hawaiian delight
directions: Cook the rice until fluffy. Drain pineapple and reserve liquid.
While rice is still warm, mix in a large bowl with pineapple and large Cool Whip. Add some pineapple juice to make creamy.
Place cherry halves around top, if desired.
Serve at room temperature with extra Cool Whip on top.
Best if let stand overnight.

title: pesto sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients in a
food processor.
Stop and start several times and scrape down
sides
of container until sauce is smooth.
Transfer to bowl.
Serve
with pasta, tossed greens or endive salad.
Makes approximately 1 cup.

title: korean chicken
directions: Mix Soy Sauce, sugar, ginger in bowl.
Chop green onions and add to bowl.
Mix and sit to the side.

title: ever ready raisin bran muffins
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in a large bowl.
Make a well in center of mixture.
Add eggs, buttermilk and oil; stir.
Cover and store in refrigerator until ready to bake.
(Can be kept for 6 weeks.)
Fill muffin papers 2/3 full.
Bake at 400° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix together sugar, oil, eggs and pumpkin.
Sift together dry ingredients.
Alternately add dry ingredients with water to first mixture.
Add nuts and pour into three greased 1-pound load pans or three 1-pound coffee cans (flour the pans).

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Cook spaghetti.
Rinse.
Drain mushrooms; reserve liquid. Melt butter; saute onion, seasonings and mushroom liquid.
Blend in soup; stir until smooth.
Gradually add milk, stirring constantly, until smooth and thick.
Mix spaghetti in buttered casserole with mushrooms, pimentos and chicken.
Pour sauce over and mix.
Top with Cheddar cheese, then Parmesan cheese.
Bake, until slightly brown, at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix diced chicken, soup mixture, salt and pepper.
In a separate bowl melt 1/2 stick oleo; add Ritz crackers and mix. Sprinkle this mixture on top of casserole and bake at 350° until bubbly.

title: hackberry leather(modern)
directions: Mix puree with honey.
Spread thinly on clean dry board or waxed paper.
Suspend cheesecloth over puree to keep insects from fruit.
Allow to dry, then peel from surface.
Roll up and wrap in plastic wrap or waxed paper.
Store in covered containers.

title: scalloped corn
directions: To corn, add beaten eggs, sugar, seasoning, melted butter and scalded milk.
Turn into buttered casserole and bake at 350° for about 45 minutes or until firm.

title: beef burgundy stew with rice verte
directions: Place meat in a bowl.
Sprinkle with bottled browning sauce and toss lightly until evenly coated.
Brown in oil.
Add tomatoes, wine, bouillon cube and seasonings.
Cover and simmer 45 minutes.
Add onions and carrots.
Cover and cook 45 minutes longer or until meat and vegetables are tender.

title: layered salad
directions: Arrange potato slices on large salad plate.
Top with avocado slices, then tomato pieces.
Sprinkle with basil.
Whisk together oil, vinegar or wine, salt and pepper to taste and pour over vegetables.
Set aside 10 minutes for dressing to soak in before serving.
Serves 2.

title: cream puff cake
directions: Combine water and oleo in pan; bring to boil.
Add flour and remove from burner.
Mix well.
Add eggs, one at a time, and beat after each one.
Spread evenly in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 400°
for 25 to 30 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Press center down with a spoon, leaving high edge.
Cool, then blend pudding, milk and cream cheese.
Spread into cooled shell.
Top with Cool Whip and drizzle chocolate syrup over Cool Whip.
You can sprinkle with chopped nuts. Keep in refrigerator.

title: chicken fried rice
directions: Combine chicken, soy sauce and 1/2 teaspoon salt.
Let stand 15 minutes.
Cook rice in hot oil in skillet over medium heat until golden brown; stir frequently.
Reduce heat; add chicken with soy sauce and broth.
Simmer, covered, 20 to 25 minutes or until rice is tender.
Remove cover the last few minutes.
Stir in onion, green pepper and celery; cook over medium heat until liquid is absorbed.
Push rice mixture to sides of skillet.
Add eggs and cook until almost set; blend into rice.
Stir in lettuce or Chinese cabbage.
Serve at once with soy sauce.

title: foolproof candy
directions: In a heavy saucepan, mix sugar, butter, marshmallows and milk. Place on low heat after mixture comes to a boil.
Cook for 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat; add morsels, nuts and vanilla.
Stir until morsels are completely melted.
Pour into a buttered dish.
When cool, cut into squares.

title: potato carrot kugel
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Cook carrots and onion in water and margarine for several minutes, until tender.
Grate potatoes and add immediately. Remove from heat and stir in beaten egg yolks.

title: debbie's barbecues
directions: Combine all ingredients, except meat and simmer for 15 minutes.
Add cooked meat.
Continue to simmer until thick. Seasoning can be adjusted to taste.

title: artichoke rice salad
directions: Cook rice as directed with butter.
Cool rice.
Add onions, peppers and olives.
Drain artichokes (reserve marinade) and add them.
In separate bowl, mix marinade, curry powder and mayonnaise. Toss with rice mix.
Chill 8 hours or overnight.
Yields 6 servings.

title: easy almond bars
directions: Combine flour, sugar, margarine, eggs, baking powder, almond extract and salt.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle with 1 tablespoon sugar and almonds.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: beef and noodle casserole
directions: Brown beef and drain fat.
Saute onion and pepper in butter or margarine.
Add beef, Worcestershire sauce, noodles and soups. Mix well.
Spoon into a greased 3-quart casserole and top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Boil chickens.
Reserve broth.
To 3 cups broth add finely chopped onion, celery, tomatoes and mushrooms.
Cook until tender. Add cooked spaghetti and deboned chicken.
Add cheese gradually until melted.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: brownie dessert
directions: Mix and bake brownie mix as directed on package. Cool and break into small pieces. Mix chocolate pudding as directed on package. Use a glass dish and layer brownies, pudding and Cool Whip; repeat. Top with Cool Whip sprinkled with a few brownie pieces. Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: home style fried rice
directions: Add 1 tablespoon of oil to the pan or wok.
Spread out the beaten egg and cook until done.
Remove the egg and chop into small pieces.
Add 1 tablespoon oil; heat the pan and saute the celery and bean sprouts.
Remove and set aside.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Beat eggs, sugar, Wesson oil, vanilla, salt and cinnamon until creamy in texture.
Add flour and soda mixed together.
Stir in apples, cherries and coconut.
Batter will be very stiff and probably have to be stirred with a spoon.
Spoon in 9-inch tube pan and smooth batter evenly.
Heat oven to between 290° and 300° and bake 1 hour and 20 minutes.

title: oven baked pork chops
directions: Brown pork chops.
Arrange in casserole.
Salt and pepper. Top with lemon and onion slices.
Mix tomato sauce and brown sugar together and pour over chops.
Cover and bake for 1 hour at 325°. Baste occasionally.
Remove cover and bake 15 minutes longer.

title: beef stroganoff with noodles
directions: In small saucepan, cook meat and onion until meat is thoroughly cooked and onion is tender, about 5 minutes.
Add water, bouillon cube and Worcestershire; heat to boiling.
Stir to dissolve bouillon.
Stir in mushrooms; reduce heat.
Stir together sour cream and flour; add to beef mixture.
Cook, stirring occasionally until sauce thickens; do not boil.
Meanwhile, cook noodles according to package directions; drain. Toss hot noodles and sauce; sprinkle with parsley if desired.
Makes 3 to 4 servings.

title: play dough
directions: Bring water, oil and food coloring to a boil.
Remove and add dry ingredients.
Mix well and knead play dough.
Store in airtight containers.

title: spinach lasagne
directions: Mix eggs, Ricotta cheese, spinach and any seasonings (i.e., basil, garlic or oregano).
In 9 x 13-inch pan, put layer of spaghetti sauce, then layer of uncooked noodles, then half of egg-cheese-spinach mixture, then layer of Mozzarella cheese and Parmesan cheese.
Repeat layers again, except put extra sauce before you put Mozzarella and Parmesan cheese topping (i.e., sauce, noodles, spinach mixture, sauce and cheese).
Bake uncovered for 1 hour at 350°.

title: melange jello mold
directions: Mix fruit and nuts in a large bowl.
In a separate bowl, mix the Jell-O and gelatine with the cup of hot water.
Add this mixture to the fruit and nuts.
Pour half of this mixture in a mold.
Refrigerate until thickened.
Spread with sour cream, then cover with the other half of the gelatine.
Chill until set.

title: louise's oatmeal cookies
directions: Sift flour, salt and soda.
Add remaining ingredients.
Form into a roll and chill.
Cut and bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until golden brown.

title: carrot raisin salad
directions: Combine Sun-Maid raisins, carrot and drained pineapple. Blend in mayonnaise, lemon juice and salt.
Serve on crisp salad greens.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: curried cauliflower
directions: Boil the cauliflower in 3 cups water and 1/2 tsp. salt.
When cooked, drain and break into flowerettes.
Place the cauliflower flowerettes in a greased 2 quart casserole.
Combine next 4 ingredients and pour over cauliflower.
Combine 1/2 cup bread crumbs and 3 Tbsp. butter.
Put on top of casserole and bake 30 minutes at 350 degrees.
Serves 6-8.

title: white sauce
directions: Melt butter without browning.
Add flour and salt and cook until well blended.
Add milk slowly, stirring constantly, so milk won't scorch.
Cook to boiling point, then remove from heat.
Beat well, until creamy.

title: cherry salad
directions: Mix Cool Whip and condensed milk by hand and large spoon. Add Cherry Pie filling, pineapple, and nuts. Place in dish. Chill.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Prepare dressing according to box.
Boil chicken on medium heat for 45 minutes.
When done and cool enough to handle, tear into bite size pieces.
Place broccoli in Pyrex dish (8 x 11-inch), turning end to end.
Put cut up chicken over broccoli.
Mix mayonnaise with soup (don't add water) and heat.
Stir until heated (don't boil).
Pour over broccoli and chicken.
Sprinkle grated cheese over everything.
Place dressing on top.
Bake at 300° for approximately 40 minutes.
If dressing starts to brown, place foil over top.

title: cranberry-orange bread
directions: Grease loaf pan, 9x5x3.
Blend dry ingredients.
Mix in shortening, orange rind, juice and egg.
Fold in cranberries. Pour into pan and bake 1 hour at 350 degrees.
Cool thoroughly before slicing with a thin, sharp knife.
(Freezes well too.)

title: swiss-stuffed mushrooms
directions: Clean mushrooms with damp paper towels.
Remove stems and set aside.
Sprinkle inside of caps with salt.
Chop stems finely. Saute in butter over medium heat 3 to 4 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients, except mushroom caps, mixing well.
Spoon mixture into mushroom caps.
Place stuffed mushrooms on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 5 to 8 minutes or until thoroughly heated.
Serve hot.
Yields 1 1/2 dozen.

title: sticky buns
directions: Grease and flour Bundt pan. Place frozen rolls around sides and bottom of pan. Mix brown sugar, butterscotch pudding mix, sugar, cinnamon and pecans. Sprinkle over rolls. Pour melted butter over the top. Place uncovered on cabinet overnight. Next morning bake in preheated oven at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: big buck's supper
directions: In large skillet fill bottom with cooking oil.
Add meat and season.
Cook on medium until brown.
Add Worcestershire.
Simmer. Dilute with water.
Serve over rice or egg noodles.

title: meat loaf with sweet potatoes
directions: Mix ground meats, onion, celery, parsley, eggs, crumbs, salt and pepper together in large bowl.

Place between two large sheets of wax paper and roll into a rectangle about 14 x 10-inches. Remove the top paper and spread the meat with the mashed potatoes. Sprinkle with the chopped pepper or onion or both.
Roll the mixture jelly roll fashion, seal the outside edge, and place in a shallow greased baking pan, seam side down.
Bake in a preheated 350° oven for 45 minutes.
Drain off excess fat and drizzle the syrup on top of the loaf.
Bake 25 minutes more or until the juices are clear and the loaf is golden brown.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix together and drop by teaspoonfuls in deep fat.

title: seafood bisque
directions: Heat in crock-pot until cheese is melted and mixture is heated through.
May be doubled.
Great for cold days.

title: apple crunch pie
directions: Peel
and
cut
apples for pie.
Use a 13 x 9-inch cake pan greased with butter.
Place apples in dish and pour orange juice over
them.
Set
aside.
Combine flour, sugar, butter, nutmeg and cinnamon.
Mix ingredients.
Will be crumbly.
Pour over apples. Bake 45 minutes at 375°.

title: chinese hamburger hash
directions: Brown
meat
in
oil, add onions and celery; cook until soft. Add
other	ingredients.
Pour into an 8 x 11-inch pan. Bake, uncovered,	at 350° for 30 minutes.
Spread 1 large pan Chinese noodles over top and bake for 15 minutes uncovered.

title: diabetic coconut pie
directions: Put in pie crust.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: easy chicken-n-dumplings
directions: Rinse whole chicken well.
Place in an 8-quart pot and cover with water.
Add next 4 ingredients.
Boil until chicken is done. Remove chicken from water and set aside to cool.
To simmering water, add cream of chicken soup and mushroom soup.
Stir well. Bring liquid to a slow boil.
Cut flour tortillas into dumpling shapes and drop into boiling liquid, one dumpling at a time.
Cook for 20 to 30 minutes, until dumplings are tender.
Debone the chicken and add to dumplings.
Serves 8 hungry people.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Stir together flour, baking soda, cinnamon, salt and oats. Cream together shortening and sugar until light and fluffy.
Beat in eggs.
Add flour mixture.
Mix in raisins and walnuts.
Drop from a teaspoon onto greased baking sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: party punch
directions: Mix juice, Kool-Aid and sugar into large pitcher or punch bowl.
Add orange slices for decoration.

title: death by chocolate
directions: Freeze Heath bars.
Prepare brownie mix as directed on box for cake-like brownies.
Cool.

title: pecan pie
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Mix eggs, syrup, sugar, shortening, milk and salt in large bowl.
(Do not beat.)
Stir in pecans. Pour into unbaked pie crust.
Bake for 15 minutes at 425°.
Turn oven temperature down to 350° and continue baking for 30 minutes or until done.

title: angel pie
directions: Beat egg whites with cream of tartar until very stiff.
Add gradually and beat well until absorbed and glossy 1/2 cup sugar. Fold in chopped nuts.
Bake 1 hour at 300° in 8-inch pie plate. Build up sides as much as possible.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Layer the above ingredients in 8 x 8 inch dish in order as listed. Brown and serve, approximately 20 to 30 min. at 350°.

title: pistachio dream
directions: Mix cream cheese, pudding, pineapple and nuts together.
Mix well.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Add cherries and serve.

title: strawberry pretzel dessert
directions: Blend the first 3 ingredients together. Put in a 9x13 pan. Bake at 350 degrees for 5 minutes. Cool. Beat sugar and cream cheese together. Add 1/2 of the cool whip and spread over cooled crust. Dissolve jello in water, add frozen berries. When partially set spoon gently over cream
cheese. Add remaining cool whip. You can garnish with fresh berries if you desire. Let set overnight.

title: famous amos chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix well with mixer: cake mix, pudding mixes & Bisquick.
Add mayonnaise and mix.

title: homemade poultry seasoning
directions: Crush all these together until fine.
Store in a tightly covered jar.
Use in same proportions as prepared poultry seasoning from store.

title: sweet and sour mustard
directions: In heavy saucepan, whisk together all the ingredients.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly until thickened.
Pour into small jars.
Keep in fridge.
Makes 1 1/2 cups.

title: crust-less cheese cake
directions: Put cottage cheese in blender and beat until smooth; add to cream cheese and mix well.
Add eggs, 1 at a time, beating well after each.
Add sugar slowly, then cornstarch, vanilla, lemon juice, melted butter and sour cream in that order.
Pour into spring-form pan that has been well buttered and dusted with vanilla wafer crumbs.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.
Turn off. Leave in oven for 1 hour.

title: cornbread
directions: Grease pan well.
Mix and sift flour, cornmeal, salt, baking powder and sugar.
Add beaten egg and milk; stir well.
Bake at 425° for 25 minutes or until done.

title: ice cream
directions: Place in home ice cream freezer and mix until firm.
Makes 4 quarts.

title: string bean casserole
directions: Drain beans and corn; mix all ingredients together.
Crush Ritz crackers in a different container.
Melt butter.
Mix crackers and butter together.
Cover top of mixture with the crackers.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: cabbage rolls
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients; add meat and rice and mix together. Steam cabbage leaves 3 minutes or until limp. Place a small amount of meat mixture on each leaf; fold in sides and roll ends over meat. Cabbage rolls may be held together with a toothpick. Place in a pot deep enough to add enough water and tomato sauce to cover cabbage rolls. Cook slowly for about 1 hour or until done.

title: down home mustard greens
directions: Wash greens thoroughly.
Use large stockpot.
Put turkey leg in bottom of pot.
Cook greens until tender.
Add all seasoning.

title: jumbo chocolate snappers
directions: Melt chocolate.
Cream shortening.
Gradually add 1/2 cup sugar, beating until light and fluffy.
Add chocolate, egg and corn syrup, beating well.
Combine flour, soda, salt and cinnamon; add to creamed mixture, beating until blended.

title: old south cucumber lime pickles
directions: Tie pickling spices into soft net or cloth bag and drop into liquid.
Soak clean cucumbers in water and lime mixture in crockery or enamel ware for 12 hours or overnight (do not use aluminum).
Wash 3 times in clear water; soak in fresh ice water for 3 hours.
Combine remaining ingredients; bring to a boil (low).
Stir until sugar is dissolved.
Add cucumbers and soak 5 to 6 hours or overnight.
Boil pickles in soaking liquid for 35 minutes.
Fill sterilized quart jars with cucumber slices, pour syrup over them, leaving 1/8-inch head space.
Cap each jar when filled.

title: s'more snacks "marshmallows"
directions: Using small container, mix gelatin in 1/2 cup cold water.
In 2-quart saucepan, combine sugar, syrup and 1/3 cup water.
Cook to soft ball stage (240°), stirring only until sugar dissolves. Remove from heat; stir in gelatin to dissolve.
Let cool 10 minutes.
In large mixing bowl, beat egg white until stiff peaks form.
Slowly add syrup, beating on high speed with mixer until candy stands in soft peaks.
Sprinkle a cold cut container (like Tupperware) with generous amounts of powdered sugar; spread candy over.
Let stand overnight.
Dust top of candy with more powdered sugar.
Dip pastry cutter or table knife in warm water and gently cut into squares.
Makes 1 1/2 pounds.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Shred cheese, mix with mayonnaise, cream of celery soup, egg and oregano.
Cook broccoli until tender but not soft.
Pour mixture over broccoli, sprinkle some bread crumbs over top and bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: pork chop and apple bake
directions: In skillet brown chops (use shortening if necessary).
Pour off fat.
In 2 quart shallow baking dish 12 x 8 x 2 combine beans and cinnamon.
Top with chops.
Cover.
Bake at 350 degrees for 30 minutes.
Combine sugar and dash of cloves, if desired.
Top chops with apples, sprinkle with sugar mixture.
Bake uncovered 15 minutes more or less until apples are tender.
Serves 6.

title: pecan dreams
directions: Cream butter, sugar and flour.
Add other ingredients.
Mix well.
Break off pieces the side of large date; roll in palm of hand.
Place on greased cookie sheet.
Bake in slow oven, 250°, for 40 to 45 minutes.
Roll in confectioners sugar while hot.

title: shoe peg corn salad
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large bowl.
Pour entire bottle of salad dressing and marinate overnight.
Drain before serving.

title: poor man's lobster
directions: Wrap serving size portions in small piece of aluminum foil. Poke fork through foil 1 time.
Cook on top of stove for 20 minutes.
Serve with hot melted butter.
Serves 3 to 4.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cut sausage into bite size pieces. Cook in small skillet until lightly browned.
Drain off any drippings.

title: blueberry pie
directions: Beat the cream cheese with the sugar until light and fluffy. Fold in Cool Whip.
Slice bananas onto graham cracker crusts.
Top with the cream cheese mixture, then spread pie filling on top. Refrigerate.
Makes 2 pies.

title: enchiladas
directions: Soften tortillas
in grease.
Drain.
Place cheese and onions on tortilla.
Roll and place in baking dish or 9 x 13-inch pan. Heat chili and enchilada sauce until blended. Pour over tortillas. Top with rest of cheese (and onion if wanted).
Cover and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: macaroni pie
directions: Cook macaroni (al dente) and drain.
Return to pan.
Scramble 1 dozen eggs in bowl.
Pour into pan with macaroni.
Add the cheese, oil, salt and pepper and mix.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch glass dish (if there are leftovers, pour that into another small glass dish).
Bake at 350° for about 35 minutes until golden brown.

title: catherine's corn bread
directions: Mix corn meal, flour, salt and sugar together.
Pour boiling water over; beat well.
Make sure lumps are out.
Then add eggs, milk and butter.
Mix well.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour.

title: sugar cookies
directions: *How to make buttermilk:
Put 1 tablespoon vinegar in cup and fill cup with milk (1 cup).

title: hamburger hash
directions: Peel potatoes and dice into small pieces; fry on medium heat in a large frypan . In another pan, fry ground beef and season.
When potatoes are cooked, add the beef; stir in well.
Slowly add cheese (let melt before you add another handful).
Stir after each handful.
Cover and let stand a couple of minutes.
Serves 5 to 6.

title: shrimp pasta salad with dill dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients and add enough mayonnaise (Kraft Free) to get the right consistency.
I add extra dill seasoning and a little dill pickle juice to thin it sometimes.

title: double rich m&m's chocolate cookies
directions: Roll in balls.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Press slightly flat.
Bake in a 300° oven for 8 to 12 minutes.
Do not overbake.

title: scalloped potatoes supreme
directions: In a large rectangular dish (glass), 8 x 10-inches.
Spray, with Mazola or Pam, sides and bottom of dish lightly.
Mix cream of mushroom soup, celery soup and 1/2 cup milk together in small pouring bowl.

Mix celery and onion, cut up in another bowl. Layer 1st layer of sliced potatoes in dish followed by a sprinkle of salt and pepper, then a layer of celery and onion, followed by a portion of the mushroom and celery soup mixture.
Continue these layers until all potatoes and other ingredients are used up. Place in oven at 350° for 45 minutes.
Stir potatoes gently several times during the baking.
After the 45 minutes, add 1 cup grated Cheddar cheese and bake about 10 minutes more or until potatoes are done.
The timed may vary according to size of your potato slices.
Enjoy!

title: christmas pickles
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients well; pour over gallon jar full of washed, whole cucumbers.
Finish filling jar with water.
Seal; let stand until December.
Remove cucumbers from jars and rinse them.
Throw away the brine.
Slice cucumbers; put into canning jars.
Mix the sugar and water; pour over cucumbers in jars.
They are ready to be eaten the next day.
Do not refrigerate after opening.

title: soft and chewy peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream together the shortening, peanut butter and sugar, then add eggs and vanilla.
Add remaining dry ingredients and blend well.
Drop by spoonful and flatten slightly on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.
Makes 6 dozen.

title: hershey bar pie
directions: Combine marshmallows, chocolate bars and milk in top of double boiler.
Heat over hot water (not boiling) until melted.
Cool. Fold into whipped cream.
Pour into crust.
Set in refrigerator at least 2 hours.
Good made the day before.

title: black midnight devil's food
directions: Combine cocoa and hot water.
Add to creamed shortening, sugar and eggs alternately with dry ingredients.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Beat ingredients on medium speed with electric mixer until smooth.
Grease and flour 2 loaf pans.
Fill 1/2 full.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: pumpkin cheesecake
directions: Mix all of the above. Reserve 1/2 cup of the above and add 1/2 cup pumpkin. Add about 1/4 teaspoon spices (nutmeg, cinnamon, ginger, cloves). Pour first mixture into pie crust. Pour second mixture on top. Spread over mixture. Bake at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: oven beef stew
directions: Combine in Dutch oven with cover and bake at 300°, covered, 3 to 4 hours, until tender.

title: cold oriental noodle salad
directions: Mix spaghetti, walnuts, scallions and chicken in large bowl.

title: pumpkin roll
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Cream eggs until light and fluffy. Gradually add sugar, pumpkin and lemon juice.
Fold in flour, baking powder and cinnamon.
Pour into well-greased jelly pan lined with wax paper (size 15 x 10 x 1-inch).
Sprinkle top with 1 cup finely chopped nuts.
Bake 15 minutes at 375°.
Quickly loosen sides with knife and turn onto a thin towel.
Sprinkle with lots of 10x sugar.
Roll from narrow side with towel and let cool.
When cool, unroll to spread with cream mixture.
Pumpkin roll freezes well.

title: rolled filled cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill until firm.
Roll out dough and cut into 2 or 3-inch circles.
Fill with Raisin Filling.

title: gran's pickled beets
directions: Place beets (either whole, sliced or quartered) in pint jars. Bring first 3 ingredients to a boil and pour over beets to cover. Seal and place in a hot water bath for 10 minutes.

title: yummy caramel bars
directions: Mix together cake mix, 1 egg and butter.
Press into 9 x 13 greased pan.
This will form the crust.

title: fried onions
directions: Select 3 large onions, peel and slice.
Place slices in cold water for 2 hours.
Prepare the batter, mixing egg and 1 tablespoon flour.
Then add salt and enough milk to obtain a solid batter.
Remove onion slices from water, dry and dip into batter. Then fry in plenty of boiling oil, adding salt when finished. Serves 4.

title: barbecued bourbon pork chops
directions: Heat oil in heavy medium saucepan over medium heat.
Add onion and saute until begin to soften.
Add thyme and saute about 1 minute.
Add bourbon and simmer until liquid is reduced to a glaze; add barbecue sauce.
Season chops with salt and pepper; grill 5 minutes per side.
Brush with sauce.
Continue grilling until done. Grilling time is about 20 minutes.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: In Pyrex dish, slice up a layer of potatoes and a layer of onions; sprinkle with salt.
Add another layer of potatoes and a layer of onions.
Lay pork chops on top.
Mix soups and water. Pour over pork chops.
Bake 1 hour at 350° or until done.

title: hot cuban black bean dip
directions: Combine all ingredients together in food processor until blended together well. Microwave for 3 to 4 minutes. Let sit for 2 minutes and serve with tortillas. Serve with tortilla chips.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Saute onions in margarine.
Stir in flour.
Add soup and water; stir until bubbly and thickened.
Add chicken and vegetables and heat thoroughly.
Place 1 crust in bottom of pie pan; add chicken/vegetable mixture.
Top with second crust.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes or until browned.

title: spoon rolls
directions: Place yeast in 2 cups water.
Melt oleo, then mix all ingredients.
Place by spoon into greased muffin tins. Bake at 350° until slightly brown.
Place rest of dough in airtight bowl and place in refrigerator.
Will keep several days.

title: yellow squash casserole
directions: Boil squash until tender; drain and mash.
Chop onion, saute in half the margarine until tender.
Add soup, pimento, sour cream, salt and pepper.
Melt remaining butter and add to dressing crumbs.

title: date cake
directions: Add water to dates and let stand.
Cream shortening and sugar; add egg and mix well.
Add dates, water and chopped nuts.
Add dry ingredients and vanilla.
Mix well.
Bake in 2 (8-inch) round greased and floured pans.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes. This was "the birthday cake."

title: white chocolate fudge
directions: Mix sugar,
oleo and milk in a heavy saucepan and bring to a full,
rolling
boil.
Cook for 5 minutes, stirring constantly. Add the 1/2 pound of white chocolate, which has been melted in
a double
boiler.
Add
marshmallows,
vanilla and nuts.
Beat
to a spreading consistency.
Pour into a greased pan or glass dish (Pyrex).
Freezes and mails well.

title: carrot cake
directions: Combine butter, cheese and vanilla.
Cream well.
Add sugar gradually, beating well.

title: kimchee squid
directions: Cut
squids
in
half;	clean and take off skin.
Slice squids about
inch
lengthwise.
Wash	about
5 times with Hawaiian salt;
squeeze and drain.
Pour light white vinegar; wash and drain for 15 minutes.
Mix with kimchee sauce made to your taste. Serves 6 to 8.

title: sweet potato dish
directions: Mix with a beater.
Pour in a casserole dish.
Bake one hour at 375°.
Let sit a few minutes before serving.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Combine eggs and pumpkin.
Blend in sugars, salt and spice. Add milk and mix well.
Divide and pour into 2 pie crusts.
Bake for 50 minutes at 400°.
Bake until knife inserted halfway between center and outer edge comes out clean.
Cool.

title: stuffed cabbage
directions: Saute onion in butter.
Mix together.
Roll in cabbage.
Cook 2 hours.
Pour canned tomato soup and 1 cup of water over top.

title: chicken and shrimp saute
directions: In a large skillet or wok, melt margarine.
Place sliced chicken breast in, cooking on medium-high heat; cook until tender. Lower heat to medium and place soy sauce, garlic and shrimp in with chicken and stir gently.
Turn shrimp once; then add white wine and remaining ingredients, cooking only 4 to 5 minutes.
When shrimp is pink, serve over warmed rice with butter wine sauce. Serves 2 to 3 people.

title: lemon bread
directions: Take juice of 2 lemons, plus 1/2 cup sugar, and mix together and set aside.

title: celery seed dressing
directions: Mix and shake well each time before using.

title: french vanilla custard pie
directions: Beat eggs; add sugar, vanilla and salt.
Stir in the scalded milk.
Pour into pastry shell.
Sprinkle with nutmeg.
Bake in moderate (350°) oven for 35 to 40 minutes.
Cool on rack.

title: pie crust
directions: Makes two 9-inch pie crusts.

title: fruit bars
directions: Pour in greased 9-inch pan.
Chill until set.
Cut in squares.

title: new orleans dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients in a screw-top jar.
Shake vigorously. Rub bowl with clove of garlic before tossing green salad with dressing.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix all dry ingredients together, then add eggs, onion and milk.
You may need more or less milk to make it the right consistency.
Spoon a small amount into hot fish grease.
Dip spoon in water to make dough drop easier.
Cook until golden brown and take up.

title: pepper pie
directions: Place sliced jalapeno peppers in the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Combine cheeses together and spread on top of peppers.
Beat eggs and pour over cheese.
Bake at 350° for approximately 15 to 20 minutes.
Pie is done when edges are lightly brown and eggs are done in center of pie.

title: bread pudding
directions: Put bread in a buttered dish and sprinkle with raisins (optional).
In a bowl, beat eggs, sugar and salt.
Scald milk and add to sugar and egg mixture.
Add vanilla and pour over bread. Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: italian herbed oatmeal focaccia
directions: Lightly spray a 13 x 9 inch baking pan with cooking spray; dust with cornmeal.
In large bowl, combine 1 cup flour, oats, 1 tablespoon Italian seasoning, yeast, sugar and 1 teaspoon garlic salt; mix well.
In small saucepan, heat water and 1/4 cup olive oil until very warm (120°F. to 130°F.).
Add to flour mixture; mix well. Gradually stir in enough remaining flour to make a soft dough. Turn dough out onto lightly floured surface.
Knead 8 to 10 minutes or until smooth and elastic.
Cover; let rest 10 minutes. Pat dough into pan, pressing dough out to edges of pan. Using fingertips, poke indentations over surface of dough.
Brush dough with remaining 2 tablespoons oil.
Sprinkle with remaining 1 tablespoon Italian seasoning and 1/2 teaspoon garlic salt. Arrange dried tomatoes across top; sprinkle with cheese.
Cover; let rise in warm place 30 minutes or until doubled in size.
Heat oven to 400°. Bake 25-30 minutes or until golden brown.
Cut into strips or squares.
Serve warm.
12 servings.

title: fudge frosting
directions: Combine brown sugar, cocoa, butter crisco, salt and milk in saucepan. Boil for 3 minutes. Add vanilla and confectioners sugar. Mix well. Frost cake while still warm.

title: mexican cheese dip
directions: Put in crock-pot and mix thoroughly.
Keep warm and serve with nachos.

title: zesty salsa corn
directions: Cook corn according to package directions. Stir in salsa and olives. Cook until hot.

title: refrigerator casserole
directions: Brown the hamburger and onion; drain.
Mix all ingredients together.
Layer mixture with cheese in a casserole dish.
Top off with cheese.
Place biscuits on top.
Bake according to directions on biscuit can.
Ingredients may differ depending on what leftovers are in your refrigerator.

title: turkey casserole
directions: Combine turkey, 1 cup of the grated cheese, pimentos, soup, onions and noodles.
Pour into a greased casserole dish.
Spread remaining cheese on top.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes.
This can be frozen before baking.

title: cornbread
directions: Preheat oven to 400°. Combine in a mixing bowl all of the ingredients
listed. Pour in a greased pan and cook for about 20 minutes or until a toothpick comes out clean.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into a large iron skillet that has been heated with 1 tablespoon oil and sprinkled with cornmeal.
Bake at 400° until brown.
Very good served with homemade vegetable soup.

title: cheese cake
directions: Lay cream cheese out to soften.
Blend cream cheese with milk until light and fluffy.
Add vanilla and lemon juice and mix well. Pour into graham cracker crust.
Chill 3 to 4 hours, until set. Top with pie filling.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix pudding.
Mix 3/4 of whip topping with vanilla pudding. In medium bowl alternate layer of cookies, bananas and pudding and whip topping mixture.
Use remaining whip topping as final layer. Sprinkle wafer crumbs on top as decoration if desired.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Place chicken in bottom of buttered casserole dish.
Add layer of dressing.
Mix soups and water and pour over dressing. Sprinkle poultry seasoning on top.
Bake at 400° until top bubbles through dressing and browns.
Serve with cranberry sauce.

title: impossible buttermilk pie
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease pie plate.
Beat all ingredients until smooth, 30 seconds in a blender on high or 1 minute with mixer.
Pour into pie plate; bake until knife inserted in center comes out clean, about 30 minutes.
Cool 5 minutes.
Serve with mixed fresh fruit if desired.
You won't believe how good this is!

title: cranberry relish
directions: Wash cranberries.
Drain, remove stems.
Chop all fruit coarsely (I use a food processor).
Add sugar, cinnamon and cloves.
Mix well and chill.

title: cherry cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine milk, oil, sugar, eggs and vanilla in a bowl and mix well.
Add flour, baking powder and salt and mix.
Pour into greased and floured pan.
Then spoon cherry pie filling over batter and sprinkle with cinnamon.
Bake for 50 minutes.

title: basque sheepherder's bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in water; add sugar and salt.
Allow to stand about 10 minutes until bubbly.
Add 4 cups flour; beat well.
Stir in enough remaining flour to make stiff dough.
Knead lightly, place in a greased bowl, cover and let rise until doubled.
Punch down, shape into a round ball and place in a 10-inch diameter cast-iron Dutch oven.
Cover with lid and let rise until doubled. Cut into 4 equal pieces and gently form loaves.
Bake in a loaf pan at 375° for 45 minutes.
Cover with foil if it starts getting too brown.
Cool on wire rack.

title: cooked cabbage
directions: Remove outer leaves and core from the cabbage.
Cut in chunks.
Put cabbage in just enough boiling water to keep from scorching.
Add red pepper or olive oil.
Salt to taste.
(If cabbages are not sweet, you may wish to add a bit of sugar.) Do not overcook cabbage.
Serve with cornbread.

title: easy fruit salad
directions: Mix, chill and serve.

title: kamizaze
directions: Shake and serve as a shot or over ice.

title: spanish rice
directions: Coat nonstick frypan with Pam cooking spray.
Add oil.
Saute onion, garlic and rice.
Saute over medium heat 5 to 10 minutes until rice looks pearly or slightly golden.
Add celery, chili powder and remaining liquid.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat to low and cover.
Simmer 25 to 30 minutes until all liquid is absorbed. Serve with tortillas, refried beans, grated cheese and green salad.

title: stuffed french toast
directions: Beat together cream cheese and vanilla until fluffy.
Stir in nuts and set aside.
Cut bread into 10 to 12 slices, 1 1/2-inches thick.
Cut a pocket in top of each.
Fill pocket with 1 1/2 tablespoons of cheese mixture.
Beat together eggs, whipping cream, vanilla and nutmeg.
Using tongs, dip the filled bread slices in egg mixture, being careful not to squeeze.
Cook on lightly greased griddle until both sides are brown.
Keep warm in oven on baking sheets.
Heat preserves and orange juice.
To serve, drizzle mixture over hot French toast.

title: crazy chocolate cake
directions: Stir dry ingredients together.
Put in all liquid.
Stir until mixed.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch baking pan (ungreased).
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until cake springs back when lightly touched with finger.
Cool in pan.

title: cranberry salad
directions: After Jell-O is cooled, add other ingredients and pour into mold.
Refrigerate.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: cocoa fudge
directions: Combine cocoa, sugar and salt in a large saucepan.
Add milk gradually.
Mix thoroughly; bring to a bubbly boil on high heat, stirring continuously.
Reduce heat to medium and continue to boil the mixture without stirring, until it reaches a temperature of 232° or until a small amount of mixture forms a soft ball when dropped in cold water.
Remove from heat.
Add butter and vanilla.

title: lime cucumber pickles
directions: Cover
cucumbers
with	mixture of lime and water.
Let stand overnight.	Next
morning
rinse
well and let stand in plain cold water 2 hours.
(Add ice cubes to make water really cold.) Rinse and drain.	Cover with sugar and vinegar mixture. Tie
spices
in a
clean cloth and add to mixture.	Add salt. Let
set overnight. Next morning, bring to boil and boil hard 35 minutes.
Put in jars and seal.

title: sour cream apple cake
directions: Mix for 4 minutes.
Slice and peel at least 3 apples.
Mix 1 part cinnamon to 2 1/2 parts sugar (e.g. 2 tablespoons cinnamon to 4 1/2 tablespoons sugar).

title: sweet and sour liver
directions: Salt and pepper liver and roll in flour.
Brown in skillet in shortening, turning until all sides are browned.
Add onion to liver.
Mix vinegar, water, sugar and catsup.
Pour over liver. Cover and simmer until onion is tender and liquid is thickened. Serve plain or over rice.

title: cream cheese biscuits
directions: Soften and mix margarine and cream cheese.
Gradually add flour and pepper; mixing well.
Roll out and cut.
Bake at 400° for 12 to 15 minutes, or until golden brown.
Serve with butter and honey.

title: cheese cake
directions: Mix cream cheese, salt
and vanilla until creamy and smooth. Add eggs, mixing well after each egg.
Add 1 c. sugar slowly while mixing.
Put mixture into the graham pie shell.
Bake at 450 degrees until center is jello like.
Remove and cool 10 minutes.

title: apple nut loaf
directions: Combine applesauce and baking soda.
Cream butter and sugar. Stir in egg and spices.
Blend in applesauce mixture.
Mix in flour and nuts.
Pour into greased loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.
Cool on rack.

title: pork chop and rice casserole
directions: Brown chops in a little oil along with onion and pepper. Place rice and 2 cups of water in casserole dish.
Add chops, onion and pepper to rice.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: old fashioned bread pudding
directions: Combine bread and milk in large bowl.
Stir in eggs, salt, sugar, vanilla and nutmeg.
Add raisins.
Pour into buttered baking dish.
Bake in 350° oven for 25 minutes.

title: party snacks
directions: Mix all ingredients, except peanuts. Pour hot oil over mixture and stir well.
Add peanuts and mix again.

title: no-knead rolls
directions: Put 1 c. water in large bowl. Add butter, salt and sugar. Dissolve yeast in 1/2
c. water plus pinch of sugar.
Add to bowl. Beat 1 egg and milk, add to bowl.
Add flour to make stiff batter.
Cover and let rise 15-20 minutes.
Put in greased muffin tins or form rolls.
This recipe makes 12 - 18
rolls and a small loaf (9 x 13 greased pan).
Bake approximately 20 minutes at 375°.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: Place sugar and corn syrup in a 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Cook on High 4 minutes.
Add peanuts and cook 4 1/2 minutes on High (until brown).
Add butter and vanilla.
Cook on High 1 to 2 minutes (1 minute and 15 seconds on larger microwave).
Remove from microwave and add baking soda.
Gently stir with wooden spoon until light and foamy.
Cool on buttered cookie sheet (about 30 minutes).
Break into pieces and place in airtight glass container.

title: peanut butter drop cookies(no bake cookies)
directions: In a large saucepan, mix together the sugar, butter and milk. Bring to a boil.
Take off heat and add remaining ingredients. Drop on wax paper by teaspoonful.
Let stand 1 hour plus longer, if necessary.
Yields 100 cookies.

title: classic pizzelles
directions: Beat eggs, adding sugar gradually.
Add cooked margarine and vanilla or anise.
Sift flour and baking powder.
Blend into egg mixture until smooth. Dough will be sticky enough to be dropped by spoon.
Bake in pizzelle maker.
Makes approximately 60 pizzelles.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°. In small bowl, combine dry ingredients; set aside. In large bowl, beat butter, sugar, brown sugar and vanilla until creamy. Beat in eggs.
Gradually beat in flour mixture. Stir in chocolate chips.
Drop by teaspoon onto ungreased cookie sheet. Bake about 9 minutes. Let cool. Store in covered container to keep soft.

title: zucchini jam
directions: Stir in gelatin.
Ladle boiling jam into jars and seal. Process in boiling water for 5 minutes.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Mix ingredients.
Bake in 3 layers at 300°.

title: sweet potato bake with pecan topping
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Spoon mixture into a 1 1/2-quart oiled casserole dish.

title: burritos
directions: Brown hamburger; drain well.
Add beans and hot taco sauce. Heat well and add grated cheese until melted.
Put mix on white tortillas and serve.
Delicious.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Cook sugar, syrup and water until it forms a soft ball when tried in water (236°).
Add peanuts and cook until mixture is amber colored (294°).
Remove from heat and add soda; stir thoroughly.
Pour on greased tin or dish.
When cool, break into uneven pieces.

title: fig pickles
directions: Put together all ingredients and make syrup by boiling for 5 minutes. Add figs and boil again for 5 minutes. Let stand overnight.

title: spicy parsley sauce
directions: Place the minced onion in a bowl.
Sprinkle onto the onion, the next five ingredients.
Stir, cover with vinegar.
Let stand 1 to 2 hours to blend flavors.
Drain, and discard vinegar.
Add tomatoes and parsley.
Serve with roasted or barbecued meats and fish.

title: zippy potato skins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Thoroughly scrub potatoes with brush under cold water.
Pat them dry.
Prick each potato with fork. Bake 1 hour or until tender.
In small bowl, mix together melted butter and hot pepper sauce; set aside.
Cut each potato in half lengthwise and scoop out pulp using a spoon.
Leave about 1/4-inch thick shell; reserve potato pulp for other use.
Cut each potato shell lengthwise into 1-inch wide strips.
Place potato skin strips on baking sheet.
Broil the potato skins 3 to 4 inches from heat source for about 5 minutes or until crisp or bake in oven at 450° for 12 to 15 minutes, until crisp.
Take out.
Brush with butter mixture.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Put back into oven until cheese melts.
Then pull out.
Sprinkle with crumbled bacon.

title: barbecued fish
directions: Clean fish and place in greased shallow pan.
Brown onion in fat.
Add brown sugar, vinegar, lemon juice, salt, Worcestershire sauce, catsup and water.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Sprinkle fish with salt and pepper and pour sauce over it. Bake at 425° for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° and continue baking 35 to 45 minutes longer.

title: pumpkin tureen
directions: Clean out pumpkin as if making a jack-o-lantern (do not cut face).
Rub interior of pumpkin with butter.
Cut bread into small cubes.
Place all ingredients into pumpkin shell and mix together. Replace top with tinfoil between lid and shell to prevent lid from falling into center of pumpkin.
Place pumpkin in a pie tin or cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 2 hours or until tender (when pierced with a fork).
To serve, scoop deeply from the bottom and sides.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Add eggs one at a time and mix well after each. Pour in greased, floured pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: angel cake
directions: Break angel food cake into bite size pieces.
Soften cream cheese, mix in sugar, milk and Cool Whip.
Add pieces of cake. Pour into dish and top with cherry pie filling or blueberry. Chill.

title: broccoli rice casserole
directions: In saucepan, saute onions in butter.
Add soup and milk. Empty Cheez Whiz in pan.
Add
rice and and broccoli.
Add to the skillet.
It should be soupy.
Cook over medium heat until it bubbles.
Grease casserole and pour in mix.
Add bread crumbs on top.
Bake 350° for 45 -60 mins.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Beat in eggs and flavorings. Stir in bananas.
Add dry ingredients; mix well.
Stir in nuts. Pour into a well-greased loaf pan.
Bake in a 300° oven 45 minutes.

title: ozark apple cake
directions: In a large bowl, combine oil, sugar, eggs and vanilla; blend well.
Add in order diced apples, chopped pecans, golden raisins, flour, salt and soda.
Blend well.
Pour into
a tube cake pan that has been pre-sprayed with no-stick cooking spray.
Bake in 350° preheated oven about 1 hour.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together; beat with electric mixer until smooth. Pour into greased casserole dish. Add topping. Bake at 325 degrees for 25-30 minutes.

title: dump cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spread pie filling evenly in bottom of greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Arrange undrained pineapple over cherry filling.
Sprinkle cake mix over pineapple.
Cover with melted margarine and top with nuts and coconut.
Bake 1 hour or until done.
Serve hot or cold.

title: old fashioned gingerbread
directions: First sift flour, then measure.
Then sift three times with baking soda, salt and spices.
Next, cream the shortening until it is light and fluffy.
Add sugar gradually, beating after each addition.
Add well beaten egg and molasses.
Beat until smooth. Next, add sifted dry ingredients and mix thoroughly.
Add hot water and stir until smooth.
Turn into well-greased and floured 8 x 14-inch pan.
Bake at 325° for 35 minutes or more.
Check to see if done.

title: blueberry coffee cake
directions: Cream shortening; add sugar, then egg and beat well.
Stir in sifted dry ingredients and milk alternately.
Blend in blueberries.
Put into greased 13 1/2 x 11-inch pan.
Sprinkle topping over batter and bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: fluffy orange pie
directions: Combine crumbs and margarine.
Press into a 9-inch pie plate. Chill.
In large bowl, beat cream cheese until fluffy; gradually beat in milk, then juice concentrate until smooth.
Fold in whipped cream.
Pile into crust.
Chill 2 hours.
Garnish as desired.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: pineapple cheese ball
directions: Drain pineapple (squeeze to get all juice out).
Let cream cheese soften.
Combine all ingredients except nuts.
Shape into ball.
Roll in crushed nuts.
Refrigerate.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Mix eggs with salt, dry mustard and half and half.
Remove crust and cube buttered bread.
Place bread cubes and sausage in casserole dish.
Pour egg mixture over bread and sausage.
Let sit 8 hours.
Cook 35 to 45 minutes at 350°.
Top with grated cheese.

title: quick nut fudge
directions: Combine all ingredients except nuts in top of double boiler. Place over simmering water; stir until smooth. Add nuts and mix. Spread quickly into 9 x 5 pan. Cool and cut.

title: patra's chocolate torte
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients together; pat into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
(Reserve about 1/2 cup for topping.)
Melt chips in microwave.
Add sugar and water.
Stir in egg yolks.
Let cool. Beat egg whites until stiff; add to cooled mixture.
Add whipped cream to mixture; fold all together.
Pour over crust; sprinkle with remaining crumbs.

title: mango bread(by dr. kang)
directions: Mix in order given.
Grease and flour loaf pans.
Pour into loaf pan and let stand 20 minutes.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until knife inserted into loaf comes out clean.
(Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan for 45 minutes.)

title: picnic bean salad
directions: Combine beans, celery, green pepper, molasses and dressing in a large bowl.
Toss to blend thoroughly.
Chill before serving.

title: mom's fresh apple pie(warren jr.'s favorite)
directions: Peel and slice apples and put into pie shells.
Sprinkle with sugar, flour, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Dot with slices of butter or margarine.
Put top crusts on and pinch edges closed.
Make four 1-inch slits in top crusts.
Bake at 400° for 40 minutes.
Makes 2 pies.

title: brownies
directions: Mix eggs and sugar.
Add melted chocolate and butter. Add vanilla, salt, flour and nuts.
Pour into buttered 13 x 9 x 2-inch dish and bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix everything, except corn flakes and melted margarine in a 2-quart casserole.
Mix corn flakes and margarine.
Sprinkle on top of casserole.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: hershey bar cake
directions: Melt chocolate bars in the chocolate syrup in double boiler. Cream sugar and margarine.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add melted chocolate, then flour and milk alternately.
Bake 1 1/2 hours in a tube pan or Bundt pan, which has been lightly greased and floured, at 300°.
Test with toothpick to determine when done.
Use chocolate icing or lightly sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: pralines
directions: Combine sugar, soda, salt, buttermilk and syrup; bring to a boil, then cook over medium heat, stirring often until mixture reaches soft ball stage (234°).
Remove from heat.
Add butter, vanilla and pecans.
Stir until mixture loses its gloss and can be dropped easily from a spoon on a well buttered piece of wax paper.
If mixture becomes thick, heat a few minutes and continue to drop.

title: chili and rice
directions: Brown beef in oil.
Stir in chili mix.
Add instant rice, tomato paste and hot water.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 10 minutes.
Serves 3 or 4.

title: beryan from isfahan(meat pancake)
directions: Combine the ribs, salt, pepper, water and cinnamon.
Cook for 2 hours.
Separate all the meat off the bones.
Chop the meat in a food processor.
Add oil and 1/2 teaspoon cinnamon.

title: chocolate pizza
directions: Roll cookie dough out on a round pizza pan or pizza stone. Bake as directed on pkg. but do not over bake.
(Cookie should still be slightly soft in the middle.)
Allow cookies to cool completely.
Melt chocolate chips.
Combine melted chocolate chips and cream cheese, then spread over cookie.
Slice bananas and strawberries and arrange on top.
Sprinkle with almonds and serve.

title: fettucine with ham
directions: In saucepan, melt 3 tablespoons butter.
Saute garlic briefly. Add green onions and mushrooms and continue to saute.
Add ham and cook briefly.
Remove from heat and set aside.
Over low heat, melt remaining butter, don't brown.
Add noodles and toss. Sprinkle with cheeses.
Toss until melted.
Add half and half. Heat over medium heat just until hot.
Sprinkle with ground pepper.
Add ham mixture.
Toss and serve immediately.

title: spice cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients well in a large bowl.
Spoon dough on greased baking sheet.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes or until golden brown.

title: fried squash
directions: Slice squash in 1/4-inch slices. Roll in mixture of flour and salt and pepper. Place in skillet with hot grease. Turn when brown. Take out when other side is brown. Salt to taste when frying. Place on paper towels to drain. May need to salt again before serving. Serve hot.

title: no bake pineapple whipped cream cake
directions: Separate ladyfingers into single layers.
There are 12 in a package and this will give you 24 halves when separated into single layers.
Line the sides and bottom of a 9 or 10-inch spring-form pan with some of the ladyfingers; press them in firmly.
Set the pan aside.
Whip the cream stiff.

title: lemon pie
directions: Mix together.
Fold in 1/2 cup whipped whipping cream.
Pour into a graham cracker crust.
Top with remaining whipped cream.

title: chocolate cake(all measurements level)
directions: Mix together flour, sugar, Crisco, milk, salt and cocoa.
Stir in baking soda, baking powder, sour milk, eggs and vanilla.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: rice-a-roni salad
directions: Mix and chill.
Add pimento for color, if desired.

title: turkey giblet-pecan stuffing
directions: Saute onion, celery and green pepper.
Add sausage.
Combine turkey gizzards, turkey necks and turkey livers.
Gradually add bread crumbs with enough turkey broth to moisten the stuffing. Add seasonings and butter.
Add crushed pecan followed by mushroom gravy.
Mix thoroughly.
Place in casserole dish and place in oven at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: fresh peach pie
directions: Sift together 1 1/2 cups sugar with 3 tablespoons flour. Beat 3 eggs well, add dry ingredients and 1 teaspoon of vanilla. Place peaches in pie shell, slice butter over peaches; top with other ingredients. Bake at 450 degrees for 10 minutes reduce heat to 350 and continue to bake for 1 hour.

title: ann's orange gelatin salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in water.
Stir in sherbet until melted.
Add fruit and nuts.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Chill.

title: veggie pizza
directions: Press crescent rolls into a jelly roll pan and make sure all perforations are pressed together.
Bake.
Mix next three ingredients and spread over rolls.
Sprinkle finely chopped carrots, broccoli and cauliflower onto top and refrigerate until serving.

title: 3-bean casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and drain excess oil.
Set aside.
In large crock-pot, place remaining ingredients and stir thoroughly.
Place ground beef in mixture, stir and cook on high 3 1/2 to 4 hours. This dish is great with any meal or with hamburgers.

title: cheese ball
directions: Cream the cream cheese in mixer, then add the other ingredients.
Form into a ball and cover with chopped pecans. Serve on assorted crackers.

title: gina's lemon pepper chicken on spinach salad
directions: Prepare salad and refrigerate, except for the cheese.
Heat oil; add chicken.
Let it cook until almost done.
Start covering with lemon pepper and cook until brown.
Spoon chicken over salad; sprinkle with cheese.

title: nuts and bolts candy
directions: Bring sugar, syrup and butter to a boil; boil 1 minute.
Stir in peanut butter and vanilla.
Add both kinds of cereal.
Mix well and press into flat, greased pan.
Let cool.
Cut into squares.

title: green bean casserole(2 servings)
directions: In 8 or 9-inch glass pie plate, microwave margarine on High 15 to 30 seconds or until melted.
Add wheat germ, oats, Italian seasoning and garlic powder; mix well.
Microwave on High 2 to 3 minutes or until golden brown, stirring after every minute.
Remove mixture from pie plate; set aside.
In same pie plate, combine the mushrooms and onion.
Microwave on High 3 to 4 minutes, stirring after 2 minutes.
Stir in combined yogurt and cornstarch, coating vegetables thoroughly.
Microwave on High 1 1/2 to 2 1/2 minutes or until sauce is slightly thickened; stir.
Sprinkle with reserved wheat germ mixture.

title: bagogi(oriental marinated steak)
directions: Slice meat very thin across grain.
(Best when meat is frozen.)
Combine soy sauce, green onions, garlic, sugar, sake, sesame seed and sesame oil in a large shallow dish.
Add meat, coat well.
Let stand at room temperature for 15 minutes or overnight in refrigerator.
Take meat slices, cook on grill. Serve with cooked rice.

title: gourmet pork chops
directions: Put salt, pepper and flour in a bag.
Put in chops and shake, brown in skillet in hot shortening.
Put chops in baking dish. Combine soup, water, ginger and rosemary.
Pour over chops. Sprinkle with half the onion rings.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Uncover, sprinkle with remaining onions. Bake 10 minutes more.
Blend sour cream into gravy.

title: chocolate almond zucchini bread
directions: Sift together the first 6 ingredients; set aside.
To sifted ingredients, add cup of almonds.
In medium bowl, mix oil, vanilla and eggs until well blended.
Stir in melted chocolate until well mixed.
Add zucchini; mix with dry ingredients, stirring just until moistened.
Pour into greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours, or until toothpick comes out clean.
Cool in pan for 10 minutes.
Place on rack to finish cooling.
Makes one large loaf.

title: danny's goulash
directions: Place ground beef in skillet.
Salt and pepper.
Then add chopped onion.
Brown, then drain well.
Add spaghetti sauce and can of tomatoes to hamburger mix.
Let simmer on low heat for 20 minutes.

title: surprise sweet potatoes
directions: Mix together sweet potatoes, 3 tablespoons melted oleo, cinnamon, salt and evaporated milk.
Stir in raisins.
Pour into 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Combine corn flake crumbs and
4 tablespoons oleo and spread over top of potato mixture.
Bake at 350°
for 40 minutes, or until top is slightly browned.
Serve hot.
Makes 6 servings.

title: basil grilled chicken
directions: Rub coarsely ground pepper into chicken.
Combine 1/3 cup melted butter and 1/4 cup basil.
Stir well.
Brush half of the butter mixture over chicken.
Place chicken on grill over medium coals.
Cover and grill 15 or 20 minutes, turning chicken and basting frequently with remaining butter mixture.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Saute onions in margarine until tender.
Mix all ingredients (except cheese).

title: sweet potato bake
directions: Place
sweet
potatoes
and
enough water to cover in a large saucepan
or Dutch oven.
Cover and cook for 25 minutes or
just until
tender.
Drain; cool slightly and peel.
In a large
bowl mash potatoes.
Stir in butter, sugar and raisins. Place
in a 2-quart baking dish, sprinkle with nuts and marshmallows.
Bake, uncovered,
at
for 30 minutes or until heated
through
and marshmallows begin to brown.
Yields 8 to 10 servings.

title: sweet italian spaghetti salad
directions: Cook spaghetti. Rinse in cold water and drain. Add all ingredients and toss well.

title: cheese cone
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Chill and shape into ball.
Roll in finely chopped nuts.

title: italian barbecue
directions: Fry sausage until brown.
Remove from pan.
Fry steaks until brown and shred.
Brown onions and peppers.
When all this is cooked, add remaining ingredients.
Simmer for 1 hour.
Serve on hard rolls.

title: t. v. mix
directions: Mix garlic salt, oil, Tabasco sauce, melted butter and celery salt.
Mix cereals and nuts with other ingredients.
Heat in 200° oven for 1 1/2 hours.
Take out and toss every 30 minutes.

title: soda-cornstarch clay
directions: Cook and stir over medium heat all ingredients for 4 minutes. Cover with a damp cloth and let cool. Knead.
Add food coloring, if desired.

title: white chili
directions: Place rinsed beans in heavy large pot.
Add enough cold water to cover by 3 inches to soak overnight.
Place chicken in heavy saucepan.
Add cold water to cover; bring to simmer.
Cook until tender, about 15 minutes.
Drain and cool.
Remove skin; cut into cubes.
Drain beans.
Heat olive oil in same pot over medium high heat.
Add onions; saute until translucent, about 10 minutes. Stir in garlic, chilies, cumin, oregano and cayenne to saute 2 minutes.
Add beans and stock; bring to boil.
Reduce heat to simmer, uncovered, until beans are very tender.
Stir occasionally for about 2 hours.
(Can be prepared one day ahead of time. Cover to refrigerate; bring to simmer before continuing.)

title: old fashioned coconut pie
directions: Mix ingredients in order and pour into uncooked pie shell. Bake at 350° until set, 30 minutes, sometimes a little longer.

title: beef pot roast(good)
directions: Wash and pat dry with paper towel.
Line iron Dutch oven with heavy foil, doubled enough to wrap and seal around roast.
Cover roast with onion soup mix, salt and pepper, rubbing seasoning into meat, cutting (slicing) into top of roast.
Place on foil with 1/2 can of mushroom soup on foil, bottom of roast.
Spread the other half over top of roast.
Wrap and seal foil over roast.
Place top on Dutch oven . Bake at 300° 1 hour for each pound of meat.
Makes good roast and gravy all in one.
Also a good way to roast chicken.

title: chicken spectacular
directions: Cook rice in chicken broth.
Grate American cheese, making 3 cups of grated cheese.
Chop onion and water chestnuts.
Drain green beans, then combine all ingredients and mix together.
Heat and serve.

title: carrot salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Let stand in refrigerator until mixture begins to thicken.
Stir in other ingredients and dip into individual molds.
Return to refrigerator to chill. Yields 6 servings.

title: vanilla pudding and fruit dessert
directions: Prepare pudding as directed.
If using cooked, let cool. Drain pineapple and fruit cocktail.
Pour in large bowl and add remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Chill and serve.

title: 3 package party rolls
directions: Cook until onion is tender in regular oven.
Layer bottom rolls with ham and cheese.
Top layer, put mixture.
Put together.
Bake in package.

title: butter cookies
directions: Make into balls and press with a glass dipped in sugar.
Bake at 350° for 12 or 15 minutes, until lightly brown on bottom.

title: oh dolly bars
directions: Melt oleo in 8 x 8-inch baking dish.
Add a layer of crumbs, then chips, then coconut, then pecans.
Repeat layering.
Then pour milk on top.
Bake at 350° until milk is absorbed, about 20 to 25 minutes.

title: neiman-marcus cake
directions: Combine cake mix, butter and 2 eggs.
Press into 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Combine cream cheese, 2 eggs and powdered sugar.
Mix well and spread over top of first mixture.
Do not mix the two mixtures together!
Bake at 350° until lightly brown, about 30 minutes.

title: ground sirloin beef balls
directions: Mix all ingredients except soup until well blended.
Roll in balls the size you wish.
Bake 15 to 30 minutes.
When done, pour off grease.
Dribble cream of mushroom soup over meatballs and serve.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Mix all the ingredients with an electric mixer.
Pour into two (2) unbaked pie shells.
Makes 2 pies.
Bake 10 minutes at 450°, then about 30 minutes at 350°.

title: escalloped corn
directions: Spray or grease 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Mix all ingredients and pour into pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: lasagne
directions: Brown meat slowly; spoon off excess fat.
Add next 6 ingredients.
Cook in crock-pot (high 1/2 day or low all day), or cover and simmer 40 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Salt to taste. Cook noodles until tender, drain and rinse in cold water.
Place a layer of noodles, sauce mix, Ricotta cheese, Mozzarella cheese, then another layer of noodles (Mozzarella cheese, if any left) and rest of sauce.
Sprinkle Parmesan cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes (depending on oven, could take longer).
Let stand 10 to 15 minutes; cut in squares.
Makes 4 to 8 servings.

title: "easy" chili con carne
directions: Brown ground beef, onions and garlic.
Drain excess fat.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well. Cover and simmer for about 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: caramel icing
directions: Boil the brown sugar, regular sugar and milk until firm when dipped in cold water.
Remove from heat and add butter.
Cool until lukewarm.
Beat at medium speed until thick and creamy. Increase to high speed until thick.

title: greek spinach pie
directions: Cook spinach, mix everything into spinach.
Season to taste. Layer phyllo dough and cooked spinach on pan.
Bake in 375° oven for 30 to 40 minutes until brown.

title: lentil soup
directions: In a large kettle, heat oil; add ham, sausage, onions and garlic.
Cook for 5 minutes.
Add celery, tomato, lentils, water, Tabasco and salt.
Cover and cook over low heat for 2 hours.
Add spinach and cook for 10 minutes longer.
Makes 4 quarts.

title: oriental chicken
directions: Cook chicken in oil for 3 to 5 minutes.
In a medium size bowl, combine rest of ingredients except pineapple.
Add to chicken; cover and simmer for 20 minutes.
Add pineapple; cover and simmer for 10 minutes.
Serve over rice.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix all together and pour into a prepared graham cracker crust.

title: french breakfast puffs
directions: Heat oven to 350 degrees.
Mix together 1/2 c. sugar and cinnamon; set aside.
Mix shortening, 1/2 c. sugar and egg. Measure flour by dip-level-pour method.
Mix flour, baking powder, salt and nutmeg; stir into shortening and sugar mixture, alternately with milk.
Fill greased muffin cups 2/3 full.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes, until golden brown.
Remove from oven and immediately roll in melted butter, then the cinnamon sugar mix.

title: chicken-green bean casserole
directions: In a greased pan, layer 1/2 package of the dry dressing, 1/2 of the chicken broth, 1/2 of the chicken, the green beans, the soup mixed with the milk, then the other 1/2 of the chicken and broth.
Top with the other 1/2 of the dressing mix.
Dot with butter or margarine.
Bake for 30 minutes at 400°.

title: pineapple upside-down cake
directions: Combine shortening, salt and vanilla.
Add sugar gradually and cream well.
Add eggs and beat thoroughly.
Add baking powder to flour and sift 3 times.
Add small amount of flour and pineapple juice.
Mix until smooth.
Grease iron skillet with butter. Sprinkle brown sugar over butter.
Arrange pineapple on sugar. Put cherries in center of the slices and pour batter over all. Bake in moderate oven at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Serve upside down with whipped cream.

title: crockpot beef stroganoff
directions: Put steak, soup mix, water or wine, mushroom soup, salt and pepper in crockpot. Cook on high 4-6 hours. Add sour cream, then continue until thoroughly heated. Serve over rice.

title: apple butter
directions: Mix applesauce, sugar and cinnamon drops; heat to boiling. Add Sure-Jell; boil for 3 minutes.
Stir constantly.
Pour into jars and seal.

title: barbara's barbecue ham
directions: Combine first five ingredients and simmer 20 minutes.
Remove all cloves.
Add chipped, chopped ham.
Cook 15 minutes more or until heated through.
Serve on buns.

title: squash relish
directions: Mix squash, onions and salt and let stand overnight.
Next day, drain and run cold water through squash mixture.
Put on stove and add last 7 ingredients and simmer for 30 minutes.
Pack in jars and seal.
Makes 8 quarts.

title: pineapple delight
directions: Bake cake mix according to box directions.
Soften cream cheese and blend with milk until smooth.
Add pudding mix and mix. Stir well-drained pineapple into pudding mixture until pudding thickens.
Spread on top of cooled cake and top with Cool Whip. Let stand a few hours or overnight.

title: strawberry sorbet
directions: In food processor or blender, puree strawberries.
In large saucepan, over medium-high heat, combine strawberry puree with 4 cups water and sugar.
Bring to a boil.
Cook 5 minutes or until sugar dissolves, stirring constantly.
Stir in lemon juice.
Remove from heat.
Cool thoroughly.
Pour mixture into 8-inch pan.
Freeze 3 to 4 hours or until firm.
With spoon, break frozen mixture into chunks.
Transfer to large bowl.
Beat with mixer until smooth. Return to pan and freeze 2 to 3 hours until firm.
Yields 16 servings (88 calories and 0.3 g fat per serving).

title: summer sausage
directions: Mix all ingredients with water and pour over hamburger and mix well.
Make into rolls and wrap in heavy aluminum foil and refrigerate for 24 hours.

title: rice krispie candy
directions: Heat sugar and syrup over medium heat.
Remove from heat and add peanut butter, stirring well.
Pour over Rice Krispies; mix and press into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Melt together chocolate chips and butterscotch chips.
Spread over top of Rice Krispie mixture.
Cut into squares.

title: double berry dessert
directions: Wash and hull berries.
Spoon into sherbet dishes.
Combine remaining ingredients and drizzle over strawberries.

title: instant pudding icing
directions: Cream the shortening.
Add sugar; beat.
Add pudding; beat. Add milk; beat
until smooth.

title: cream cheese danish
directions: Cream the cream cheese and 1 cup sugar together.
Spread 1 package of rolls on the bottom of greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Seal the seams.
Spread the cheese mixture over the roll dough.
Place 2nd pack of rolls over cheese.
Pinch these together also.

title: chocolate crackle tops
directions: Combine cake mix, eggs, water and shortening.
Mix with spoon until well blended.
Shape into balls the size of small walnuts. Roll balls in confectioners sugar.
Place on greased baking sheet and bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes 50 cookies.

title: refreshing lime salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water.
Cool slightly.
Stir in buttermilk; chill until thick.
Fold in pineapple, lemon juice, cottage cheese, nuts, celery and mayonnaise.
Chill.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Boil macaroni and rinse. Mix all ingredients. Set in refrigerator overnight.

title: copper penny carrots
directions: Cook carrots until almost tender.
Add remaining ingredients. Chill.
Keep in refrigerator.

title: cream puff dessert
directions: Melt margarine in water and bring to a boil.
Remove from heat and add flour, stirring until you can form a ball.
Beat eggs into mixture, one at a time.
Spread into greased 9 x 13-inch or equivalent jelly roll pan.
Bake at 400° to 425° for 25 minutes or until brown.
Cool completely.
Beat cream cheese until soft. Gradually add milk and beat until smooth.
Add pudding and beat for 2 minutes.
Spread over cooled puff.
Mix whipped topping according to directions and spread on top of pudding.
Drizzle with chocolate syrup or top with fresh fruit.

title: micro-veggie platter
directions: Arrange veggies on microwaveproof platter in rings.
Lay pepper strips on top in a circle.
Place mushrooms and onions over top.
Sprinkle onion mix evenly over all.
Cover with plastic wrap and microwave on High for about 8 minutes or until done.
Do not add water.
Serve from same dish.

title: cinnamon buns
directions: Combine flour, sugar, salt and cinnamon in a large bowl. Combine egg, water, milk and melted butter.
Add slowly to flour mixture.
Knead for 5 minutes.
Roll and cut into 1-inch slices. Place each slice into greased muffin pan.
Allow to rise to double its size.
Spread butter on each top and bake at 375° for 25 minutes.

title: cool whip pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into graham cracker crust. Chill 1 hour. Enjoy!

title: raisin custard bread pudding
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 1-quart casserole dish.
Put bread and raisins in large mixing bowl.
Add scalded milk; soak 5 minutes.
Add butter, sugar, salt, eggs and vanilla; mix well. Pour into prepared casserole.
Sprinkle with nutmeg.
Put casserole dish in an 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking pan.
Pour 2 cups hot water in pan.
Bake for 60 to 65 minutes, or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Serve warm.
Makes 8 servings.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Press sugar cookie mix into large 10 x 14-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Cool.
Cream together the cream cheese, vanilla and sugar.
Spread onto pastry.
Place fruit onto cream cheese mixture.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli as directed on package; drain.
Mix first 7 ingredients and pour into a baking dish.
Top with crushed cracker crumbs.
Bake for 1 hour or until brown on top in a 350° oven.

title: sweet potato pudding
directions: Mix milk
into	beaten	eggs and add other ingredients. Bake in 300° oven 2 hours.

title: graham cracker squares
directions: Mix ingredients.
Spread in a 9 x 9 x 2-inch greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until squares are golden.
Cool and cut into squares.
Can add 1/2 cup coconut or 1/2 cup peanut butter chips as well.

title: dill pickles
directions: Bring to boil.
Pack pickles in jars as you slice.
Put 1 head of dill in jar.
Pour mixture over pickles and seal.

title: pizza hot dish
directions: Mix together. Top with 8 oz. shredded mozzarella cheese. Bake in a 9 X 13 pan, covered at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: vegetable cheese dip
directions: Thaw and drain broccoli.
Saute celery and onion in butter. Add broccoli, cheese and seasonings.
Serve with dip chips.

title: cheddar top meat loaf
directions: Combine meat, crumbs, 1 cup cheese, 1/2 cup barbecue sauce and remaining ingredients; mix lightly.
Shape into a loaf in shallow baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Brush with remaining barbecue sauce; continue baking for 15 minutes.
Top with remaining cheese.
Serves 8.

title: sweet sour meat loaf
directions: Mix meat and all ingredients together.
Lightly grease baking dish and place meat in pan leaving a little sauce around pan.

title: 24 hour slaw
directions: Combine vinegar, sugar, dry mustard, celery seed and salt in saucepan.
Bring to a boil.
Remove from heat.
Add salad oil. Pour liquid over shredded cabbage and cover tightly.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: bacardi rum pina colada cake
directions: Note:
With vanilla flavor, increase water to 3/4 cup and add 1 cup coconut.

title: chinese beef
directions: Brown onions and celery in small amount of oil; set aside. Brown beef and rice until "grey."
Add onions and celery; mix in soup and water.
Add soy sauce, mushrooms and pepper; mix well. Toss in bean sprouts.
Pour into casserole.
Cook for 30 minutes at 350°, then cook for 30 minutes, uncovered.
Can be made ahead and frozen.
Serves 6 to 8 people.

title: frances' chicken
directions: Line pan with dried beef.
Bone chicken breasts.
Beat together soup and sour cream.
Pour over chicken.
Cover with Reynolds Wrap.
Cook 1 hour.
Uncover.
Cook 1 additional hour.

title: potato-cheese soup
directions: Saute onion and celery.
Add flour, salt and pepper and stir. Mix in 1 cup of water, stirring constantly for 2 minutes (boil is okay), then add potatoes, milk and cheese.
Heat slowly until cheese melts; do not boil.
Garnish with parsley or croutons. Great way to use leftover mashed potatoes.

title: lemony iced tea
directions: In a 2-quart pitcher mix instant tea, lemonade and sugar. Fill with water.
Sugar may be increased or decreased according to taste.

title: peanut butter cups
directions: Mix all ingredients except the chocolate chips.
Shape into balls and set aside.
Melt the chocolate chips in a double boiler. Spoon chocolate into the bottom of mini cupcake pan with liners. Put peanut butter balls in them.
Spoon rest of chocolate on top. Place in freezer until they harden.
Makes 2 1/2 dozen cups.

title: split level brownies
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Cream sugar and shortening. Beat in eggs and vanilla.
Blend in flour mixture.

title: chocolate peanut butter chip cookies
directions: Mix the butter, eggs, sugar and vanilla; add baking soda, salt and flour.
Then add peanut butter chips.
Bake at 350°.

title: cheese dip
directions: Melt cheese in double boiler.
Add slightly drained tomatoes with melted cheese into blender.

title: pickled cucumbers
directions: Sprinkle cucumbers with coarse salt and leave in colander to drain for 1 hour.
Cut each quarter into 1-inch chunks.
Place in a glass jar and cover with vinegar and water (1 part vinegar to 2 parts water).
Season with salt, peppercorns, fennel, clove and bay leaf.
Add onion and garlic.
Cover and refrigerate overnight; best after a few days.
Will keep for a month in the refrigerator.

title: pimento spread
directions: Cube the cheese.
Combine with milk.
Melt over low heat. Stir until smooth.
Cool, but do not chill.
Combine egg, vinegar, sugar and pimento.
Bring to boil over medium heat.
Turn heat to low.
Cook for 6 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Cool.

title: norwegian pie(from 1975 edition)
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients and mix well.
Add rest of ingredients.
Mix well.
This will be stiff and will spread unevenly in two 8-inch pie pans.
Bake for 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.
Serve with Dream Whip.
Put nutmeg in Dream Whip (instead of vanilla) for an unusual flavor.

title: fried rice
directions: Scramble eggs in Magnalite pot.
Remove eggs.
Wilt chopped garlic.
Add meat.
Saute together.
Add cooked rice.
Season with soy sauce until rice is light brown. Add green onions and scrambled eggs.
Sprinkle on Accent and simmer for a few minutes.

title: creamy broccoli dip
directions: Beat all ingredients in a medium bowl.
Serve with fresh vegetables, dippers, or crackers.
Makes 3 1/2 cups.

title: chicken and dressing casserole
directions: Toss stuffing mix with 1/2 Cup chicken broth and beaten eggs. Spread in 11 X 7 1/2 baking dish.
Top with chicken.
Combine remaining 1/2 Cup soup and broth with milk an pimentos.
Pour over chicken and dressing, cover with foil. Bake at 350 for 45 minutes.

title: scotch eggs
directions: Cover eggs with a layer of sausage, sealing egg well.
Roll in crumbs.
Bake in a preheated 350 degree oven for 15-20 minutes, or until golden brown.

title: quick 'n hearty soup(makes 4 servings)
directions: In large heavy pan, over medium-high heat, brown beef and onion until done; drain.
