Drain tomatoes, reserving liquid; chop tomatoes.
Stir water, potato, celery, stewed tomatoes with liquid, steak sauce and salt into pan.
Heat to a boil; reduce heat.
Cover; simmer 25 minutes.

title: green bean salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and marinate with 1 cup sugar, 1/2 cup Wesson oil, 3/4 cup vinegar and 1 tsp. salt.
Leave over night and drain for at least 1 hour.

title: zucchini pie
directions: In a bowl combine hash browns, onion, Parmesan cheese and 1 egg.
Put into a 9-inch pie pan, or 10-inch quiche dish.
Pat the mixture in the bottom and up the sides.
Bake at 400° for 35 minutes.
In large skillet cook zucchini in margarine until crisp-tender.
Arrange on the potato crust.
In small bowl combine 2 eggs, cheese, milk, oregano, salt and pepper.
Pour over zucchini.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: fluffy gelatin salad
directions: Dissolve marshmallows, gelatin and hot water; set aside.
Cream together cream cheese and crushed pineapple.
Blend cream cheese mixture with the marshmallow mixture.
Prepare topping according to package directions.
Fold in gelatin and cheese mixture.
Spray mold with Pam.
Pour into mold and refrigerate until set.
May be made the day before.

title: summer squash
directions: In saucepan, cook squash and onion in boiling salted water for 5 minutes.
Drain.

title: cucumber dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Delicious served with fresh vegetables or chips.

title: delicious corn bread
directions: Beat together egg, buttermilk and honey.
Mix well together all dry ingredients.
Combine all ingredients, including melted butter and mix well.
Spread into an 8-inch buttered square pan and bake at 425° for 20 minutes.
Serve hot with butter and a hunk of Cheddar cheese.

title: pumpkin squares
directions: Combine sugar
and
oil
with
mixer.
Add
pumpkin and eggs, one at a time.
Combine flour, salt, soda, baking powder and cinnamon.
Add
to	pumpkin mixture. Add vanilla and nuts. Pour on a greased
and floured sheet pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Cool 2 to 3 hours before topping.

title: heath bar candy
directions: Melt butter in large pan.
Add sugar, corn syrup and water. Cook to hard crack (300°), stirring occasionally.
Add 1 cup almond bits and stir.
Spread in well-greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Cool.
Turn candy out of 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan onto wax paper.

title: pear salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in pear liquid. (Add enough water to make 1 1/3 cups, if necessary.)
Add cream cheese.
Blend with mixer at low speed.
Chill until slightly thickened.
Add pears and nuts. Fold in Dream Whip.
Place in mold.
Garnish with maraschino cherries.
Chill until set.

title: williamsburg pound cake with cranberry glaze
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Cream butter and sugar.
Beat egg yolks until thick.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Alternately add yolks, whites and flour to the creamed butter and sugar.
Beat until light and smooth.
Pour into a well-greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Bake 1 1/2 hours or until golden brown.
Cool 5 minutes before turning out of the pan onto a cooling rack.
Bring water and sugar to a boil.
Cook 10 minutes.
Add cranberries and cook until skins pop, about 5 minutes.
Remove cranberries with a slotted spoon and reserve as a condiment.
Continue cooking syrup until thickened, about 20 to 25 minutes.
Cool.
Drizzle over cake.

title: turkey fruit salad
directions: Combine turkey, lettuce, grapes, apples and celery in a bowl. Cover and refrigerate for 1 hour.
Add French dressing and toss. Serve sprinkled with sunflower seeds.
Makes 4 servings.

title: apple cake
directions: Fill pie plate (Pyrex) with apples 2/3 full.
Sprinkle 1 tablespoon of sugar and 1 tablespoon of cinnamon over apples. Combine melted butter, sugar, flour, eggs, salt, walnuts and vanilla.
Pour mixture over the apples.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: tomato relish
directions: Blend together and cook for 2 to 3 hours until thick.
Can in hot jars and seal.

title: jayne's breath of death burger bean casserole
directions: Set pork and beans aside.
Combine all other ingredients with cooked and drained beef.
Simmer meat 5 to 10 minutes.
Pour beans into a greased baking dish.
Pour meat mixture over beans. Bake, uncovered, 45 minutes at 350°.
Serves 3 to 4.

title: mother in law breast of chicken saute
directions: Bone chicken and half breasts.
Mix flour, salt and pepper. Dredge breasts in flour.
In butter, brown lightly until tender.

title: beef burgundy
directions: In skillet, brown meat in butter.
Add remaining ingredients except noodles.
Cover; cook over low heat for 1 hour or until tender.
Stir occasionally.
Serve with noodles.
Serves 4.

title: corn pudding
directions: Beat egg yolks; add milk, seasonings, sugar and flour.
Mix well; add green pepper and corn.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites; pour into a greased casserole.
Bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes.

title: mountain dew cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°. Grease and flour (or spray with Pam cooking spray) a Bundt cake pan and put nuts in bottom of pan (if you want nuts). Mix all ingredients together well. Bake at 325° for 50 to 60 minutes. Leave cake in pan and pour glaze over cake.

title: banana-nut cake
directions: Cream butter or shortening, sugar and eggs.
Combine flour, baking soda and baking powder and add to creamed mixture.
Add bananas, sour milk, vanilla and walnuts.
Pour into greased and floured 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes. Cool and frost.

title: cheese potatoes
directions: Place hash browns in a greased 9 x 13-inch dish. Melt remaining ingredients in microwave; pour over potatoes and mix. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: refrigerator pineapple cheesecake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Bring pineapple juice to a boil in a saucepan over medium-high heat and add gelatin. Stir until dissolved. Remove mixture from heat and cool to lukewarm.

title: octoberfest sausage
directions: Brown sausage in butter in 1 1/2-quart pan.
Arrange onion, sauerkraut, apples and potatoes around sausage.
Top with apple juice, salt and pepper to taste.
Cover tightly and simmer over low heat, stirring once, for 30 to 40 minutes or until potatoes test done.
Serve with potato cakes and applesauce.
Serves 6.

title: hot tamales
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Use a heaping tablespoon of mixture.
Shape with fingers on a piece of foil.
Twist ends. Place in seasoned boiling water.
Boil about 12 minutes, then check.
(Season water with red pepper, garlic salt, etc.)

title: seafood spaghetti
directions: Cook onion in margarine until tender.
Add tomatoes, tomato sauce, mushrooms, garlic salt and oregano.
Simmer, uncovered, 20 to 30 minutes or until thickened slightly.
Add shrimp or clams and heat until hot.
Cook spaghetti according to package directions.
Serve sauce over drained spaghetti and top with Parmesan cheese to taste.
Serves 4.

title: lemon orange cake
directions: In
a
mixing
bowl
cream butter, shortening and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Combine dry ingredients.
Add to creamed mixture alternately with buttermilk, beginning and ending with dry ingredients.
Stir
in extracts.
Pour into 3 greased and floured 9-inch
cake
pans.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or
until cake
tests
done.
Cool
for
minutes in pans. Remove from pan and let cool.

title: glazed carrots
directions: Cook carrots approximately 10 minutes or just to boiling.
Mix melted margarine and sugar, pouring over carrots.
Heat just until mixture is combined well.
Serve immediately.

title: banana bread
directions: Combine oil, sugar, eggs, milk and mashed bananas.
Stir in dry ingredients.
Grease two 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pans.
Pour half of batter into each pan.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: barbecue ribs
directions: Choose lean ribs. Can be either pork or beef. Put on grill and cook for 5 minutes. Then start basting ribs every 15 minutes with sauce.

title: maple sour cream frosting
directions: Combine sugars, cornstarch and salt in heavy saucepan. Blend in sour cream and egg yolks.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly until thickened. Remove from heat. Add maple flavoring and butter. Chill until spreading consistency.

title: penna.  dutch eb'l dumplings(apple dumplings)
directions: Sift flour, baking powder and salt together.
Cut in shortening.
Add milk and mix to a smooth dough.
Turn onto a floured surface and divide into 6 portions.
Roll each section large enough to cover one apple.
Place an apple on each piece of pastry.
Mix sugar and cinnamon together.
Fill each core cavity with the cinnamon mixture.
Moisten edges of the pastry, bring over the apple and seal.
Place on a greased baking sheet.
Bake at 350° about 35 minutes or until apples are tender and pastry is light brown.
Serve with warm milk or cream.

title: caramel brownies
directions: Mix cake mix, butter and half of the evaporated milk in bowl and divide in half.
Spread half of mixture in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake for 5 to 6 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken taco rice
directions: Cook pepper strips and chicken until lightly browned.
Add broth, tomato sauce, taco mix and corn.
Bring to a boil.
Stir in rice.
Cover; remove from heat.
Let stand.
Fluff with fork. Serve with cheese, tortilla chips and sour cream.
Also can be used in a tortilla wrap!

title: potato chip cookies
directions: Cream the shortening and sugar. Add eggs, vanilla and beat well. Add flour and soda; mix well. Add chips and nuts; blend. Drop from teaspoon on greased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.

title: citrus spice potpourri
directions: To Dry Peels:
Slice peels into very thin strips.
Place on a cookie sheet and bake in oven on its lowest possible setting. Bake several hours or until dried and hard.

title: turkey breast in crock-pot
directions: Place turkey breast in crock-pot.
Pour Worcestershire sauce over turkey.
Combine seasonings and rub into turkey.
Pour chicken broth into bottom of crock-pot.
Cook on low for 5 to 8 hours or until done.

title: potato cheese soup
directions: Saute celery and onions in butter for five minutes.
Add broth and spices (and potatoes if you are using raw).
Simmer until vegetables are tender.
Stir in half and half.
Add cheese and stir until melted.
Makes 2 quarts.
If you want a smoother soup, put ingredients in blender before you add half and half and cheese.

title: hampton roads deviled crabs
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake in a well-greased casserole until golden brown.
This may be made into cakes or fill crab shells and bake at 375°, until brown.

title: fruit dessert
directions: Drain mandarin oranges well; mix all ingredients together. Chill and serve.

title: five hour beef stew
directions: Layer in order given in ovenproof casserole dish.
Cover and bake at 250° for 5 hours.
Don't peek.
Serve with salad and bread.

title: hobo stew
directions: Start a
small	fire.
Wash and slice potato, onion and carrot.
Place
all
ingredients
in the foil and seal.
Throw (place carefully)
in
the	fire.
Check
in about 20 minutes, depending on how
hot the fire is and how hungry the boys are. If it fails, have a jar of peanut butter and bread.

title: biscuits
directions: Bake at 400° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Brown beef, onions, celery and green pepper.
Drain off grease.
Add
remaining
ingredients
and cook 5 more minutes. Spoon onto buns.
Makes 6 to 8 Sloppy Joes.

title: chicken soup(yield:  2 quarts)
directions: Place chicken in a heavy 6-quart pot; cover with water and lid.
Cook over medium-high heat until water comes to a boil. Remove lid and simmer for about 30 minutes, skimming off foam as it rises with a slotted spoon.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer, partially covered, 1 to 1 1/2 hours longer until chicken is very tender and falls off the bones.
Cool in broth until chicken can be handled.
Remove chicken; discard skin and bones (save meat for salad or casserole).
Strain liquid.
Puree vegetables in food processor or blender and return to soup.
Serve with rice or noodles.

title: hardee's biscuits
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Do not knead dough, just roll out on floured board and cut.
Brush top with buttermilk before baking.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.

title: liz's cabbage rolls
directions: Combine all ingredients (except cabbage and soup mixture) and mix well.
Separate each cabbage leaf and place in boiling water until tender, but not too soft as to split.
Place a ball of the meat mixture on each leaf, (the amount of mixture depends on the size of the cabbage leaf) roll up and place in a 9 X 13 glass casserole dish.
Pour the tomato soup mixture over the cabbage rolls.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.

title: great rice
directions: Mix everything except butter and put in casserole.
Put stick of butter in center; cover and bake at 325° for 45 minutes.
Great with fried chicken.
Leftovers are even better warmed up.

title: no bake chocolate butter fluff
directions: Cream softened margarine.
Gradually add sugar. Beat until fluffy.
Add melted chocolate, vanilla and eggs.
Beat with mixer for 3 minutes.
Make graham cracker crust in bottom of pan.
Put a layer of ice cream on the crust.
Spread chocolate sauce on top. Freeze.
Cut when ready to serve.

title: holly farm taters
directions: Wash and slice or quarter unpeeled potatoes.
Mix all ingredients in a shaker bag.
Put potatoes in bag.
Melt margarine in a pan.
Put potatoes in the pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Turn after 1/2 hour of baking.

title: pork chop delight
directions: Brown chops; combine soups and milk.
Place chops and carrots in crock-pot.
Pour soup mixture over all.
Cover and cook on low for 6 to 8 hours.

title: spam casserole
directions: Cook noodles until tender.
Meanwhile, cut up celery and cook until tender.
Saute Spam and green pepper; add to celery.
Mix in cooked eggs and mushroom soup.
Place in lightly greased casserole dish.
Top with bread crumbs and cover.
Bake at 325° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: oyster snack crackers
directions: Combine Ranch dressing with dill and oil.
Pour over crackers. Stir to coat.
Place in a warm 250° oven for 15 to 20 minutes. Stir gently during baking.

title: chicken roll
directions: For each serving, remove breast from bone.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Place strip of cheese and strip of ham on the breast. Roll, pin with toothpick.
Roll in flour, slightly brown in one stick margarine.
Place rolls in baking dish.
Add mushroom soup and 1/2 cup water to margarine.
Heat and pour over chicken rolls. Bake at 300° for 2 hours.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: In a mixing bowl, combine flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
In another bowl, beat eggs.
Blend in milk, butter, nutmeg and vanilla; pour into dry ingredients and mix just until moist. Fold in blueberries.
Fill muffin cups 2/3 full.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Brush tops with melted butter and sprinkle with sugar.
Makes 1 dozen.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Mix flour and sugar together in bowl. Make well in center.
Combine egg, milk and oil.
Add all at once to dry ingredients.
Stir quickly, just until moistened.
Wash and drain blueberries and gently fold into batter.
Fill greased muffin cups 2/3 full.
Bake at 400° for about 25 minutes.
Serves 12.

title: herman cookies
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for about 10 minutes. Frost with chocolate icing if desired.

title: christmas cookies
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add eggs.
Sift dry ingredients and add alternately with sour milk.
Add vanilla and roll out. Use cookie cutters.
Bake at 350° for 6 to 12 minutes.
Let cool and frost with Christmas frosting.

title: chicken cordon bleu
directions: Place the chicken breasts between plastic wrap paper.
Lightly pound or roller pin chicken.
Remove wrap.
In small bowl, combine cheese and ham.
Sprinkle chicken with salt; spread mustard on. Place mixture of ham and cheese in middle of breast.
Roll, jelly roll style, pressing ends to seal.
Cover and refrigerate at least 30 minutes.

title: bacon macaroni salad
directions: Prepare macaroni and cheese as directed on box.
Add remaining ingredients; mix together.
Add additional mayonnaise, if desired. Chill.

title: chocolate drop cookies
directions: Combine sugar, butter and cocoa.
Add milk in saucepan.
Bring to a boil.
Quickly reduce heat to medium and cook 3 to 4 minutes until a ball forms in a glass of cold water when dropped.
Remove from heat.
Stir in quick cooking oats, nuts and vanilla.
Drop by teaspoons on wax paper.

title: yogurt cream cheese
directions: Line a colander with double layer of cheesecloth which is damp.
Gently pour the yogurt into fabric-lined colander. Colander should be suspended in pan large enough to collect whey. Let sit eight hours or overnight.
Save whey for baking bread, cooking rice, etc.

title: remarkable fudge(700 watt microwave)
directions: Total Cooking Time:
9 minutes and 15 seconds.

title: stuffed bell peppers on rice
directions: Cut tops off of green peppers; remove seeds and membrane. Boil water in a deep pan, place peppers in for 5 minutes and cook. Drain.
Soak bread in water to soften.
Squeeze excess water out. Combine meat, bread and next 7 ingredients.
Stuff peppers with meat mixture.
Place in a large, deep baking dish or pan.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour and cocoa. Beat egg yolks with milk until well blended. Add vanilla. Cook in heavy saucepan until thick. Pour in baked pie shell.

title: easy evergreen punch
directions: Mix and serve.
Great for Christmas and St. Patrick's Day!

title: diet french fries
directions: Cut potatoes French-style.
Mix oil and water; pour over potatoes and toss.
Spray large pan with Pam.
Spread potatoes on pan.
Bake 40 minutes at 400°.

title: cheesy bean dip
directions: Mix ingredients (except 1 c. cheddar cheese). Transfer to a 9 X 13 baking dish, coated with nonstick cooking spray. Sprinkle remaining cheese on top. Bake, uncovered at 350 degrees for 20-25 minutes. Serve with tortilla chips.

title: chess pie
directions: Cream butter; blend together sugar and cornstarch and add eggs one at a time.
Beat mixture well; add vanilla.
Pour into pie crust that has been baked 5 minutes in a 450° oven.
Bake in a 350° oven until firm, about 45 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: In greased baking dish, arrange in layers chicken, a mixture of the soup (undiluted), mayonnaise, celery, onion, salt, pepper and the sliced eggs.
Top with some coarsely crumbled potato chips.
Sprinkle with some slivered almonds and a little cooking sherry (if desired).
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.
Serve piping hot on Chinese egg noodles.

title: orange mist
directions: Pour 2 cups of orange juice into an ice cube tray.
Freeze until solid.
Transfer to a plastic bag and have ready for use in freezer.

title: broccoli au gratin
directions: Cook and drain broccoli.
Place broccoli in a greased casserole.
Combine soup and milk; heat.
Add cheese and allow to melt.
Pour sauce over broccoli.
Mix crumbs with oleo and sprinkle over the broccoli and sauce.
Bake until bubbles.

title: teriyaki sauce
directions: Combine ingredients.
Marinate flank steaks (2) for 5 to 7 hours or chicken for 2 to 3 hours.

title: pineapple drink
directions: Put all ingredients in electric blender.
Blend on liquefy or ice breaker for 30 to 45 seconds.
Makes 2 (8-ounce) thick shakes.

title: chicken salad
directions: Mix together and spread on bread or toast.

title: punch
directions: Add enough water to make one gallon.
Can freeze for later use.

title: orange mint tea
directions: Put juice, mint and grated rind in a large pot.
Add enough water to make about 3 quarts and stir; heat until it starts to boil.
Then turn to low heat and simmer for 15 minutes. Add honey to taste.

title: dill crackers
directions: Mix dressing, dill and oil.
Add crackers and mix until dry. Good for snacks.

title: quick apple pie
directions: Cut apples into cubes.
Layer in pie plate.
Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Add water.
Mix sugar, flour and margarine until crumbly.
Sprinkle on top of apples.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: ham and scalloped potatoes in the crock-pot
directions: Layer potatoes, ham, onion and cheese twice.
Spoon soup over top (undiluted). Cook 8 hours on low.
You may add sweet peas or green beans.

title: easy creamy chocolate fudge
directions: Combine over hot, not boiling, water the chocolate morsels and condensed milk.
Stir until morsels are melted and mixture is smooth.
Stir in nuts and vanilla.
Spread evenly into foil lined 8-inch pan.
Chill until firm, about 2 hours.
Cut into squares. Or you may roll each square into a ball and roll in finely chopped nuts.
Makes about 64 (1-inch) squares.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Thicken mixture with cornstarch or flour and water to thicken.
Cook rice as directed on package.
Place in pan and place mixture on top of rice.
Cook 1 hour.

title: barbecue deer meat
directions: Put deer meat in the bottom of a roaster.
Layer vegetables and pepperoni over the meat, then pour barbecue sauce over and bake at 350° until done.

title: raisin-filled cookies
directions: Cream shortening and add sugar gradually.
Beat until light. Add beaten eggs and blend; add vanilla.
Sift dry ingredients and add to creamed mixture.
Chill overnight.

title: elegant scalloped corn
directions: Combine ingredients.
Pour into a greased 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Top with additional buttered cracker crumbs.
Dust with paprika.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: chicken italian
directions: Brown chicken that has been tossed with flour, salt and oregano until done in a small amount of Pam.
Remove.
In pan drippings, cook onion until golden; add cut-up zucchini, tomatoes, lemon juice and zest of lemon.
Add chicken broth; bring to a boil and add basil.
Return chicken to pan and heat until warm.
Good with rice or noodles.

title: easy baked beans
directions: For 4 servings you will need:

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Grease 9 x 12-inch baking dish. Preheat oven to 350°. Tear bread into bite-size pieces and spread in pan. Brown sausage and spoon over bread. Sprinkle with cheese. Beat together remaining ingredients. Pour over mixture in pan.
Bake 40 minutes. Cut into squares.

title: strawberries romanoff
directions: Clean and dry strawberries.
For sauce, mix all ingredients (except strawberries) with a wire whip until blended.
Do not use blender.
Refrigerate.
When ready to serve, pour chilled sauce over chilled strawberries.

title: english toffee dessert
directions: Crush wafers and use half to cover the bottom of a 9 x 12-inch buttered pan.
Cream butter until fluffy.
Gradually add sifted powdered sugar and beat until well mixed.
Add egg yolks, one at a time, beating thoroughly.
Stir in chopped nuts, vanilla and melted chocolate.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Pour into pan and cover with remaining crushed wafers.
Refrigerate for at least 4 hours for butter to set.

title: best ever banana quick bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Spray bottom of loaf pan with nonstick cooking spray.
In a large bowl, combine first 6 ingredients; beat 1 minute at medium speed.
Stir in remaining ingredients, just until dry ingredients are moistened.
Pour batter into prepared pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool 5 minutes; remove from pan.
Yields 1 loaf.

title: crispy won ton
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Place approximately 1 teaspoon of filling on each won ton sheet.
Wet edges of sheet with water and press into triangles or rectangles.
Deep fry in oil until well done (approximately 3 to 4 minutes) or until brown.

title: crumb cake(shoo-fly)
directions: Take out a cup of crumbs for top.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken until tender.
Pick off in small pieces and place in buttered baking dish.
Pour 1/4 cup juice from boiled chicken over this.
Combine soups and sour cream together.
Spread this over chicken.
Sprinkle with croutons and pour another 1/4 to 1/2 cup of chicken broth over top.
Bake at 400° for about 40 minutes.

title: shrimp fried rice
directions: Fry eggs and slice into shreds; cook onion in oil with salt, pepper and peeled shrimp.
Add mushrooms, pea pods and rice.
Mix in soy sauce and sugar.
Mix and fry until done.

title: mostacelli express
directions: Make sauce in large skillet.
Brown hamburger.
Saute onion and pepper until tender.
Drain grease.
Add salt, pepper, basil, oregano, bay leaf, tomato paste, can of tomatoes and 1 cup water. Let simmer 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Cook mostacelli according to directions.
Layer in 13 x 9-inch pan:
mostacelli, cheese (Velveeta) and sauce.
Repeat.
Sprinkle with Parmesan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: cajun boil
directions: Fill stockpot about 1/2 full with water. Squeeze lemons into water and add to water.

Put Zatarain's package in water. Bring to a boil. Add potatoes, celery, onion and bell pepper; cook for 5 to 7 minutes. Then add sausage, corn and okra. Cook for 10 minutes. Add shrimp and mushrooms; cook for 2 minutes.

title: creamy potato cheese soup
directions: Saute butter and onions on low for 10 to 15 minutes in skillet; don't brown.
Add flour to onions and butter, cook 4 to 5 minutes; don't brown.
Mix chicken stock with Potato Buds; use a whip and blend until smooth.
Add stock mixture to roux; mix slowly, using whip.
Cook for 15 to 20 minutes.
Whip in half and half and cook for 10 more minutes.
Do not boil.
Season with broiler spice, basil and Tabasco.
Add 4 cups diced, cooked potatoes.

title: barbecue spareribs
directions: Cut ribs into bite size pieces.
Put all ingredients into oven bag.
Bounce and squish bag until mixed.
Put in pan and cut small slits on top of bag.
Bake 1 1/2 hours in preheated 325° oven. Serve with rice.

title: crab fettuccine
directions: Cook fettuccine according to directions on package.
In saucepan, melt butter. Add garlic, half and half and crab.
Heat for 3 minutes. Add Parmesan cheese and pepper. Stir in fettuccine and serve.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Bake for 35 minutes.

title: good salad
directions: Combine romaine, leaf lettuce, onions and celery. Refrigerate.
Saute Ramen noodles in a little oil.
Bake almonds in 350° oven until golden, set aside.
Mix oil, vinegar and sugar. Set aside.
When ready to serve; toss dressing with greens and add nuts and noodles.

title: 3-cheese spread
directions: Mix all in a blender or food processor.

title: pizza dip
directions: Combine cream cheese, sour cream, oregano and garlic.
Mix well and spread on pie plate up the sides like pizza crust.
Spread pizza sauce in center of pie plate.
Sprinkle pepperoni, onion and green pepper over top.
Bake 10 minutes at 350°.
Top with cheese and melt.
Serve with pieces of crusty bread.

title: sausage balls
directions: Grate cheese.
Mix cheese and sausage.
Add flour; mix well. Shape into small balls.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: beef casserole
directions: Saute beef in cooking oil;
drain fat.	Place beef in a casserole dish.
Place layer of sliced onion over beef.
Place layer
of
Tater
Gems
over
onion.
Pour	soup over this and cover.
Cook at 350° for 1 hour.

title: mile high strawberry dessert
directions: Crust:
Mix vanilla wafer crumbs with the melted margarine. Cover bottom only of 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: "ice it hot cake"
directions: Pour hot water, cocoa and margarine
over sugar and flour. Begin mixing with beater.
Add eggs, buttermilk, baking soda and vanilla.
Beat good.
Bake at 375° for 40 minutes.

title: barbecued chicken wings(best ever)
directions: Mix all ingredients except wings together and pour over chicken. Dot with butter. Bake at 400° for 1 1/2 hours.
Turn occasionally while baking.

title: tia maria chocolate cake
directions: Lightly oil Bundt mold and set aside.
Sift granulated sugar, flour, cocoa, baking powder, salt and powdered almonds into bowl of mixer.
Using dough hook, mix at low speed 2 minutes.
Add butter to bowl.
Continue to mix at medium speed until well mixed. Reduce speed to low.
Add Tia Maria and blend for 1 minute.
At medium speed, add yolks and whole eggs; beat for 5 minutes.
Using a spatula, fold in stiff egg whites until mixed well.
Pour into mold.
Cool for 40 minutes at 350° until knife inserted comes out clean.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Mix together all ingredients; put in ungreased loaf pan. Bake at 325° approximately 45 minutes or until done.

title: beef kabobs
directions: Cut meat into 1-inch cubes and marinate in sauce 4 hours or overnight in the refrigerator.
Alternately lace the vegetables and meat cubes onto 18-inch skewers.
Baste the shish kabobs with sauce and place on grill over glowing coals.
Turn and baste frequently.
Cook 20 minutes or until tender.
Push off onto plates and serve hot.
Pass the heated sauce.

title: marinated peppers a la danby
directions: Cut peppers in half lengthwise. Remove the stems, seeds and membranes. Slice into 3/4-inch strips. Cook in olive oil in skillet, covered, over low heat for 8 minutes or a little longer. Stir occasionally to prevent browning. Peppers should still have a crunch to them. Add the vinegar, sugar and oregano and stir. Cook 2 to 3 minutes more. Serve warm or chilled.

title: make ahead roast beef
directions: Cut as much fat as possible off the roast beef and discard the fat.
Heat the vegetable oil in heavy Dutch oven pan.
Brown the meat on all sides quickly over high heat.
Take the meat out of the pan and clean out the excess oil.
Puree the onions with 3/4 cup water in a blender.
Put the meat and onion mixtures back in your pot.
Cover and cook on low heat for 2 1/2 hours.
Take the meat out of the pot and cool it off and place in refrigerator overnight. Put all the juice from the roast beef with onions separately in the refrigerator.

title: rabbit in wine
directions: Cut rabbit in serving size pieces.
Brown pieces in half of the melted margarine and the bacon fat.
Remove from pan and place on waxed paper.
Add the remainder of the margarine to the pan and saute onions.
Add rabbit, salt and pepper, nutmeg, bay leaves, wine and a cup of water.
Stir well.
Cover and let simmer 1 1/2 to 2 hours, stirring occasionally.
Add a little extra water or wine if liquid cooks away and mixture appears too dry.
Remove bay leaves and add cup hot water.

title: easy strawberry pie
directions: Mix ingredients and pour into pie shell.
Chill and top with whipped cream.
Garnish with extra strawberries.

title: cream of broccoli soup
directions: Wash and clean broccoli, then cut up. Combine broccoli in medium pan with onion, thyme and chicken broth.
Bring to boil until broccoli is soft.
Remove from stove.
Reserve a cup of the broccoli for later use.
Transfer remaining broccoli mixture to blender.
Whirl until pureed.
In a 4-quart pan, melt butter over medium heat.
Stir in flour, salt, mace, nutmeg and pepper.
Cook until bubbly.
Remove from heat.
Stir in half and half.
Blend in broccoli.
Heat again and add cheese (do not boil).
Makes about 6 servings.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Melt the butter in a saucepan.
In a bowl, cream the brown and granulated sugars with the eggs.
Add salt and baking powder.
Mix soda with the boiling water; then add this to the mixture.
Add milk, vanilla and melted butter.
Now add flour a little at a time.
The mixture will be very stiff (hand mixer will not handle it).
After you are sure all flour is mixed well, stir in chocolate chips.
Grease cookie sheet lightly.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: eggs in a basket with cinnamon circles
directions: Take a slice of bread and, using a circle cookie cutter, cut the shape of a circle from the middle of the bread.
Set circle aside.
Butter both sides of remaining bread and place over medium heat.
Put a dab of butter in the center of the circle and melt. Crack an egg into the center of the bread in the circle.
Brown one side, then flip and brown the other.
When done, butter both sides of extra bread circle.
Slightly brown on both sides, then sprinkle with cinnamon and sugar.

title: dumplings
directions: Sift flour, baking powder and salt together, add beaten egg and
warm
water, stir well.
Knead until smooth and free from lumps.
Divide
the
dough into several small pieces and wrap around
a
prune (dried ones that have been cooked until tender and
well
drained).
Cook
in
boiling
water
5 to 6 minutes or until done.
If you desire, you may butter them and top them with cottage cheese.

title: chocolate cream cake
directions: Prepare cake mix as for pound cake recipe on back of box in 3 round layers and cool.

title: best ever candy corn
directions: Keep popped corn crisp in slow oven (300° to 325°).
In a large
saucepan,
combine
sugar,
syrup,
water, butter and salt. Cook
over
moderate heat, stirring occasionally, until syrup reaches soft-crack stage (290°).
Remove from heat; stir in 1 tablespoon vanilla.
In a large buttered bowl or pan, mix nuts and popcorn.
Pour
syrup
in
fine
steam
over mixture. Working quickly, mix well until kernels are completely coated. Spread
out thin
on
buttered
cookie
sheets
or
platters. Quickly separate
into
bite
size	clusters
with 2 buttered forks. Cool.
Makes about 3 1/2 quarts.

title: applesauce oatmeal muffins
directions: Combine oats, flour, cinnamon, baking powder and baking soda. In separate bowl, mix applesauce, milk, brown sugar, oil and egg white.
Mix with dry ingredients and fill muffin cups.
Combine remaining ingredients and sprinkle over batter.
Bake 20 to 22 minutes at 400°.
Yield:
12 muffins.

title: applesauce muffins
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake in greased muffin tins at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes, until golden brown.

title: simple rice pudding
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large casserole.
Bake in 350° oven until thick and the top is brown (1 to 1 1/2 hours).
Great when served with vanilla ice cream!

title: berry dips
directions: Mix half of the whipped topping and orange peel in small bowl. Mix remaining whipped topping, strawberries and yogurt in separate bowl.
Dip with whole strawberries, peaches or melon slices and cake cubes into mixture/mixtures.
Makes 5 1/4 cups. Store leftover dips in refrigerator.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Or use any combination of vegetables.

title: frog-eye salad
directions: Boil noodles in salted water until tender.

Drape cotton dish towel over colander to drain noodles, rinse with cold water. Drain mandarin oranges, but reserve juice of all three pineapples. Cook pineapple juice, sugar, flour, eggs and lemon juice until thick.
Pour over cooked noodles and let set overnight.
Add all fruit, Cool Whip, marshmallows and coconut to taste.
Makes large salad.

title: lasagna
directions: Cook noodles as directed; drain and lay flat on wax paper. Brown ground beef, then mix meat and spaghetti sauce.
Mix egg and cottage cheese.
Spread a thin layer of sauce in bottom of 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Top with single layer of noodles and spread a thin layer of cottage cheese mixture.
Sprinkle with cheese. Repeat layers, ending with a layer of cheese.
Bake at 375° for 40 minutes.

title: blueberry crisp
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Place berries in 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Mix sugar, flour, margarine and salt together with fork or blend
with mixer.
Sprinkle over the berries.
Bake for 1 hour. Yields 6 servings.
May substitute other berries.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serve with your favorite crackers.

title: pizza dip
directions: Brown hamburger meat and onions and drain.
Add other ingredients and microwave until cheese is melted.
Stir and serve hot with slices of French bread.

title: double treat peanut butter cookies
directions: In a medium bowl, combine flour, baking soda, salt and baking powder.
In a large bowl, cream shortening; add sugars beating until light and fluffy.
Blend in peanut butter gradually.
Add vanilla.
Add dry ingredients, beat until blended.
Stir in chocolate chips.
Drop by teaspoon onto ungreased cookie sheet. Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 350°.
Cool 1 minute and remove from pan.

title: apple pie filling
directions: Combine sugar, cinnamon, salt, cornstarch, water and lemon juice.
Cool this only until it starts to thicken. Pour over apples in jars, leaving 1 1/2-inches from top for swelling.
Seal. Process in hot water bath for 25 minutes.

title: apple dumplings
directions: Mash out biscuits. Put 1/4 apple in center of biscuit and wrap biscuit around apple. Lay in pan. Sprinkle with cinnamon. Bake at 325° for 10 minutes. Boil water with butter. Add sugar. Stir until sugar is dissolved. Pour over biscuits. Put back in oven and cook approximately 40 minutes.

title: layered italian casserole
directions: Brown garlic in oil.
Add celery and sauce. Heat.
Broil sausage 15 minutes.
Cool.
Slice.
Brown and drain ground beef. Boil noodles until tender.
Rinse.
Pour 3/4 cup sauce in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Add layer of 1/3 noodles, 1/3 Parmesan, 1/2 Mozzarella, Ricotta, ground beef and sausage.
Repeat, ending with noodles, Parmesan and sauce.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: hot chocolate
directions: Combine ingredients and mix 1/3 cup mix per cup hot water.

title: french onion soup
directions: Cook onions and margarine until onions are tender.
Add remaining ingredients and cook until bubbly.
Serve with dash of Parmesan cheese on top.

title: peanut butter bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Combine flour, baking powder and salt. Set aside.
Heat peanut butter and butter until melted.
Stir in sugar, eggs and vanilla. Add flour mixture. Bake 25 to 30 minutes.

title: sugarplums
directions: Cream butter thoroughly.
Add sugar slowly; continue beating until mixture is light and crumbly.
Add cream and vanilla; beat until completely blended.
Shape and decorate as desired.
Store in a cool place.

title: cheese danish
directions: Spread 1 can crescent rolls in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix together cream cheese, vanilla, sugar and egg yolk.
Spread over crescent roll base.
Top with 1 can crescent rolls; pinch edges together and brush with egg white.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: vegetable salad
directions: Marinate vegetables in dressing and refrigerate overnight. Serve well chilled.
